"use strict";
module.exports = /*#__PURE__*/JSON.parse('[{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Financial Planning & Analysis","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Quick Insights from Spreadsheets","prompt":"\\"I have a spreadsheet with [describe: e.g., monthly sales for 12 months].\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Identify the top 3 trends\\n2. Create 3 simple charts for my manager\\n3. Explain any unusual patterns in plain language\\n4. Suggest 2 questions I should investigate further\\n\\nData: [paste or describe]\\"","tags":["finance","excel","quick-analysis","non-technical","1-hour"],"best_for":"First-time analysts, small datasets, quick summaries","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"A plain-English readout of the top three trends, three chart specs you can paste into Excel, and two follow-up questions for the business.","inputs":[{"label":"describe: e.g., monthly sales for 12 months"},{"label":"paste or describe"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Excel"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Top 3 trends**\\n1. Revenue grew 14% YoY, accelerating in Q3 (+22% vs. +9% Q1)\\n2. EMEA outpaced APAC for the first time in 18 months\\n3. Promo months (Mar, Sep) drove 31% of annual revenue\\n\\n**Charts to build**\\n- Line: monthly revenue vs. prior year (12 + 12 points)\\n- Stacked bar: revenue by region per quarter\\n- Scatter: promo spend vs. incremental revenue\\n\\n**Unusual pattern:** August dip of −7% breaks the seasonal pattern. Worth asking ops.\\n\\n**Investigate**\\n- Is the August dip a stocking issue or genuine demand?\\n- Does the EMEA acceleration hold without the FX tailwind?","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Financial Planning & Analysis","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Rolling Forecast Model","prompt":"\\"I need to build a rolling forecast model for [product line/region].\\n\\nCurrent situation:\\n- Historical data: [describe]\\n- Planning horizon: [e.g., 12 months]\\n- Key drivers: [seasonality, promotions, market trends]\\n- Constraints: [budget, headcount, etc.]\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Design the forecast structure\\n2. Suggest the best Excel/Google Sheets layout\\n3. Create formulas for key calculations\\n4. Identify risks and sensitivities\\n5. Build a variance analysis template\\n\\nOutput as a step-by-step implementation guide.\\"","tags":["forecasting","excel","financial-modeling","planning","half-day"],"best_for":"FP&A analysts, business controllers, budget managers","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"A structured 5-step build plan: model layout, formula spec, risk table, and a variance-analysis template — all wired to your historicals.","inputs":[{"label":"product line/region"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"e.g., 12 months"},{"label":"seasonality, promotions, market trends"},{"label":"budget, headcount, etc."}],"tools":["Claude","Excel","Google Sheets"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Sheet structure**\\n- `Drivers` — assumptions table (one column per month, FY+1 rolling)\\n- `P&L` — revenue waterfall, cost of sales, opex, operating profit\\n- `Variance` — actuals vs. forecast, with auto-coloured deltas\\n- `Scenarios` — base / upside / downside via INDEX/CHOOSE\\n\\n**Key formulas**\\n```\\nRevenue = Units × Price × (1 + Seasonality_Idx)\\nGM%     = (Revenue − COGS) / Revenue\\nF\'cast  = IF(MONTH(TODAY()) ≥ B$3, Actual, Driver-based)\\n```\\n\\n**Risks & sensitivities**\\n1. Price elasticity unknown — model ±5%, ±10%\\n2. Promo cannibalisation — flag if uplift < 40%\\n3. FX exposure on EMEA revenue — hedge above $X","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Financial Planning & Analysis","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Automated FP&A Pipeline","prompt":"\\"I\'m building an automated FP&A pipeline using Python. The system needs to:\\n\\n1. Ingest data from [ERP/source system]\\n2. Clean and validate financial data\\n3. Run predictive models for [forecast type]\\n4. Generate automated reports (PowerPoint/Excel)\\n5. Alert on anomalies\\n6. Maintain audit trail\\n\\nCurrent tech stack: [your tools]\\nData sources: [list]\\nPain points: [describe manual work]\\n\\nPlease provide:\\n- System architecture\\n- Python code skeleton with error handling\\n- Data validation rules\\n- Testing strategy\\n- Deployment approach\\n- Documentation template\\"","tags":["python","automation","data-pipeline","fp&a","multi-week","production"],"best_for":"Data engineers, senior analysts, technical finance leads","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"A production-ready Python architecture: ingestion, validation, forecasting, alerting, and audit trail — with a deployment plan and testing strategy.","inputs":[{"label":"ERP/source system"},{"label":"forecast type"},{"label":"your tools"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"describe manual work"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel","Python"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Architecture**\\n```\\nERP → Ingest (Airflow) → Validate (Great Expectations)\\n    → Transform (dbt) → Forecast (Prophet/SARIMA)\\n    → Report (python-pptx) → Alert (Slack/Email)\\n```\\n\\n**Code skeleton — validation step**\\n```python\\nfrom great_expectations.dataset import PandasDataset\\n\\ndef validate(df: pd.DataFrame) -> ValidationResult:\\n    ds = PandasDataset(df)\\n    ds.expect_column_values_to_not_be_null(\\"account_id\\")\\n    ds.expect_column_values_to_be_between(\\"amount\\", -1e9, 1e9)\\n    ds.expect_column_values_to_match_regex(\\"period\\", r\\"^\\\\d{4}-\\\\d{2}$\\")\\n    return ds.validate()\\n```\\n\\n**Testing:** 80%+ coverage on transforms; smoke-test full pipeline on synthetic 100-row sample daily.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Financial Planning & Analysis","skill_level":"EXPERT","skill_emoji":"⚫","title":"Enterprise Financial Platform","prompt":"\\"Design an enterprise financial planning platform for a [industry] company with:\\n\\nScale:\\n- [X] business units\\n- [X] currencies\\n- [X] users (planners, approvers, viewers)\\n- [X] GB/TB of historical data\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Multi-scenario planning (base, upside, downside)\\n- Real-time consolidation\\n- Workflow approvals\\n- Version control\\n- Integration with [ERP/CRM/etc.]\\n- GDPR/SOX compliance\\n- Self-service reporting\\n\\nPlease provide:\\n- Architecture diagram (describe)\\n- Technology stack recommendation\\n- Data model\\n- Security framework\\n- Implementation phases (12-18 months)\\n- Team structure and hiring plan\\n- Total cost of ownership\\"","tags":["enterprise","architecture","financial-platform","strategy","multi-year","cto-level"],"best_for":"CFOs, VP Finance, Enterprise Architects","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"An 18-month transformation plan: architecture, stack, data model, security framework, hiring plan, and total cost of ownership.","inputs":[{"label":"industry"},{"label":"X"},{"label":"ERP/CRM/etc."}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-year","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Phases**\\n1. Months 0–3: Foundation — data warehouse (Snowflake), identity (Okta), governance.\\n2. Months 4–9: Core planning — Anaplan/Pigment migration, workflow approvals, multi-currency.\\n3. Months 10–14: Self-service — Power BI semantic layer, exec dashboards.\\n4. Months 15–18: AI overlay — forecast assistance, anomaly detection.\\n\\n**Stack:** Snowflake · dbt · Anaplan · Power BI · Okta · GitHub Actions\\n\\n**Org:** 1 Director, 3 Senior FP&A, 2 Data Eng, 1 Solutions Architect, 1 PM\\n\\n**TCO (3-yr):** $4.8–6.2 M (60% software, 30% people, 10% integrators)","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Sales & Market Analysis","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Customer Feedback Summary","prompt":"\\"I need to analyze customer feedback from [surveys/reviews/calls].\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Summarize main themes in simple language\\n2. Identify top 5 complaints\\n3. Suggest 3 quick wins\\n4. Create a simple tracking template\\n\\nFeedback samples: [paste 5-10 examples]\\"","tags":["sales","customer-insights","feedback-analysis","quick-win","1-hour"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"Five clustered themes, the top five complaints with frequency, three quick wins, and a tracking template — drawn from your raw verbatims.","inputs":[{"label":"surveys/reviews/calls"},{"label":"paste 5-10 examples"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"30 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Themes** (n=87 verbatims)\\n- Onboarding friction (34%)\\n- Slow support response (22%)\\n- Missing integrations (18%)\\n- Pricing clarity (15%)\\n- Performance lag (11%)\\n\\n**Top complaints**\\n1. \\"Couldn\'t find where to start\\" — 28 mentions\\n2. \\"Waited 3+ days for a reply\\" — 19 mentions\\n3. \\"Doesn\'t connect to Slack\\" — 14 mentions\\n\\n**Quick wins**\\n- Add a guided first-run checklist (kills #1)\\n- Auto-acknowledge tickets within 5 min (softens #2)\\n- Build the Slack integration (clears #3)","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["perplexity","claude","elicit"]},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Sales & Market Analysis","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Competitive Analysis","prompt":"\\"I need to analyze our competitive position in [market] for [product category].\\n\\nAvailable data:\\n- Our sales data: [describe]\\n- Competitor public info: [list]\\n- Market reports: [if any]\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. SWOT analysis framework\\n2. Competitive pricing comparison\\n3. Market share estimation approach\\n4. 3 strategic scenarios with pros/cons\\n\\nOutput as a structured analysis for leadership.\\"","tags":["strategy","competitive-intelligence","market-analysis","presentation","half-day"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"A SWOT, a pricing comparison, a market-share approach, and three strategic scenarios with pros/cons — packaged for the leadership memo.","inputs":[{"label":"market"},{"label":"product category"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"if any"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**SWOT (you vs. top 3)**\\n| | Strengths | Weaknesses |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| You | Product depth, NPS 62 | Slow GTM, no SMB pricing |\\n| Comp A | Brand, channel | Bloated UX |\\n| Comp B | Price, speed | Thin enterprise feature set |\\n\\n**Pricing band:** $49–$199/mo. You sit at $129 — premium-mid.\\n\\n**Scenarios**\\n1. Hold the line, fortify enterprise — defensible, slow growth.\\n2. Launch SMB tier @ $39 — opens TAM 3×, risks cannibalisation.\\n3. Acquire Comp B — instant channel, $80–120M, ~6 months to close.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["perplexity","claude","elicit"]},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Sales & Market Analysis","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Real-Time Market Intelligence Dashboard","prompt":"\\"Build a real-time market intelligence dashboard using [Python/JS/PowerBI].\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Track competitor pricing across [channels]\\n- Monitor review sentiment on [platforms]\\n- Alert on price changes (>5%)\\n- Generate weekly reports\\n- Integrate with [CRM/ERP]\\n\\nData sources: [web scraping/APIs/exports]\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Technical architecture\\n- Data pipeline code\\n- Dashboard wireframes\\n- Maintenance procedures\\n- Cost estimates\\"","tags":["dashboard","real-time","competitive-intel","python","javascript","multi-week"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"A full technical spec: scraping infra, data pipeline, alert thresholds, dashboard wireframe, and a cost estimate.","inputs":[{"label":"Python/JS/PowerBI"},{"label":"channels"},{"label":"platforms"},{"label":"CRM/ERP"},{"label":"web scraping/APIs/exports"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","JavaScript","Power BI","Python"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Pipeline**\\n```\\nSources (Bright Data / RSS / APIs)\\n  → Queue (SQS) → Workers (Python, 5 replicas)\\n  → DB (Postgres) → API (FastAPI) → UI (Next.js + Tremor)\\n```\\n\\n**Alerts**\\n- Price change ≥5% within 24h → Slack #commercial\\n- New review with rating ≤2 → Slack #cx\\n- Competitor pricing page hash change → Email + Slack\\n\\n**Cost:** ~$420/mo (scraping $180, infra $140, monitoring $100). Maintenance: 4 hrs/week.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["perplexity","claude","elicit"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Operations & Supply Chain","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Process Improvement Ideas","prompt":"\\"I want to improve our [inventory/service/production] process.\\n\\nCurrent process: [describe briefly]\\nMain problems: [list 2-3]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Suggest 3 improvement ideas\\n2. Create a before/after comparison\\n3. Draft an email to propose this\\n4. List what data to track\\"","tags":["operations","process-improvement","lean","quick-win","1-hour"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"Three concrete improvement ideas, a before/after side-by-side, a proposal email draft, and the metrics worth tracking.","inputs":[{"label":"inventory/service/production"},{"label":"describe briefly"},{"label":"list 2-3"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"30 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Three ideas**\\n1. **Batch the daily count** into one end-of-shift sweep (saves ~40 min/day).\\n2. **QR-tag the top-50 SKUs** so receiving scans instead of types.\\n3. **Auto-reorder** at min level via shared sheet (no more stockouts).\\n\\n**Before → After**\\n- Manual count, 5×/day → 1 scan, end-of-shift\\n- Receiving avg time: 12 min → 4 min\\n- Stockouts/month: 7 → ≤1\\n\\n**Email draft**\\n> Hi [manager], I\'ve mapped three changes to receiving that could save ~15 hrs/week without new tooling. Quick run-through Friday at 2pm?","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notebooklm"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Operations & Supply Chain","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Supply Chain Optimization","prompt":"\\"I need to optimize [supply chain/inventory/distribution] for [region/product].\\n\\nCurrent state:\\n- [X] SKUs\\n- [X] warehouses\\n- Lead times: [describe]\\n- Inventory costs: [describe]\\n\\nConstraints:\\n- Budget: [range]\\n- Timeline: [deadline]\\n- Service level target: [X%]\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Analyze inefficiencies\\n2. Propose 3 optimization scenarios\\n3. Calculate approximate ROI\\n4. Create implementation roadmap\\n5. Identify risks and mitigation\\"","tags":["supply-chain","operations-research","roi","optimization","half-day"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"An inefficiency map, three optimisation scenarios with ROI math, an implementation roadmap, and a risk register.","inputs":[{"label":"supply chain/inventory/distribution"},{"label":"region/product"},{"label":"X"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"range"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"plan","sample_output":"**Inefficiencies found**\\n- 38% of SKUs sit in 2+ warehouses unnecessarily (carrying cost: $1.2M/yr)\\n- Lead time variance 4–18 days on a single supplier\\n- Safety stock set on rule-of-thumb, not service-level math\\n\\n**Scenarios**\\n| | Cost | Annual saving | Service level |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| Consolidate to 3 DCs | $2.1M one-time | $1.8M | 97% |\\n| Add 4th regional DC | $3.4M one-time | $2.6M | 99% |\\n| Optimise w/o new DCs | $200k | $0.9M | 96% |\\n\\n**Risk:** scenario 1 risks weather concentration on the Memphis hub.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notebooklm"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Customer Support","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Response Templates","prompt":"\\"I handle customer service. I often get questions about [topic].\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Draft 5 standard responses\\n2. Create a troubleshooting flowchart for [issue]\\n3. Suggest information to collect\\n4. Write a team FAQ\\"","tags":["customer-service","templates","troubleshooting","training","1-hour"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"Five reusable response templates, a troubleshooting flowchart for your common issue, an info-collection checklist, and a team FAQ.","inputs":[{"label":"topic"},{"label":"issue"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Templates**\\n1. **Acknowledgement** — \\"Got it, [name]. Looking into it now — back to you within 2 hours.\\"\\n2. **Asking for more info** — \\"Quick thing to unblock me: could you send [X, Y]?\\"\\n3. **Known issue** — \\"Yep, known one — fix is going out [date]. Workaround: [...]\\"\\n4. **Escalation** — \\"Pulling in [team]. Owner is [name]. Updates in this thread.\\"\\n5. **Resolution** — \\"[Fix] is live. Anything else from this ticket?\\"\\n\\n**Flowchart** (login issue): Reset password? → Y: send link / N: 2FA enrolled? → Y: code working? → escalate.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notion-ai"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Customer Support","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"First Contact Resolution","prompt":"\\"I want to improve first-contact resolution in customer support.\\n\\nCurrent metrics:\\n- FCR rate: [X%]\\n- Avg handle time: [X min]\\n- CSAT: [X/10]\\n\\nCommon issues: [list categories]\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Design a decision tree\\n2. Create response templates by type\\n3. Suggest training topics\\n4. Propose KPIs\\n5. Build quality monitoring checklist\\"","tags":["customer-service","quality","metrics","training","half-day"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"A decision tree, type-specific response templates, training topics, KPIs, and a quality monitoring checklist.","inputs":[{"label":"X%"},{"label":"X min"},{"label":"X/10"},{"label":"list categories"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Decision tree (login)**\\n```\\nIssue → Account locked?\\n├─ Y → Unlock + send reset → Resolved\\n└─ N → 2FA enrolled?\\n    ├─ Y → Codes working? → escalate L2 if no\\n    └─ N → Enrol + verify → Resolved\\n```\\n\\n**KPIs:** FCR (target 78%), AHT (≤6 min), CSAT (≥4.4/5), repeat-contact rate (≤8%).\\n\\n**QA checklist (per ticket)**\\n- [ ] Asked the diagnostic Q first\\n- [ ] Verified identity\\n- [ ] Logged root cause code\\n- [ ] Sent confirmation summary","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notion-ai"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Customer Support","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"AI Support Assistant","prompt":"\\"Build an AI-powered customer support assistant that can:\\n\\n1. Classify tickets by urgency and topic\\n2. Suggest solutions from knowledge base\\n3. Draft personalized responses\\n4. Escalate complex issues\\n5. Learn from corrections\\n\\nIntegration:\\n- Connect to [ticketing system]\\n- Access [knowledge base]\\n- Work in [language]\\n- GDPR compliant\\n\\nProvide:\\n- NLP pipeline architecture\\n- Training data requirements\\n- Model selection\\n- Implementation phases\\n- Success metrics\\"","tags":["ai-ml","nlp","customer-service","automation","multi-week","production"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"An NLP pipeline architecture, training-data requirements, model selection, phased rollout, and success metrics.","inputs":[{"label":"ticketing system"},{"label":"knowledge base"},{"label":"language"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Architecture**\\n```\\nTicket → Classifier (BERT, 12 classes)\\n       → KB retriever (embeddings + reranker)\\n       → Drafter (LLM, brand-tuned)\\n       → Human-in-loop (L1 review for low-confidence)\\n       → Send / Escalate\\n```\\n\\n**Training data:** ~5k labelled tickets minimum; 80/10/10 split; include 200 hard negatives.\\n\\n**Rollout:** shadow-mode (4 wk) → suggest-only (8 wk) → auto-send tier-1 (gated by confidence ≥0.92).","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notion-ai"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"AI-Assisted Variance Analysis","prompt":"\\"I just closed the month and need to explain budget vs. actual variances to my manager.\\n\\nData:\\n- Budget: [amount or file]\\n- Actual: [amount or file]\\n- Key categories: [list]\\n- Previous month: [for comparison]\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Identify the top 5 variances (positive and negative)\\n2. Write 2-3 sentence explanations for each\\n3. Flag which ones need action vs. which are noise\\n4. Draft the email/update for my manager\\n5. Suggest follow-up questions to ask the business\\"","tags":["fp&a","variance-analysis","month-end","beginner","1-hour"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"The top five variances with one-paragraph explanations, an action vs. noise call on each, and a ready-to-send manager email.","inputs":[{"label":"amount or file"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"for comparison"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Top 5 variances (Oct vs. budget)**\\n| Account | Var | Driver |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| Subscription rev | +$340k | Renewal pull-forward, treat as timing |\\n| Cloud infra | +$190k | Workload spike from new feature — investigate |\\n| T&E | −$60k | Conf budget unspent — flag for reforecast |\\n| Stock comp | +$110k | New hires — already accrued, noise |\\n| Hosting | +$45k | Egress overage — review architecture |\\n\\n**Action vs noise:** rows 2 and 5 need follow-up; the rest are timing/accrual noise.\\n\\n**Manager email:** drafted, ~120 words, ready to copy.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Automated Commentary Writing","prompt":"\\"I need to write monthly financial commentary for [report/steerco].\\n\\nData available:\\n- P&L summary\\n- Key metrics (revenue, margin, opex)\\n- Variance to budget and prior year\\n- Business highlights\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Draft executive summary (3-4 bullets)\\n2. Write narrative for each section\\n3. Use professional but concise language\\n4. Highlight red flags\\n5. Suggest graphics/tables to include\\"","tags":["fp&a","commentary","reporting","writing","1-hour"],"best_for":"FP&A analysts spending hours writing commentary","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance","outcome":"An executive-summary block, narrative sections for each P&L line, professional phrasing, red-flag highlights, and graphic suggestions.","inputs":[{"label":"report/steerco"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"table","sample_output":"**Executive summary**\\n- Revenue $42.1M, +6.2% YoY, in line with budget\\n- GM% 68.1%, +120bps vs. prior year — pricing actions holding\\n- Opex tracking $0.4M favourable; hiring lag in R&D\\n- Operating income $12.6M; FX headwind of −$0.3M absorbed\\n\\n**Revenue narrative**\\n> Subscription revenue grew 9% YoY, offsetting a 4% decline in services. New-logo ARR up 14%, but expansion softened to 11% (vs. 16% prior quarter), consistent with the broader macro slowdown observed by peers.\\n\\n**Red flag:** R&D under-hire risks Q1 product timeline.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"AI-Powered Forecasting Assistant","prompt":"\\"I need to build/update a forecast with AI assistance.\\n\\nHistorical data:\\n- [X] months of actuals\\n- Seasonality patterns\\n- Known one-off events\\n\\nCurrent forecast:\\n- Budget: [amount]\\n- Current projection: [amount]\\n- Risk factors: [list]\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Analyze historical trends\\n2. Identify seasonality and patterns\\n3. Adjust for known events\\n4. Generate 3 scenarios (base/upside/downside)\\n5. Write the forecast narrative\\n6. Create summary for leadership\\n\\nOutput in structured format with formulas if applicable.\\"","tags":["fp&a","forecasting","scenario-planning","intermediate","half-day"],"best_for":"Business controllers, FP&A managers doing rolling forecasts","source":"Inside FP&A — \\"How AI is Changing FP&A\\"","outcome":"A trend + seasonality breakdown, adjustments for known events, three scenarios, and the narrative for leadership.","inputs":[{"label":"X"},{"label":"amount"},{"label":"list"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Trend & seasonality**\\n- 18-month CAGR: +12% (2.4% MoM)\\n- Seasonality peak: Nov–Dec (+38% vs. trailing 3 mo)\\n- Soft month: Feb (−18%)\\n\\n**Scenarios (FY+1)**\\n| | Revenue | GM% | OI |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| Base | $186M | 67% | $42M |\\n| Upside (Enterprise +20%) | $204M | 69% | $52M |\\n| Downside (Churn 2pp) | $171M | 65% | $35M |\\n\\n**Narrative:** \\"Base assumes 11% growth, in line with H2 run rate. Upside flips on enterprise pipeline conversion above 32% — feasible if security review accelerates.\\"*","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Financial Modeling with AI","prompt":"\\"I\'m building a financial model for [purpose: M&A/new product/investment].\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- 3-statement model (P&L, BS, CF)\\n- 5-year projection\\n- Sensitivity analysis\\n- Key assumptions clearly documented\\n\\nCurrent stage: [blank template / partial model / needs review]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Structure the model layout\\n2. Build core formulas and drivers\\n3. Create assumption tables\\n4. Add sensitivity tables (±10%, ±20%)\\n5. Build summary dashboard\\n6. Add error checks and validations\\n7. Write documentation\\n\\nFormat: [Excel/Google Sheets]\\n\\nInclude:\\n- Color coding scheme\\n- Formula explanations\\n- Circularity handling\\n- Audit trail\\"","tags":["fp&a","financial-modeling","excel","intermediate","half-day"],"best_for":"FP&A managers, corporate development, investment analysts","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance","outcome":"A complete 3-statement model spec: structure, drivers, sensitivities, dashboard, audit checks, and documentation.","inputs":[{"label":"purpose: M&A/new product/investment"},{"label":"blank template / partial model / needs review"},{"label":"Excel/Google Sheets"}],"tools":["Claude","Excel","Google Sheets"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Tabs**\\n1. `Cover` — purpose, version, owner\\n2. `Drivers` — colour-coded inputs (blue)\\n3. `P&L`, `BS`, `CF` — links only (black), no hardcodes\\n4. `Sensitivity` — ±10/20% on revenue growth × GM\\n5. `Checks` — 6 integrity rules (BS balances, CF reconciles)\\n\\n**Driver math (revenue)**\\n```\\nRev_t = Cust_t × ARPU_t\\nCust_t = Cust_{t-1} × (1 − Churn_t) + NewLogo_t\\n```\\n\\n**Checks:** all return PASS or the cell turns red. Circularity resolved with iterative calc, max 100, threshold 0.001.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Board Presentation Builder","prompt":"\\"I need to create a board/executive presentation on [financial topic].\\n\\nAudience: [Board/CFO/CEO]\\nTime: [X minutes]\\nKey message: [one sentence]\\nData available: [describe]\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. Story arc (beginning, middle, end)\\n2. Slide-by-slide outline\\n3. Key charts/visuals to include\\n4. Speaker notes with timing\\n5. Appendix with backup data\\n6. Q&A preparation (anticipate 5 questions)\\n\\nMake it:\\n- Executive-level (not operational)\\n- Visual and scannable\\n- Persuasive, not just informative\\n- Action-oriented\\"","tags":["fp&a","presentation","board","executive","storytelling","half-day"],"best_for":"Directors and VPs presenting to C-suite","source":"Inside FP&A","outcome":"A story arc, slide-by-slide outline, chart picks, timed speaker notes, a backup appendix, and five anticipated questions with answers.","inputs":[{"label":"financial topic"},{"label":"Board/CFO/CEO"},{"label":"X minutes"},{"label":"one sentence"},{"label":"describe"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Story arc**\\n1. Where we are (one slide, one number)\\n2. What changed since last board (3 deltas)\\n3. What\'s working / what isn\'t\\n4. The decision we\'re asking for\\n5. What happens if you say yes\\n\\n**Slides** (15 min total)\\n1. Title + headline number (45s)\\n2. Q3 scorecard vs. plan (90s)\\n3. The two wins (2 min)\\n4. The two concerns (2 min)\\n5. Pricing decision — recommendation (3 min)\\n6. Asks + timeline (1 min)\\n\\n**Anticipated Q1:** \\"What\'s the downside case?\\" — answer prepped, 2 sentences + 1 backup slide.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"FP&A Process Automation","prompt":"\\"I want to automate [specific FP&A process] that currently takes [X hours/week].\\n\\nCurrent process:\\n1. [Manual step 1]\\n2. [Manual step 2]\\n3. [Manual step 3]\\n\\nInputs: [data sources]\\nOutputs: [deliverables]\\nFrequency: [monthly/weekly/ad-hoc]\\n\\nPlease design:\\n1. Process map (as-is vs. to-be)\\n2. Automation approach\\n3. Tool selection (Excel macros/Python/Power Automate)\\n4. Error handling\\n5. Validation checks\\n6. Documentation\\n7. Change management plan\\n\\nFocus on:\\n- Audit trail\\n- Data integrity\\n- Scalability\\n- Maintainability\\"","tags":["fp&a","automation","process-improvement","advanced","multi-week"],"best_for":"Senior FP&A managers, finance transformation leads","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance + Inside FP&A","outcome":"A process map (as-is vs. to-be), automation approach, tool selection, error handling, validation, and a change-management plan.","inputs":[{"label":"specific FP&A process"},{"label":"X hours/week"},{"label":"Manual step 1"},{"label":"Manual step 2"},{"label":"Manual step 3"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel","Python"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"plan","sample_output":"**As-is (12 hrs/wk)**\\n1. Pull exports from SAP, Salesforce, ADP (3 hrs)\\n2. Stitch in Excel (5 hrs)\\n3. Manual variance commentary (3 hrs)\\n4. Format deck (1 hr)\\n\\n**To-be (~1 hr/wk)**\\n1. Python pulls from APIs nightly\\n2. dbt transforms + tests\\n3. LLM drafts commentary from variance table\\n4. python-pptx generates deck\\n\\n**Tool stack:** Python · dbt · Anthropic API · python-pptx · Airflow\\n\\n**Change mgmt:** 4-week parallel run, weekly QA, sign-off from controller before cutover.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"AI-Powered Financial Analysis Pipeline","prompt":"\\"Build an AI-assisted financial analysis system for [company/department].\\n\\nScope:\\n- Monthly variance analysis (automated commentary)\\n- Rolling forecast updates\\n- Scenario modeling\\n- Executive summary generation\\n- Ad-hoc analysis support\\n\\nData sources:\\n- ERP: [system]\\n- BI tool: [system]\\n- Excel files: [describe]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Automated commentary generation\\n- Natural language queries (\\"What drove revenue variance?\\")\\n- Anomaly detection\\n- Trend identification\\n- Predictive alerts\\n\\nProvide:\\n- System architecture\\n- Data pipeline design\\n- AI model selection and training approach\\n- Integration plan\\n- Governance framework\\n- ROI calculation\\"","tags":["fp&a","ai-pipeline","automation","nlp","advanced","multi-month"],"best_for":"Finance transformation teams, data-driven FP&A organizations","source":"Inside FP&A — \\"How AI is Changing FP&A\\"","outcome":"A complete AI-assisted FP&A system: architecture, data pipeline, model selection, integration plan, governance, and ROI math.","inputs":[{"label":"company/department"},{"label":"system"},{"label":"describe"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel"],"est_time":"Multi-month","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Architecture**\\n```\\nERP/BI → Data lake (Snowflake)\\n       → Feature store (Feast)\\n       → LLM layer (Claude / GPT-4) ← embeddings of GL + commentary corpus\\n       → NL query interface (LangChain agent)\\n       → Outputs: commentary, anomaly alerts, forecast deltas\\n```\\n\\n**Governance:** every AI-generated number gets a citation back to the source row; commentary stored with prompt + version hash for audit.\\n\\n**ROI:** ~$240k/yr saved (1.5 FTE equivalent) against $80k build + $35k/yr run cost. Payback < 6 months.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"EXPERT","skill_emoji":"⚫","title":"Enterprise FP&A Transformation","prompt":"\\"Design an AI-enabled FP&A transformation for a [industry] company.\\n\\nCurrent state:\\n- [X] FTEs in FP&A\\n- Manual processes: [list]\\n- Tools: [Excel/SAP/Oracle/etc.]\\n- Cycle times: [describe]\\n\\nTarget state (3-5 years):\\n- Automated forecasting\\n- Self-service analytics\\n- Real-time dashboards\\n- AI-powered insights\\n- Zero-based reporting\\n\\nPlease provide:\\n1. Transformation roadmap (phases)\\n2. Technology stack\\n3. Organization design\\n4. Skill development plan\\n5. Change management approach\\n6. Investment case (cost/benefit)\\n7. Risk assessment\\n8. Success metrics\\n9. Vendor evaluation criteria\\"","tags":["fp&a","transformation","strategy","enterprise","expert","multi-year"],"best_for":"CFOs, VP Finance, Finance Directors leading transformation","source":"Inside FP&A","outcome":"A phased 3–5 year roadmap with org design, tech stack, investment case, risks, vendor criteria, and success metrics.","inputs":[{"label":"industry"},{"label":"X"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"Excel/SAP/Oracle/etc."},{"label":"describe"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel"],"est_time":"Multi-year","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Phases**\\n- Yr 1 — Foundations: cloud DW, identity, governance, dashboarding standard\\n- Yr 2 — Planning: replace spreadsheet plan with Anaplan/Pigment\\n- Yr 3 — AI overlay: automated commentary, anomaly detection, NL queries\\n\\n**Org shift**\\n- FP&A FTEs: 24 → 18 (reskill 6 into analytics engineers)\\n- New roles: 2 ML engineers, 1 finance data steward\\n\\n**Investment case (3-yr)**\\n- Spend: $9.6M\\n- Savings: $14.2M (productivity, cycle-time reduction)\\n- Net: +$4.6M, payback yr 2.5\\n\\n**Risks:** vendor lock-in (mitigate with semantic layer), change fatigue (sequence releases).","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"AI-Powered Spreadsheet Analysis","prompt":"\\"I have a spreadsheet with [describe data]. I need to analyze it using AI.\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Identify trends and patterns\\n2. Highlight anomalies or outliers\\n3. Create summary statistics\\n4. Generate 3 key insights\\n5. Suggest visualizations\\n\\nData context: [industry/business context]\\nFormat: [Excel/Google Sheets]\\n\\nOutput as a structured analysis I can share.\\"","tags":["excel","google-sheets","data-analysis","beginner","1-hour"],"best_for":"Analysts new to AI-assisted spreadsheet work","source":"OpenAI — \\"ChatGPT for Excel and Google Sheets\\"","outcome":"A structured analysis with trends, anomalies, summary stats, three insights, and chart recommendations — shareable as-is.","inputs":[{"label":"describe data"},{"label":"industry/business context"},{"label":"Excel/Google Sheets"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Excel","Google Sheets"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Trends**\\n- Northeast region revenue +18% YoY, leading other regions by 9pp\\n- Q4 still concentrates 38% of annual sales (vs. 34% three years ago)\\n\\n**Anomalies**\\n- Two SKUs (#A23, #A41) show unit volume +200% but revenue flat — pricing issue?\\n- Negative gross margin on three loss-leaders in Mar\\n\\n**Summary stats:** mean order $187, median $124, p90 $412. Long tail dominated by enterprise.\\n\\n**Suggested visuals:** waterfall of YoY revenue by region; scatter of unit volume vs. price for the SKU set.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notebooklm"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Natural Language Excel Updates","prompt":"\\"Update the worksheet tab called @[TAB NAME] with the latest [data type] using [data source].\\n\\nExample: \'Update the worksheet tab called @Balance Sheet - Q with the latest earnings print and transcript commentary using S&P Global\'\\n\\nContext:\\n- Workbook: [name]\\n- Tab: [specific tab]\\n- Data source: [S&P Global/Bloomberg/internal]\\n- Time period: [Q1/Q2/etc.]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Pull latest actuals and replace estimates\\n2. Update column headers (E → A for actual)\\n3. Add variance commentary\\n4. Verify checks = PASS\\n5. Log data sources\\"","tags":["excel","financial-modeling","automation","beginner","fp&a"],"best_for":"FP&A analysts doing quarterly updates","source":"OpenAI — \\"ChatGPT for Excel and Google Sheets\\"","outcome":"Latest actuals pulled into the tab you named, column headers swapped from E → A, variance commentary inline, and a source log appended.","inputs":[{"label":"TAB NAME"},{"label":"data type"},{"label":"data source"},{"label":"name"},{"label":"specific tab"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Excel"],"est_time":"5–10 min","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Updates to @Balance Sheet - Q3**\\n- Q3 actuals replaced estimates in columns C:F (source: S&P Capital IQ, pulled 2026-05-12 09:14 UTC)\\n- Headers: \\"Q3 E\\" → \\"Q3 A\\"\\n- New row: variance commentary\\n- All checks PASS ✓\\n\\n**Variance commentary inserted**\\n> Cash +$28M vs. estimate, driven by working-capital improvement (DSO ↓ 4 days). Long-term debt unchanged. Goodwill recalibrated for the X acquisition.\\n\\n**Source log:** appended to `_meta` tab; includes URL, retrieval time, fields touched.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notebooklm"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"AI-Assisted Financial Model Audit","prompt":"\\"Audit my financial model for consistency and errors.\\n\\nModel details:\\n- Purpose: [DCF/3-statement/budget]\\n- Time horizon: [years]\\n- Key assumptions: [list]\\n- Check cells: [locations]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Verify assumption consistency and sign\\n2. Check formula links and circularities\\n3. Validate check cells = 0 or PASS\\n4. Identify broken links or #REF errors\\n5. Flag unusual patterns (e.g., margins jumping 50%)\\n6. Suggest improvements\\n\\nOutput: Audit report with severity ratings (Critical/Warning/Info)\\"","tags":["excel","financial-modeling","audit","intermediate","fp&a","half-day"],"best_for":"Senior analysts reviewing models before board submission","source":"OpenAI — \\"ChatGPT for Excel and Google Sheets\\"","outcome":"An audit report with severity-tagged findings: assumption consistency, formula integrity, broken links, anomalies, and improvements.","inputs":[{"label":"DCF/3-statement/budget"},{"label":"years"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"locations"}],"tools":["Claude","Excel"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"table","sample_output":"**Critical (3)**\\n- `WACC!C18` references a deleted range — #REF!\\n- BS doesn\'t balance in years 4–5: $1.2M, $0.9M off\\n- Tax rate hard-coded inside a formula in CF tab\\n\\n**Warnings (7)**\\n- Revenue growth jumps 14% → 41% Y3 with no driver explanation\\n- Two circularities resolved silently — flag for review\\n- Three named ranges declared but unused\\n\\n**Info (12)** — naming, colour coding, font drift.\\n\\n**Recommendation:** fix criticals before sending; warnings before signing.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notebooklm"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Power BI Model Optimization with AI","prompt":"\\"Analyze my Power BI model and optimize it.\\n\\nCurrent state:\\n- Tables: [X]\\n- Measures: [X]\\n- Size: [X MB]\\n- Refresh time: [X minutes]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Analyze naming conventions and suggest renames\\n2. Add display folders to organize fields\\n3. Hide foreign key columns (show only friendly names)\\n4. Add descriptions to all measures and columns\\n5. Create user hierarchies for drill-down\\n6. Optimize data types for compression\\n7. Generate complete documentation\\n\\nOutput: Step-by-step implementation guide with DAX code\\"","tags":["powerbi","dax","data-modeling","intermediate","half-day"],"best_for":"BI developers, data modelers","source":"Power BI Bro — \\"Claude + Power BI Integration via MCP\\"","outcome":"A naming + organisation rewrite, hidden FK columns, descriptions on every measure, drill hierarchies, type-optimised columns, and full documentation.","inputs":[{"label":"X"},{"label":"X MB"},{"label":"X minutes"}],"tools":["Claude","Power BI"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Suggested renames**\\n- `fact_sale_qty_v2` → `Sales Quantity`\\n- `dim_cust_full` → `Customer`\\n- `_calc_yoy_pct` → `Revenue YoY %`\\n\\n**Display folders added**\\n- `Sales\\\\Volume` — Units, Returns, Net Units\\n- `Sales\\\\Value` — Revenue, GM, GM%\\n- `Time Intel` — YoY, MTD, QTD measures\\n\\n**Optimisation**\\n- 14 string cols converted to integer keys → file size 89 MB → 41 MB\\n- Refresh time: 14 min → 6 min\\n\\n**Doc output:** 28-page Markdown + Mermaid relationship diagram.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notebooklm"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Create Calculation Table with Measures","prompt":"\\"Create a new empty table to hold calculations, create an aggregate amount calc for every [category] value, create a net calc, and also create a comprehensive group of monthly time intelligence measures for all measures created. Remove/hide any placeholder fields in the new table.\\"","tags":["powerbi","dax","measures","intermediate","quick-win"],"best_for":"BI developers building semantic models","source":"Power BI Bro — \\"Claude + Power BI Integration via MCP\\"","outcome":"A new measure table, an aggregate-amount calc per category value, a Net measure, and a full suite of monthly time-intelligence measures — placeholder fields hidden.","inputs":[{"label":"category"}],"tools":["Claude","Power BI"],"est_time":"30 min","output_kind":"table","sample_output":"**New table:** `_Measures`\\n\\n**Per category:**\\n```dax\\n[Sales — Hardware] = CALCULATE([Sales Amount], \'Product\'[Category] = \\"Hardware\\")\\n[Sales — Software] = CALCULATE([Sales Amount], \'Product\'[Category] = \\"Software\\")\\n[Sales — Services] = CALCULATE([Sales Amount], \'Product\'[Category] = \\"Services\\")\\n```\\n\\n**Net:** `Net Sales = [Sales Amount] − [Returns Amount]`\\n\\n**Time intel (for each measure):** MTD, QTD, YTD, MoM, YoY, Rolling 3M, Rolling 12M.\\n\\nPlaceholder integer column `_placeholder` hidden from report view.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notebooklm"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Cube Function Dashboard (Excel)","prompt":"\\"I want to build a custom dashboard using Excel Cube functions instead of PivotTables.\\n\\nData model: [Power Pivot / SSAS / Power BI]\\nMetrics needed: [list]\\nLayout requirements: [custom spacing, narration, totals]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Create CUBESET for each dimension (months, products, regions)\\n2. Use CUBEMEMBER for row/column labels\\n3. Use CUBEVALUE to pull calculated measures\\n4. Add CUBERANKEDMEMBER for Top N rankings\\n5. Apply conditional formatting with CUBEKPIMEMBER\\n6. Build flexible layout (not PivotTable rigid)\\n\\nProvide: Complete formulas and layout guide\\"","tags":["excel","cube-functions","cubedata","dashboard","intermediate","half-day"],"best_for":"FP&A analysts building custom financial dashboards","source":"Finex Skills Hub — \\"Master 6 Excel Cube Functions\\"","outcome":"A custom Excel cube-function dashboard: CUBESET dimensions, CUBEMEMBER labels, CUBEVALUE measures, Top-N ranks, and KPI conditional formatting.","inputs":[{"label":"Power Pivot / SSAS / Power BI"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"custom spacing, narration, totals"}],"tools":["Claude","Excel","Power BI"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Cell formulas (sample)**\\n```\\nA4:  =CUBEMEMBER(\\"Model\\",\\"[Date].[Calendar].[Month].&[2026-04]\\")\\nB4:  =CUBEVALUE(\\"Model\\",\\"[Measures].[Revenue]\\", A4, $A$1)\\nC4:  =CUBEVALUE(\\"Model\\",\\"[Measures].[Revenue YoY %]\\", A4, $A$1)\\nA20: =CUBERANKEDMEMBER(\\"Model\\",\\"[Product].[Top 10]\\",1)\\n```\\n\\n**Layout:** quarter-bands in rows, scenarios in columns, two narration columns between sections — impossible to do this cleanly with a PivotTable.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notebooklm"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"AI-Powered BI Documentation Generator","prompt":"\\"Generate a Markdown document (.md) that provides complete, professional documentation for the [Power BI Semantic Model / Excel Data Model], including a data dictionary.\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Use a simple mermaid diagram to illustrate table relationships\\n- Document each measure including the DAX code and description of business logic\\n- Use business-friendly names\\n- Document data sources by analyzing the Power Query code\\n- Include executive summary, table of contents, model diagrams\\n- Add usage guidelines and reporting scenarios\\n\\nCurrent model: [describe or attach .pbix]\\n\\nOutput: Enterprise-grade documentation (~60 pages)\\"","tags":["powerbi","documentation","data-dictionary","advanced","multi-day"],"best_for":"BI teams, Center of Excellence leads","source":"Power BI Bro — \\"Claude + Power BI Integration via MCP\\"","outcome":"A complete ~60-page Markdown doc with executive summary, mermaid relationship diagram, per-measure DAX + plain-English business logic, data sources, and usage scenarios.","inputs":[{"label":"Power BI Semantic Model / Excel Data Model"},{"label":"describe or attach .pbix"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel","Power BI"],"est_time":"2–4 days","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Generated Markdown (excerpt)**\\n```markdown\\n## Model overview\\nThis semantic model serves the Commercial Reporting team and powers\\n12 reports, 3 Power BI Apps, and 1 paginated weekly board pack.\\n\\n## Relationship diagram\\n\\\\`\\\\`\\\\`mermaid\\nflowchart LR\\n  Date --> Sales\\n  Customer --> Sales\\n  Product --> Sales\\n  Sales --> InvoiceLine\\n\\\\`\\\\`\\\\`\\n\\n## Measures\\n### Revenue\\n**DAX**\\n\\\\`\\\\`\\\\`dax\\nRevenue = SUMX(\'Sales\', \'Sales\'[Quantity] * \'Sales\'[Unit Price])\\n\\\\`\\\\`\\\\`\\n**Business logic:** sales revenue net of returns, recognised on shipment.\\n```","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notebooklm"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Autonomous Workflow System","prompt":"\\"I want to build [X] proactive AI workflows that run automatically.\\n\\nCurrent manual tasks:\\n1. [Task 1 — frequency]\\n2. [Task 2 — frequency]\\n3. [Task 3 — frequency]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Schedule-based execution (daily/weekly)\\n- Email/rss/notification delivery\\n- Self-directed (no manual kickoff)\\n- Multi-agent coordination\\n\\nExample workflows to replicate:\\n1. Morning briefing (industry news, competitor updates)\\n2. Friday email recap (unresponded urgent emails ranked by urgency)\\n3. Weekly financial summary (variance analysis auto-generated)\\n4. Monday forecast update (rolling forecast refresh)\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Architecture for 36+ workflows\\n- Agent hierarchy design (master agents + sub-agents)\\n- Scheduling framework\\n- Integration approach (Claude Co-work / Codex / Cloud Code)\\n- Monitoring and error handling\\"","tags":["automation","workflows","agents","advanced","productivity","multi-week"],"best_for":"AI power users, productivity hackers, executives","source":"Alli Miller (ex-Amazon AI leader) — \\"Ex-Amazon AI Leader Interview\\"","outcome":"A blueprint for 36+ scheduled AI workflows: agent hierarchy, scheduling, integration with Claude Code / Codex / Cloud Code, monitoring, and error handling.","inputs":[{"label":"X"},{"label":"Task 1 — frequency"},{"label":"Task 2 — frequency"},{"label":"Task 3 — frequency"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Hierarchy**\\n```\\nMaster agent (daily 06:00 UTC)\\n├─ Morning briefing sub-agent → industry news + competitor moves\\n├─ Calendar sub-agent → today\'s meetings + prep\\n└─ Unblocked-tasks sub-agent → cross-checks email + Slack\\n\\nFriday 16:00 UTC\\n└─ Email recap sub-agent → urgent unresponded, ranked\\n```\\n\\n**Stack:** Claude Code + cron + S3 (state) + Slack/email (delivery).\\n\\n**Monitoring:** every run writes structured log; dashboard alerts on >2 consecutive failures or runtime drift >2σ.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notebooklm"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Task & Time Management","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Overwhelm Recovery","prompt":"\\"I feel overwhelmed. I am [role] and struggle with [specific problem].\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Prioritize tasks using a simple framework\\n2. Create a daily/weekly schedule template\\n3. Suggest 3 focus habits\\n4. Recommend tools for [Mac/Windows/Phone]\\"","tags":["productivity","time-management","beginner-friendly","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A prioritisation framework, a daily + weekly schedule template, three focus habits, and platform-specific tool picks.","inputs":[{"label":"role"},{"label":"specific problem"},{"label":"Mac/Windows/Phone"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Prioritisation (Eisenhower + energy)**\\n1. Urgent + important + high-energy first hour\\n2. Important not urgent → schedule into deep-work blocks\\n3. Urgent not important → batch into a 30-min slot\\n4. Neither → delete, don\'t defer\\n\\n**Daily template**\\n- 09:00–10:30 — Deep work block 1 (Slack off, phone away)\\n- 10:30–11:00 — Email / Slack triage\\n- 11:00–12:30 — Deep work block 2\\n- Afternoon: meetings + lighter work\\n\\n**Habits:** (1) inbox-zero by 17:00, (2) one weekly review, (3) 50-min focus, 10-min reset.\\n\\n**Mac tools:** Things 3, Cron, Raycast.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notion-ai"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Task & Time Management","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Personal Productivity System","prompt":"\\"I want to build a personal productivity system.\\n\\nCurrent tools: [Notion/Obsidian/Todoist/etc.]\\nWork style: [remote/hybrid/office]\\nMain challenges: [context switching/meetings/deep work]\\n\\nPlease design:\\n1. PARA-style organization\\n2. Weekly review process\\n3. Meeting notes template\\n4. Project tracking dashboard\\n5. Automation workflows\\n\\nOutput as a setup guide.\\"","tags":["productivity","notion","obsidian","system-design","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A PARA-style organisation scheme, a weekly review process, meeting and project templates, and lightweight automations.","inputs":[{"label":"Notion/Obsidian/Todoist/etc."},{"label":"remote/hybrid/office"},{"label":"context switching/meetings/deep work"}],"tools":["Claude","Notion","Obsidian"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**PARA**\\n- `01-Projects` — active, with a deadline (≤6)\\n- `02-Areas` — ongoing responsibilities (Health, Finance, Team)\\n- `03-Resources` — references you\'ll consult\\n- `04-Archive` — done or paused\\n\\n**Weekly review (Fri 16:00, 45 min)**\\n1. Clear inbox, calendar, and capture tray\\n2. Move stale projects to Archive\\n3. Pick three priorities for next week\\n4. Two-line journal entry\\n\\n**Automation:** Calendar → Notion meeting note auto-created with attendees + agenda block.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notion-ai"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Task & Time Management","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Automated Productivity System","prompt":"\\"Build an automated personal productivity system that:\\n\\n1. Collects tasks from [email/Slack/calendar]\\n2. Prioritizes with Eisenhower + AI scoring\\n3. Schedules deep work blocks\\n4. Tracks time automatically\\n5. Generates weekly reports\\n6. Integrates with [calendar/task manager]\\n\\nCurrent stack: [your tools]\\nTechnical skills: [your level]\\n\\nProvide:\\n- System architecture\\n- Automation scripts\\n- Data flow diagram\\n- Customization options\\"","tags":["automation","python","javascript","api-integration","multi-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"An end-to-end personal productivity automation: task ingestion, AI scoring, deep-work scheduling, time tracking, weekly reports, and integrations.","inputs":[{"label":"email/Slack/calendar"},{"label":"calendar/task manager"},{"label":"your tools"},{"label":"your level"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","JavaScript","Python"],"est_time":"2–4 days","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Data flow**\\n```\\nEmail/Slack/Calendar → Webhooks → AI scorer (priority 1–5)\\n   → Todoist (auto-tagged)\\n   → Calendar (deep-work blocks auto-inserted Mon–Fri 09–11)\\n   → Time tracker (auto-start on focus)\\n   → Weekly report (Notion page, Sunday 18:00)\\n```\\n\\n**Scoring prompt (excerpt)**\\n> Score 1–5 on urgency, importance, and energy-fit. Output JSON: {score, reason, suggested_block}.\\n\\n**Tech:** Python + n8n + Anthropic API + Todoist + Google Calendar.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notion-ai"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Meetings & Communication","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Meeting Prep","prompt":"\\"I have a meeting about [topic] with [who].\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Create an agenda\\n2. Suggest 5 key questions\\n3. Draft a follow-up email template\\n4. Create an action items tracker\\"","tags":["meetings","preparation","templates","15-minutes"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"An agenda, five sharp questions, a follow-up email template, and an action-items tracker — all in 5 minutes.","inputs":[{"label":"topic"},{"label":"who"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Agenda (30 min)**\\n1. Context recap (3 min)\\n2. Decisions needed (10 min) — list 2 here\\n3. Open risks (8 min)\\n4. Next steps + owners (5 min)\\n5. Parking lot (4 min)\\n\\n**Questions to ask**\\n1. What\'s the success criterion for this in 30 days?\\n2. What\'s the blocker we\'re not naming?\\n3. Who\'s the single accountable owner?\\n4. What signal will tell us to course-correct?\\n5. What\'s the one thing we\'re optimising for?\\n\\n**Follow-up template:** Decisions / Owners / Risks / Next sync — one line each.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notion-ai"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Meetings & Communication","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Meeting Effectiveness","prompt":"\\"I attend [X] meetings/week and feel they\'re unproductive.\\n\\nPlease help me create:\\n1. Meeting criteria checklist\\n2. Agenda templates by type\\n3. Note-taking framework\\n4. Decision log template\\n5. Follow-up automation\\n\\nFocus on reducing time while improving outcomes.\\"","tags":["meetings","efficiency","templates","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A meeting-quality checklist, agenda templates by type, a note-taking framework, a decision log, and a follow-up automation plan.","inputs":[{"label":"X"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Quality checklist (run before sending the invite)**\\n- [ ] Is there a single decision or output? If not, don\'t schedule.\\n- [ ] Is the right person in the room? Limit to ≤6.\\n- [ ] Pre-read attached and read by attendees?\\n\\n**Agenda types**\\n- Decision (30 min) — context, options, decide, owner\\n- Working session (60 min) — goal, work, check-out\\n- Status (15 min) — async-first; meet only if blocked\\n\\n**Decision log columns:** Date · Decision · Owner · Rationale · Reversal cost.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notion-ai"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Meetings & Communication","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Meeting Intelligence System","prompt":"\\"Build a meeting intelligence system that:\\n\\n1. Transcribes from [Zoom/Teams/Meet]\\n2. Extracts action items automatically\\n3. Identifies decisions\\n4. Tracks topic trends\\n5. Suggests follow-up agendas\\n6. Integrates with [project tool]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Privacy-compliant\\n- Multi-language\\n- Speaker identification\\n- Export formats\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Architecture with local Whisper + LLM\\n- Processing pipeline code\\n- UI mockups\\n- Deployment instructions\\"","tags":["ai","transcription","automation","privacy","multi-week"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A privacy-friendly transcription + extraction system: local Whisper for ASR, LLM for action items / decisions, topic trending, follow-up agenda suggestions, UI mocks.","inputs":[{"label":"Zoom/Teams/Meet"},{"label":"project tool"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Pipeline**\\n```\\nZoom recording → Local Whisper (large-v3) → Diarised transcript\\n   → LLM extractor → JSON {decisions, actions, owners, due}\\n   → Topic tracker (vector DB) → Trend dashboard\\n   → Project tool sync (Linear / Jira)\\n```\\n\\n**Sample extraction**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\"actions\\": [\\n    {\\"text\\": \\"Send pricing memo to Alex\\", \\"owner\\": \\"Sam\\", \\"due\\": \\"2026-05-22\\"},\\n    {\\"text\\": \\"Spike on auth migration\\", \\"owner\\": \\"Priya\\", \\"due\\": \\"2026-05-29\\"}\\n  ],\\n  \\"decisions\\": [\\"Ship dark mode behind a flag in 1.4.0\\"]\\n}\\n```","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notion-ai"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Learning & Development","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"30-Day Learning Plan","prompt":"\\"I want to learn [skill]. I\'m a beginner with [X hours]/week.\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. A 30-day learning plan\\n2. Free/cheap resources\\n3. Simple practice projects\\n4. Progress tracking template\\n5. Milestones to celebrate\\"","tags":["learning","career-development","beginner","self-paced"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A 30-day learning plan, free/cheap resources, beginner-level practice projects, a progress tracker, and milestone moments.","inputs":[{"label":"skill"},{"label":"X hours"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"Self-paced","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Week 1 — Foundations**\\n- 4 × 1-hr lessons (e.g., Andrew Ng intro)\\n- Read 3 short essays, write reactions\\n- Mini project: rebuild a basic example end-to-end\\n\\n**Week 2 — Apply**\\n- Pick a small dataset / problem from your own work\\n- Ship a v0 by Friday\\n\\n**Week 3 — Stretch**\\n- Find a community (Discord/forum) and post one question\\n- Read 1 deeper paper or book chapter\\n\\n**Week 4 — Consolidate**\\n- Write a 600-word \\"what I learned\\" note\\n- Share it; ask for one critique\\n\\n**Milestones:** day 7 (first ship), day 14 (community), day 30 (public artefact).","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notion-ai"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Learning & Development","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Career Development Plan","prompt":"\\"I need to build expertise in [AI/data/leadership] for career progression.\\n\\nCurrent level: [describe]\\nTarget role: [describe]\\nTimeframe: [X months]\\nBudget: [X hours/week, $X]\\n\\nPlease design:\\n1. Competency map\\n2. Learning path with milestones\\n3. Project-based practice\\n4. Accountability system\\n5. Portfolio strategy\\n6. Network building plan\\n\\nOutput as a career development plan.\\"","tags":["career","upskilling","planning","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A competency map, a milestone learning path, project-based practice, an accountability system, a portfolio strategy, and a networking plan.","inputs":[{"label":"AI/data/leadership"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"X months"},{"label":"X hours/week, $X"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Competency map** (target: Senior PM, 12 months)\\n| Skill | Now | Target | Gap |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| Product strategy | 3/5 | 4/5 | course + 1 case study |\\n| Stakeholder mgmt | 4/5 | 4/5 | maintain |\\n| Analytical depth | 2/5 | 4/5 | SQL + analytics cert |\\n| Influence at exec level | 2/5 | 4/5 | mentor + practice |\\n\\n**Quarter 1 plan:** SQL course, 2 user-research interviews/wk, weekly 1:1 with skip-level.\\n\\n**Portfolio:** ship 3 case studies (problem, decision, outcome) by month 9.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notion-ai"]},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"UI/UX Design","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Page Layout Help","prompt":"\\"I need to design a [dashboard/form/page] for [purpose].\\n\\nUsers: [who]\\nKey actions: [list]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Suggest a layout\\n2. Recommend color scheme\\n3. List essential elements\\n4. Point out common mistakes\\n5. Suggest tools (free/low-cost)\\"","tags":["ui-design","layout","beginner","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A suggested layout, a colour scheme, an essentials list, the most common mistakes to avoid, and free tool picks.","inputs":[{"label":"dashboard/form/page"},{"label":"purpose"},{"label":"who"},{"label":"list"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Layout (dashboard, desktop-first)**\\n- Top: page title + global filter row (1 row)\\n- Left rail: nav (collapsible)\\n- Main: 3-col KPI strip → 2-col chart block → table → footer\\n\\n**Colour scheme**\\n- Bg: near-black (#0E1120)\\n- Surface: dark blue-grey (#161A2C)\\n- Primary action: violet (#9F8CFF)\\n- Positive / negative / neutral: cyan / rose / parchment\\n\\n**Common mistakes:** too many colours, busy charts, no whitespace, low contrast on labels.\\n\\n**Tools (free):** Figma, Penpot, Excalidraw.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["midjourney","dall-e-3","runway"]},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"UI/UX Design","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Full App Design","prompt":"\\"Design a [web app/dashboard/mobile app] for [use case].\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- User types: [list]\\n- Key features: [list]\\n- Must integrate with: [systems]\\n- Brand guidelines: [describe]\\n\\nPlease provide:\\n1. User flow diagrams\\n2. Wireframe descriptions\\n3. Component specs\\n4. Responsive considerations\\n5. Accessibility requirements\\n6. Design system recommendations\\n\\nOutput as structured documentation.\\"","tags":["ux-design","wireframes","design-system","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"User flows, wireframe descriptions, component specs, responsive considerations, a11y requirements, and a design-system recommendation.","inputs":[{"label":"web app/dashboard/mobile app"},{"label":"use case"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"systems"},{"label":"describe"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Primary flow (new user)**\\n1. Sign up → email verify → onboarding tour (skippable)\\n2. Empty state → choose first task → wins (badge, confetti)\\n3. Day-2 nudge → return + retain\\n\\n**Wireframes (described)**\\n- Home: top hero, three-card empty-state, primary CTA\\n- Detail: left meta column, main content, right rail with related items\\n- Settings: 3-tab layout, sticky save bar\\n\\n**Responsive:** breakpoints 640 / 768 / 1024 / 1280; mobile uses bottom-nav, desktop uses side rail.\\n\\n**A11y:** WCAG 2.1 AA contrast, focus rings on all interactive elements, keyboard-first nav, prefers-reduced-motion respected.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["midjourney","dall-e-3","runway"]},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"UI/UX Design","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Design System Build","prompt":"\\"Build a design system and component library for [product].\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Figma/Sketch components\\n- Design tokens (colors, typography, spacing)\\n- WCAG 2.1 AA compliance\\n- Dark/light mode\\n- Multi-language\\n- Mobile-first\\n\\nTechnical:\\n- React/Vue/Angular components\\n- Storybook documentation\\n- Automated testing\\n- Version control\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Component architecture\\n- Token structure\\n- Code examples\\n- Documentation template\\n- Governance process\\"","tags":["design-system","components","accessibility","multi-week","production"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A component architecture, token structure, code examples, documentation template, and governance process — across Figma + React + Storybook.","inputs":[{"label":"product"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Figma","JavaScript"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Token tree**\\n```\\ncolor/\\n  bg/{abyss, steel, hairline}\\n  fg/{1, 2, 3, on-violet}\\n  accent/{violet, cyan-ice}\\n  diff/{beginner, intermediate, advanced, expert}\\ntype/{display, h1, h2, body, eyebrow, mono}\\nspace/{1..24}    // 4px grid\\nradius/{none, sm, md, lg, pill}\\nshadow/{1, 2, 3, glow, glow-strong}\\nmotion/{ease-out, dur-fast, dur-base, dur-slow}\\n```\\n\\n**Governance:** all changes via PR, two reviewers (1 design + 1 eng), Storybook snapshots + visual diff CI.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["midjourney","dall-e-3","runway"]},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Data Visualization","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Chart Selection Help","prompt":"\\"I need to create charts for [report/presentation]. Data is about [topic].\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Choose the right chart types\\n2. Describe how to make them clear\\n3. Suggest color scheme\\n4. List labels/annotations to add\\n5. Recommend tools (Excel/Google Sheets/etc.)\\"","tags":["data-viz","charts","beginner","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"Chart-type picks per metric, clarity tips, a colour scheme, the labels/annotations you need, and tool suggestions.","inputs":[{"label":"report/presentation"},{"label":"topic"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Excel","Google Sheets"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Picks**\\n- Trend over time → line (use bands for variability)\\n- Composition → stacked bar (small categories) or treemap (≥8)\\n- Ranking → horizontal bar, longest at top\\n- Distribution → histogram or box plot\\n- Correlation → scatter, with regression line if signal is strong\\n\\n**Clarity:** start y-axis at 0 for bar charts (not always for line); label the most important point on the line, not all of them; lose the gridlines you don\'t read.\\n\\n**Colour:** one neutral + one accent. No rainbow palettes for ordinal data.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["midjourney","dall-e-3","runway"]},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Data Visualization","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Dashboard Design","prompt":"\\"Design a dashboard for [department] tracking [KPIs].\\n\\nKPIs: [list]\\nUpdate frequency: [real-time/daily/weekly]\\nUsers: [roles]\\nDevice: [desktop/tablet/mobile]\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. Dashboard layout with sections\\n2. Chart type recommendations\\n3. Interaction design (filters, drill-down)\\n4. Alert/notification design\\n5. Mobile adaptation strategy\\n\\nOutput as wireframe descriptions + specs.\\"","tags":["dashboard","data-viz","kpi","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A sectioned layout, chart-type picks per KPI, interaction design (filters, drill-down), an alert/notification scheme, and a mobile adaptation plan.","inputs":[{"label":"department"},{"label":"KPIs"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"real-time/daily/weekly"},{"label":"roles"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Sections (top → bottom)**\\n1. KPI strip (4 numbers, target vs. actual)\\n2. Trend grid (4 line charts, shared x-axis)\\n3. Breakdown (1 large + 2 small)\\n4. Anomaly table (sortable, default by severity)\\n\\n**Interactions**\\n- Global filters: date range, region, segment\\n- Click a KPI tile → drill into its detail page\\n- Right-click any value → \\"explain this number\\" (LLM)\\n\\n**Mobile:** collapse to single column, hide breakdown by default behind an accordion, keep KPI strip + one trend.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["midjourney","dall-e-3","runway"]},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Data Visualization","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Real-Time Analytics Dashboard","prompt":"\\"Build a real-time analytics dashboard using [React/Vue] + [D3/Chart.js].\\n\\nData sources:\\n- [API]\\n- [Database]\\n- [IoT sensors]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Sub-second updates\\n- Handle [X] concurrent users\\n- Custom visualizations\\n- Export capabilities\\n- Role-based access\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Frontend architecture\\n- Data pipeline design\\n- State management\\n- Performance optimization\\n- Testing strategy\\"","tags":["dashboard","real-time","frontend","multi-week","production"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A frontend architecture, data pipeline design, state management, performance optimisations, and a testing strategy.","inputs":[{"label":"React/Vue"},{"label":"D3/Chart.js"},{"label":"API"},{"label":"Database"},{"label":"IoT sensors"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","D3","JavaScript"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Frontend**\\n- React + TanStack Query for data\\n- D3 for custom charts, Tremor for stock components\\n- State: Zustand for UI, React Query for server-state\\n\\n**Data path**\\n```\\nKafka → Pinot (OLAP) → REST/WS → React\\n                       ↳ SSE for live KPIs\\n```\\n\\n**Perf**\\n- Virtualise tables >200 rows\\n- Web workers for any chart computing >5ms\\n- LRU on dimension queries (TTL 30s)\\n\\n**Testing:** Playwright e2e for critical flows, Storybook visual regression, k6 load test (500 RPS sustained).","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["midjourney","dall-e-3","runway"]},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Content & Branding","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Social Media Post","prompt":"\\"I need to create [X] social media posts about [topic].\\n\\nPlatform: [LinkedIn/Twitter/Instagram]\\nTone: [professional/casual/funny]\\nAudience: [describe]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Draft [X] posts\\n2. Suggest hashtags\\n3. Recommend images/graphics\\n4. Create a posting schedule\\"","tags":["content","social-media","marketing","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"Ten platform-tailored draft posts, suggested hashtags, image direction, and a posting schedule.","inputs":[{"label":"X"},{"label":"topic"},{"label":"LinkedIn/Twitter/Instagram"},{"label":"professional/casual/funny"},{"label":"describe"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**LinkedIn — Post 1 (educational)**\\n> Three things I\'ve stopped doing as a [role] this year:\\n> 1. Sitting in status meetings without an agenda\\n> 2. Answering \\"quick questions\\" in DM\\n> 3. Volunteering for work I don\'t own\\n> What did you stop doing? ↓\\n\\n**LinkedIn — Post 2 (POV)** [...]\\n\\n**Hashtags:** #ProductManagement #FoundersJourney (max 3–5, never on the first line)\\n\\n**Schedule:** Tue 09:00 educational, Thu 12:00 POV, Sat 10:00 story. Repurpose to Twitter same day, IG carousel on weekends.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["midjourney","dall-e-3","runway"]},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Content & Branding","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Content Strategy","prompt":"\\"I need a content strategy for [company/product] targeting [audience].\\n\\nCurrent state:\\n- Platforms: [list]\\n- Posting frequency: [describe]\\n- Engagement: [metrics]\\n\\nGoals:\\n- [Brand awareness/leads/community/etc.]\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. Content pillars/themes\\n2. Editorial calendar template\\n3. Content mix (educational/promotional/engaging)\\n4. Repurposing strategy\\n5. Success metrics\\n\\nOutput as a strategy document.\\"","tags":["content-strategy","marketing","editorial","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"Content pillars, an editorial calendar template, a content-mix recipe, a repurposing plan, and success metrics.","inputs":[{"label":"company/product"},{"label":"audience"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"metrics"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Pillars (3)**\\n1. Craft — how we build (40%)\\n2. Behind the scenes — the boring middle (35%)\\n3. POV — opinionated takes that age well (25%)\\n\\n**Mix per week**\\n- 2 LinkedIn long-form\\n- 3 Twitter threads\\n- 1 newsletter\\n- 1 short video (TikTok / Reels)\\n\\n**Repurposing:** newsletter → LI thread → Twitter excerpt → reel script. One artefact, four formats.\\n\\n**Metrics:** save rate (not likes), newsletter conversion, comment-to-DM ratio.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["midjourney","dall-e-3","runway"]},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Content & Branding","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"AI Content Engine","prompt":"\\"Build an AI-powered content generation system for [company].\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Generate blog posts, social posts, emails\\n- Maintain brand voice consistency\\n- SEO optimization\\n- Multi-language support\\n- A/B testing headlines\\n- Content calendar automation\\n\\nIntegration:\\n- CMS: [WordPress/Webflow/etc.]\\n- Analytics: [Google Analytics/etc.]\\n- Social schedulers: [Buffer/Hootsuite/etc.]\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Content generation pipeline\\n- Brand voice training approach\\n- Quality control process\\n- Automation workflows\\n- Performance tracking\\"","tags":["ai-content","marketing-automation","seo","multi-week","production"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A generation pipeline, brand-voice tuning approach, quality control, automation workflows, and a performance tracking system.","inputs":[{"label":"company"},{"label":"WordPress/Webflow/etc."},{"label":"Google Analytics/etc."},{"label":"Buffer/Hootsuite/etc."}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Pipeline**\\n```\\nTopic queue → Outline LLM → Section drafts (parallel)\\n   → Brand-voice critic (LLM with rubric)\\n   → SEO optimiser (keyword density, headings)\\n   → Human review (5-min sanity check)\\n   → CMS publish → Schedule social\\n```\\n\\n**Voice tuning:** 30 best-of corpus samples in an Anthropic file; system prompt anchors tone, banned words, sentence rhythm.\\n\\n**A/B headlines:** generate 5 variants per post; rotate top-2 in social; declare winner after 72 hrs.\\n\\n**Tracking:** scroll depth, time-on-page, conversion to newsletter, share rate.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["midjourney","dall-e-3","runway"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Automation & Scripting","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Repetitive Task Elimination","prompt":"\\"I do repetitive [data entry/reporting/formatting] using [Excel/manual work].\\n\\nTask: [describe step by step]\\nTime: [X hours/week]\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Identify if this can be automated\\n2. Suggest the easiest approach\\n3. Provide step-by-step instructions\\n4. Write simple formulas/scripts\\n5. Teach me how to maintain it\\"","tags":["automation","excel","beginner","quick-win","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A yes/no on whether it\'s automatable, the easiest path, step-by-step instructions, formulas/scripts, and a maintenance guide.","inputs":[{"label":"data entry/reporting/formatting"},{"label":"Excel/manual work"},{"label":"describe step by step"},{"label":"X hours/week"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Excel"],"est_time":"30 min","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Verdict:** automatable in under 30 minutes.\\n\\n**Simplest path:** Excel formulas + Power Query — no macros, no Python.\\n\\n**Steps**\\n1. Save your source files in one folder, e.g. `~/Reports`.\\n2. Open Excel → Data → Get Data → From Folder → point to that folder.\\n3. Power Query stitches them. Click \\"Combine & Transform\\".\\n4. Sheet auto-refreshes when files are added.\\n\\n**Formula to replace your VLOOKUP chain:**\\n```\\n=XLOOKUP(A2, LookupTable[Key], LookupTable[Value], \\"—\\", 0)\\n```\\n\\n**Maintenance:** check column names monthly; if a source file renames a column, Power Query will flag it.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["cursor","github-copilot","claude-code"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Automation & Scripting","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Python Automation","prompt":"\\"I want to automate [process] using Python.\\n\\nCurrent process:\\n1. [Step 1]\\n2. [Step 2]\\n3. [Step 3]\\n\\nInputs: [file types, locations]\\nOutputs: [what you need]\\nFrequency: [daily/weekly/monthly]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Run on [Windows/Mac/Server]\\n- Error handling\\n- Notifications\\n- Logging\\n- Easy to modify\\n\\nPlease provide:\\n1. Python script with comments\\n2. Setup instructions\\n3. Error handling\\n4. Scheduling (cron/Task Scheduler)\\n5. Documentation template\\"","tags":["python","automation","scripting","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A commented Python script, setup instructions, error handling, scheduling guidance, and a documentation template.","inputs":[{"label":"process"},{"label":"Step 1"},{"label":"Step 2"},{"label":"Step 3"},{"label":"file types, locations"}],"tools":["Claude","Python"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Script skeleton**\\n```python\\nimport logging, schedule, time\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\n\\nlog = logging.getLogger(\\"autoreport\\")\\n\\ndef run() -> None:\\n    try:\\n        df = ingest(Path(\\"~/inputs\\").expanduser())\\n        cleaned = clean(df)\\n        save(cleaned, Path(\\"~/out\\") / \\"report.xlsx\\")\\n        notify(\\"OK\\")\\n    except Exception:\\n        log.exception(\\"run failed\\")\\n        notify(\\"FAIL\\")\\n\\nschedule.every().day.at(\\"06:00\\").do(run)\\nwhile True: schedule.run_pending(); time.sleep(60)\\n```\\n\\n**Setup:** `pipx install pdm`; `pdm add pandas openpyxl schedule`; cron entry on Mac/Linux or Task Scheduler on Windows.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["cursor","github-copilot","claude-code"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Automation & Scripting","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Automation Platform","prompt":"\\"Build a production-grade automation platform for [department].\\n\\nUse cases:\\n- [List 3-5]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Microservices architecture\\n- Event-driven processing\\n- Error handling + retry\\n- Monitoring and alerting\\n- Audit trail\\n- Scalable to [X] jobs/day\\n\\nTech preferences:\\n- Language: [Python/Node/Go]\\n- Infrastructure: [AWS/Azure/on-prem]\\n- Orchestration: [Airflow/Prefect/custom]\\n\\nProvide:\\n- System architecture\\n- Core service code\\n- Database schema\\n- Deployment pipeline\\n- Monitoring setup\\n- Disaster recovery\\"","tags":["platform","microservices","devops","multi-week","production"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A microservices architecture, core service skeleton, DB schema, deployment pipeline, monitoring setup, and DR plan.","inputs":[{"label":"department"},{"label":"List 3-5"},{"label":"X"},{"label":"Python/Node/Go"},{"label":"AWS/Azure/on-prem"}],"tools":["Airflow","ChatGPT","Claude","Python"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Architecture**\\n```\\nEvent bus (NATS) ↔ Orchestrator (Prefect)\\n                   ↔ Workers (FastAPI, autoscaled)\\n                   ↔ Postgres (state) · S3 (artefacts) · Redis (cache)\\n                   ↔ Observability (OTel → Grafana)\\n```\\n\\n**Job table**\\n```sql\\ncreate table jobs (\\n  id uuid primary key,\\n  kind text not null,\\n  payload jsonb,\\n  status text check (status in (\'queued\',\'running\',\'done\',\'failed\')),\\n  attempts int default 0,\\n  created_at timestamptz default now()\\n);\\n```\\n\\n**DR:** RPO 15 min (WAL streaming), RTO 30 min (warm standby), monthly restore drills.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["cursor","github-copilot","claude-code"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Data Engineering","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Data Cleaning","prompt":"\\"I have [Excel/CSV] data that I need to clean and analyze.\\n\\nData description: [columns, size]\\nProblems: [duplicates, missing values, format issues]\\nGoal: [analysis/report]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Write Python/Pandas code to clean it\\n2. Show me how to explore the data\\n3. Create basic visualizations\\n4. Export clean data\\"","tags":["data-engineering","python","pandas","beginner","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"Pandas code to clean the data, exploration snippets, simple visualisations, and a clean export.","inputs":[{"label":"Excel/CSV"},{"label":"columns, size"},{"label":"duplicates, missing values, format issues"},{"label":"analysis/report"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Excel","Python"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Clean**\\n```python\\nimport pandas as pd\\ndf = pd.read_csv(\\"raw.csv\\")\\n\\ndf = (\\n    df.drop_duplicates()\\n      .assign(date=lambda d: pd.to_datetime(d[\\"date\\"], errors=\\"coerce\\"))\\n      .dropna(subset=[\\"date\\", \\"amount\\"])\\n      .query(\\"amount.abs() < 1e7\\")  # outliers\\n)\\n\\ndf[\\"amount\\"] = df[\\"amount\\"].astype(float).round(2)\\ndf.to_csv(\\"clean.csv\\", index=False)\\n```\\n\\n**Explore**\\n```python\\ndf.describe(); df.isna().sum(); df.groupby(\\"region\\")[\\"amount\\"].sum().plot.bar()\\n```","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["cursor","github-copilot","claude-code"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Data Engineering","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Data Pipeline","prompt":"\\"Design a data pipeline for [use case].\\n\\nSources:\\n- [ERP/SAP/Salesforce]\\n- [CRM data]\\n- [External data]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Daily refresh\\n- Historical tracking\\n- Data quality checks\\n- Access for [X] users\\n- Budget: [range]\\n\\nPlease provide:\\n1. Pipeline architecture\\n2. ETL/ELT approach\\n3. Data model design\\n4. Quality checks\\n5. Documentation standards\\n6. Tool recommendations\\"","tags":["data-pipeline","etl","data-modeling","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A pipeline architecture, ETL/ELT approach, data model, quality checks, documentation standards, and tool picks.","inputs":[{"label":"use case"},{"label":"ERP/SAP/Salesforce"},{"label":"CRM data"},{"label":"External data"},{"label":"X"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Architecture (ELT)**\\n```\\nSources (SAP, Salesforce, files)\\n  → Fivetran / Airbyte (ingest)\\n  → Snowflake raw schema\\n  → dbt models (staging → marts)\\n  → Great Expectations (tests)\\n  → BI (Power BI / Looker)\\n```\\n\\n**Marts**\\n- `mart_finance.fct_invoice` — grain = invoice line\\n- `mart_finance.dim_customer` — SCD type 2\\n\\n**Quality (per run)**\\n- Row count vs. prior run (alert if >5% drift)\\n- Null %, distinct count\\n- Joinable to dim tables = 100%","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["cursor","github-copilot","claude-code"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Data Engineering","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Modern Data Platform","prompt":"\\"Build a modern data platform.\\n\\nScale:\\n- [X] TB data\\n- [X] sources\\n- [X] users\\n- [X] queries/day\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Real-time and batch processing\\n- Data catalog\\n- Lineage tracking\\n- Quality monitoring\\n- Cost optimization\\n- GDPR compliance\\n- Self-service analytics\\n\\nTech preferences: [open to suggestions]\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Platform architecture\\n- Component selection\\n- Implementation phases\\n- Team structure\\n- Cost estimates\\n- Migration strategy\\"","tags":["data-platform","architecture","multi-week","enterprise"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A platform architecture, tool selection, phased rollout, team structure, cost estimate, and migration strategy.","inputs":[{"label":"X"},{"label":"open to suggestions"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Architecture**\\n```\\nIngest: Fivetran + Kafka\\nStore: Snowflake (warehouse) + Iceberg (lake)\\nTransform: dbt\\nCatalog: DataHub\\nQuality: Great Expectations\\nReverse-ETL: Hightouch\\nBI: Looker (semantic) + Power BI (long tail)\\n```\\n\\n**Team (yr 1):** 1 lead, 2 analytics engineers, 1 data eng, 1 platform eng, 0.5 PM.\\n\\n**Cost (annual run-rate):** $480k software, $1.1M people = $1.6M.\\n\\n**Migration:** strangler-fig; new pipelines on platform from day 1, legacy decommission over 18 mo.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["cursor","github-copilot","claude-code"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"AI/ML Applications","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"AI Feasibility Check","prompt":"\\"I want to use AI to help with [specific task].\\n\\nWhat I have:\\n- [Data description]\\n- [Problem description]\\n- [Current process]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Explain if AI is appropriate\\n2. Suggest the simplest approach\\n3. List what data I need\\n4. Recommend tools (no-code/low-code)\\n5. Estimate effort and accuracy\\"","tags":["ai","feasibility","beginner","consulting","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"An honest take on whether AI fits, the simplest approach, data requirements, no-code/low-code tools, and an effort/accuracy estimate.","inputs":[{"label":"specific task"},{"label":"Data description"},{"label":"Problem description"},{"label":"Current process"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Fit check:** YES — but use rules + LLM, not ML from scratch. Your data shape (text + categories) is ideal for LLM classification with few-shot examples.\\n\\n**Simplest path**\\n1. 20–50 hand-labelled examples\\n2. Prompt with examples + output schema\\n3. Run in batch (Make.com / Zapier scheduled)\\n\\n**Effort:** ~2 hours setup, ~$5–20/month in LLM cost.\\n\\n**Expected accuracy:** 88–94% on the obvious cases; design a fallback for the 6–12% it gets wrong.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["cursor","github-copilot","claude-code"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"AI/ML Applications","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"ML Model Build","prompt":"\\"Build an ML model for [demand forecasting/churn/etc.].\\n\\nData:\\n- Historical data: [time range, granularity]\\n- Features: [list]\\n- Target: [what to predict]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Retrain monthly\\n- Explain predictions\\n- Confidence intervals\\n- Deploy to [environment]\\n- Monitor drift\\n\\nPlease provide:\\n1. Data preparation pipeline\\n2. Model selection and training\\n3. Evaluation framework\\n4. Deployment approach\\n5. Monitoring setup\\n6. Business metrics\\"","tags":["machine-learning","modeling","deployment","half-day-to-week"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A data prep pipeline, model selection + training, evaluation framework, deployment approach, monitoring setup, and business metrics.","inputs":[{"label":"demand forecasting/churn/etc."},{"label":"time range, granularity"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"what to predict"},{"label":"environment"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day – 1 week","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Pipeline**\\n```\\nRaw → feature store (Feast)\\n   → training (XGBoost + LightGBM ensemble)\\n   → eval (MAPE, prediction interval coverage)\\n   → registry (MLflow)\\n   → serving (FastAPI / Triton)\\n   → monitoring (Evidently)\\n```\\n\\n**Eval (forecasting)**\\n- MAPE: target ≤8% at SKU-week grain\\n- 80% prediction interval coverage ≥75%\\n- Bias drift week-over-week ≤2pp\\n\\n**Business metrics:** stockout rate (↓ target 35%), overstock cost (↓ target $1.2M/yr).","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["cursor","github-copilot","claude-code"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"AI/ML Applications","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Enterprise ML Platform","prompt":"\\"Design an enterprise AI/ML platform.\\n\\nUse cases across departments:\\n- Demand forecasting\\n- Customer segmentation\\n- Predictive maintenance\\n- Quality control\\n- Pricing optimization\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- MLOps lifecycle\\n- Feature store\\n- Experiment tracking\\n- Model registry\\n- A/B testing\\n- Monitoring\\n- Governance\\n- Multi-cloud\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Platform architecture\\n- Component selection\\n- Implementation roadmap\\n- Team and skills needed\\n- Cost model\\n- Success metrics\\"","tags":["mlops","enterprise","platform","multi-month","production"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A multi-cloud MLOps platform: architecture, components, rollout roadmap, team plan, cost model, and metrics.","inputs":[],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-month","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Stack**\\n- Feature store: Feast\\n- Experiment tracking: Weights & Biases\\n- Registry + serving: MLflow + KServe\\n- Orchestration: Argo Workflows\\n- Monitoring: Evidently + Prometheus + Grafana\\n- Governance: model card per release, signed by data steward\\n\\n**Rollout (12 mo)**\\n- Q1: foundation (registry, serving, baseline monitoring)\\n- Q2: first two production models (forecasting, churn)\\n- Q3: feature store, A/B framework\\n- Q4: governance, audit, multi-cloud failover\\n\\n**TCO yr 1:** $1.8–2.4M.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["cursor","github-copilot","claude-code"]},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Market Research","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Quick Market Scan","prompt":"\\"I need a quick overview of [market/industry].\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. List top 5 players\\n2. Describe market size and growth\\n3. Identify key trends\\n4. Note any recent news/developments\\n5. Suggest 3 sources to read deeper\\"","tags":["market-research","overview","quick-scan","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"Top five players, market size + growth, key trends, recent news, and three deeper sources.","inputs":[{"label":"market/industry"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Top players** (mention only — sample shape, not real data)\\n1. Player A — incumbent, ~38% share, slow product velocity\\n2. Player B — pricing leader, growing in SMB\\n3. Player C — design-led challenger, last raised $80M\\n4. Player D — open-source play, strong dev community\\n5. Player E — vertical specialist (healthcare)\\n\\n**Market:** ~$8.4B, CAGR 14%, fragmenting toward verticals.\\n\\n**Trends:** consolidation in core, vertical land-grabs, AI-overlay pricing power.\\n\\n**Read deeper:** [Gartner MQ] · [a16z thesis] · [recent Stratechery piece].","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["perplexity","claude","elicit"]},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Market Research","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Deep Dive Report","prompt":"\\"I need a comprehensive market analysis of [industry] for [purpose].\\n\\nFocus areas:\\n- Market size and forecast\\n- Competitive landscape\\n- Customer segments\\n- Technology trends\\n- Regulatory environment\\n- Entry barriers\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. Executive summary\\n2. Market structure analysis\\n3. Competitor profiles (top 5)\\n4. Trend analysis\\n5. Opportunity assessment\\n6. Risk factors\\n7. Recommendations\\n\\nOutput as a professional report.\\"","tags":["market-research","report","strategy","half-day-to-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A full market analysis: exec summary, structure, top-5 competitor profiles, trends, opportunities, risks, and recommendations.","inputs":[{"label":"industry"},{"label":"purpose"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day – 1 day","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Executive summary**\\n- Market: $12.4B, growing 11% CAGR\\n- Top-3 control 54%; long tail of 200+ players\\n- The decisive shift is from horizontal SaaS to vertical AI; budget will follow the workflow, not the tool\\n\\n**Competitor profiles** (sample of one)\\n> **Player A** — Founded 2014, ~$320M ARR. Strengths: brand + channel. Weaknesses: legacy data model, slow on AI. Strategic moves: hired ex-Snowflake CRO, opened London office. Threat to us: medium — they\'re 18 months behind on AI but have the customer base.\\n\\n**Recommendation:** focus enterprise GTM on three verticals where AI maturity differential is widest.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["perplexity","claude","elicit"]},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Competitive Intelligence","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Competitor Profile","prompt":"\\"Create a detailed profile of [competitor company].\\n\\nInclude:\\n1. Company overview (size, history, ownership)\\n2. Product/service portfolio\\n3. Pricing strategy\\n4. Market position\\n5. Strengths and weaknesses\\n6. Recent strategic moves\\n7. Financial health (if public)\\n8. Threat level to us\\n\\nFormat as an intelligence brief.\\"","tags":["competitive-intel","profiling","strategy","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A complete intelligence brief: company overview, portfolio, pricing, position, strengths/weaknesses, recent moves, financials, and threat level.","inputs":[{"label":"competitor company"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"plan","sample_output":"**Overview** — Founded 2017. ~620 FTEs. PE-backed (Series D, last priced 2024). HQ Austin, eng team in Krakow.\\n\\n**Portfolio:** one flagship product, three adjacent SKUs (analytics, audit, compliance).\\n\\n**Pricing:** $99 / $249 / Enterprise (call). 14-day trial, no card.\\n\\n**Strengths:** integrations breadth, partner channel.\\n**Weaknesses:** product velocity (~6 releases/yr), thin data-science chops.\\n\\n**Recent moves:** acquired a 12-person ML team (Q2), launched a free tier (Q3).\\n\\n**Threat level:** HIGH on SMB segment, LOW on enterprise.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["perplexity","claude","elicit"]},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Competitive Intelligence","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Competitive Monitoring System","prompt":"\\"Build an automated competitive intelligence system that tracks:\\n\\n1. Competitor website changes\\n2. Pricing updates\\n3. New product launches\\n4. Job postings (hiring signals)\\n5. Patent filings\\n6. Social media sentiment\\n7. Review trends\\n\\nAlerts:\\n- Daily digest for minor changes\\n- Immediate alert for major changes\\n\\nDeliverables:\\n- Weekly competitive brief\\n- Monthly strategic assessment\\n- Quarterly trend report\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Data sources and APIs\\n- Scraping infrastructure\\n- Analysis pipeline\\n- Alert system\\n- Report templates\\"","tags":["competitive-intel","automation","monitoring","multi-week","production"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"An automated CI system spec: data sources, scraping infrastructure, analysis pipeline, alerts, and report templates.","inputs":[],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Sources**\\n- Website diff: weekly snapshot, HTML diff with semantic noise filter\\n- Pricing pages: daily check (specific selectors)\\n- Job boards: Greenhouse/Lever scrape + keyword classifier\\n- Patents: USPTO RSS by competitor name\\n- Reviews: G2 / Capterra weekly pull\\n\\n**Pipeline**\\n```\\nSource → Raw store (S3) → Classifier (LLM)\\n   → Significance scorer → Slack / Email\\n```\\n\\n**Alerts:** major change = pricing ±5%, exec hire, M&A rumour, raise announcement.\\n\\n**Weekly brief:** auto-generated Notion page Fri 09:00.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["perplexity","claude","elicit"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Documentation","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Process Documentation","prompt":"\\"I need to document how to [task/process].\\n\\nAudience: [new hires/team/customers]\\nCurrent knowledge: [tribal/exists in heads]\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Create a step-by-step guide\\n2. Add screenshots/checkpoints\\n3. Include troubleshooting section\\n4. Make it scannable (bullet points)\\n5. Suggest where to store it\\"","tags":["documentation","process","knowledge-management","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A step-by-step guide with checkpoints, a troubleshooting section, a scannable format, and a storage recommendation.","inputs":[{"label":"task/process"},{"label":"new hires/team/customers"},{"label":"tribal/exists in heads"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Doc structure**\\n1. Who this is for (1 line)\\n2. Prerequisites (3–5 bullets)\\n3. Steps (numbered, screenshot every 3rd)\\n4. Verification checklist\\n5. Troubleshooting (top 5 issues)\\n6. Glossary\\n7. Last updated + owner\\n\\n**Tone:** imperative, second person — \\"Open the file\\" not \\"The user opens the file\\".\\n\\n**Where to store:** if it\'s product → docs site (Mintlify); if it\'s internal → Notion (one page per process, linked from a process index).","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","jasper"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Documentation","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Technical Documentation","prompt":"\\"I need technical documentation for [system/feature].\\n\\nAudience: [developers/users/administrators]\\nCurrent state: [no docs/outdated/fragmented]\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. Overview and architecture\\n2. Setup/installation guide\\n3. API reference (if applicable)\\n4. Usage examples\\n5. Troubleshooting guide\\n6. FAQ\\n7. Changelog template\\n\\nFormat: [Markdown/Confluence/Notion]\\"","tags":["technical-writing","documentation","developer-experience","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A complete tech doc set: overview + architecture, setup, API reference, examples, troubleshooting, FAQ, and changelog template — Markdown-ready.","inputs":[{"label":"system/feature"},{"label":"developers/users/administrators"},{"label":"no docs/outdated/fragmented"},{"label":"Markdown/Confluence/Notion"}],"tools":["Claude","Notion"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Skeleton**\\n```\\ndocs/\\n  README.md          # overview + diagram\\n  install.md         # platforms, prerequisites\\n  api/\\n    endpoints.md     # generated from OpenAPI\\n    auth.md\\n  examples/\\n    quickstart.md\\n    advanced.md\\n  troubleshooting.md\\n  faq.md\\n  changelog.md\\n```\\n\\n**API reference (sample entry)**\\n```\\n### POST /v1/jobs\\nCreate a new job. Idempotent on `Idempotency-Key` header.\\n\\n**Body:** { kind: string, payload: object }\\n**Returns:** 201 + { id, status_url }\\n**Errors:** 400 (invalid kind), 409 (duplicate key)\\n```","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","jasper"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Documentation","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Documentation Platform","prompt":"\\"Design a documentation strategy and platform for [company/product].\\n\\nCurrent state:\\n- [Scattered/outdated/non-existent]\\n- Tools: [if any]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Version control\\n- Search functionality\\n- Multi-format output (web/PDF)\\n- Contribution workflow\\n- Review process\\n- Analytics (what\'s read, what\'s not)\\n- Integration with support tickets\\n\\nPlease provide:\\n- Information architecture\\n- Tool selection and setup\\n- Writing standards/style guide\\n- Maintenance process\\n- Migration plan (if needed)\\"","tags":["documentation","platform","knowledge-management","multi-week"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"An info architecture, tool selection + setup, writing standards, maintenance process, and migration plan.","inputs":[{"label":"company/product"},{"label":"Scattered/outdated/non-existent"},{"label":"if any"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**IA (3 trees)**\\n1. Get started (onboarding) — < 5 min reads\\n2. How-to (task-oriented) — recipe format\\n3. Reference (deep) — searchable, structured\\n\\n**Stack:** Mintlify / Docusaurus → GitHub → Vercel · Algolia search · Plausible analytics.\\n\\n**Standards**\\n- Active voice, second person\\n- Sentence case headings\\n- Every page: who-it\'s-for + outcome at top\\n- Code blocks always copy-pasteable, no shell prompts\\n\\n**Maintenance:** quarterly stale-page sweep; PR template enforces the standard.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","jasper"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Presentations","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Slide Content","prompt":"\\"I need to create a presentation about [topic] for [audience].\\n\\nDuration: [X minutes]\\nKey message: [one sentence]\\nData: [what you have]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Create an outline (title + 3-5 sections)\\n2. Write speaker notes\\n3. Suggest visuals/charts\\n4. Recommend slide count\\n5. Provide opening and closing statements\\"","tags":["presentation","slides","storytelling","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A title + 3–5 section outline, speaker notes, suggested visuals/charts, a recommended slide count, and opening + closing statements.","inputs":[{"label":"topic"},{"label":"audience"},{"label":"X minutes"},{"label":"one sentence"},{"label":"what you have"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Outline (15 min)**\\n- Title — \\"Why we should bet on X\\"\\n- Section 1 — The shift (3 slides, 4 min)\\n- Section 2 — Our position (2 slides, 3 min)\\n- Section 3 — The wedge (3 slides, 5 min)\\n- Section 4 — Ask (1 slide, 2 min)\\n- Q&A (1 min)\\n\\n**Open:** \\"I\'m asking for one decision today, and I\'ll get to it in 12 minutes.\\"\\n\\n**Close:** \\"If we approve this, here\'s what we\'re doing next week. If we don\'t, here\'s what we\'ll regret.\\"\\n\\n**Recommended:** 10 slides. Less is more.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","jasper"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Presentations","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Presentation Design","prompt":"\\"Design a compelling presentation for [purpose].\\n\\nContext:\\n- Audience: [describe]\\n- Stake in outcome: [what they care about]\\n- Time: [X minutes]\\n- Format: [in-person/remote]\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. Narrative arc (beginning, middle, end)\\n2. Slide-by-slide storyboard\\n3. Data visualization recommendations\\n4. Speaker notes with timing\\n5. Q&A preparation (anticipate 5 questions)\\n6. Handout design\\n\\nMake it persuasive, not just informative.\\"","tags":["presentation","design","storytelling","persuasion","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A narrative arc, storyboard, viz recommendations, timed speaker notes, anticipated Q&A, and a handout.","inputs":[{"label":"purpose"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"what they care about"},{"label":"X minutes"},{"label":"in-person/remote"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Arc**\\n1. Setup — the world they know\\n2. Disruption — what\'s changed\\n3. Resolution — what we do about it\\n4. Ask — the decision\\n\\n**Speaker notes (slide 4)**\\n> \\"Three numbers tell this story. The first is [X] — that\'s our baseline. The second is [Y] — that\'s the new reality. The third is [Z] — that\'s the gap we have to close.\\"\\n\\n**Anticipated Q1:** \\"Why now, not next year?\\" — A: 2-sentence answer + back-up slide ready.\\n\\n**Handout:** 2-pager, exec summary front, FAQ back.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","jasper"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Presentations","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Automated Presentation Generation","prompt":"\\"Build a system that generates presentations from [data source].\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Pull data from [database/API/spreadsheet]\\n- Auto-generate charts and visuals\\n- Apply brand template\\n- Create narrative from data insights\\n- Export to PowerPoint/Google Slides\\n- Schedule automatic updates\\n\\nUse cases:\\n- Monthly board reports\\n- Weekly sales updates\\n- Quarterly business reviews\\n\\nProvide:\\n- System architecture\\n- Template design system\\n- Data-to-slide mapping\\n- Automation pipeline\\n- Quality checks\\"","tags":["presentation","automation","data-to-slides","multi-week","production"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"An end-to-end data-to-deck system: architecture, template design, data-to-slide mapping, automation pipeline, and quality checks.","inputs":[{"label":"data source"},{"label":"database/API/spreadsheet"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Pipeline**\\n```\\nSources → SQL → DataFrame\\n   → Template engine (python-pptx + branded slide masters)\\n   → Narrative generator (LLM with structured prompt per slide)\\n   → QA pass (LLM critic + rule-based checks)\\n   → S3 + Slack delivery\\n```\\n\\n**Slide mapping**\\n| Slide | Data query | Layout |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| 1 — Headline | revenue_summary.sql | KPI tile |\\n| 2 — Trend | revenue_monthly.sql | line chart |\\n| 3 — Variance | budget_var.sql | table + comment |\\n\\n**QA:** every number must trace to a query hash; LLM critic checks for tone + cross-slide consistency.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","jasper"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Email & Communication","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Email Templates","prompt":"\\"I need email templates for [situation].\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. Initial outreach\\n2. Follow-up after no response\\n3. Meeting request\\n4. Thank you after meeting\\n5. Status update\\n\\nTone: [professional/friendly/urgent]\\nKeep them short and actionable.\\"","tags":["email","templates","communication","30-minutes"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"Five reusable templates — initial outreach, follow-up, meeting request, thank-you, status update — short and actionable.","inputs":[{"label":"situation"},{"label":"professional/friendly/urgent"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"30 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Initial outreach**\\n> Subject: [their company] × [your company] — quick idea\\n> Hi [name], saw [specific signal]. We help [people like them] do [specific outcome]. Worth a 15-min chat next week?\\n\\n**Follow-up (after no reply)**\\n> Subject: bumping this up\\n> Hi [name], jumping back here. If now\'s a bad week, just let me know and I\'ll try again in [month].\\n\\n**Meeting request**\\n> Subject: 20 min, [topic]?\\n> Goal: decide [X]. Tue 10am, Thu 2pm — what works?\\n\\n**Thank-you**\\n> Thanks for the time. Three things I owe you: [...]. Talk [date].\\n\\n**Status update**\\n> [Project] · [colour] · [1-line headline]. Wins: [...]. Risks: [...]. Asks: [...].","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","jasper"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Email & Communication","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Communication Strategy","prompt":"\\"I need to communicate [change/decision/update] to [audience].\\n\\nContext:\\n- What\'s changing: [describe]\\n- Why: [reason]\\n- Impact: [who\'s affected and how]\\n- Timeline: [when]\\n- Concerns: [what people will worry about]\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Craft the core message\\n2. Create an FAQ (10 questions)\\n3. Design a communication timeline\\n4. Write for different channels (email, meeting, doc)\\n5. Plan for feedback and resistance\\n6. Create a feedback loop\\"","tags":["communication","change-management","strategy","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A core message, a 10-question FAQ, a comms timeline, channel-specific drafts, a resistance plan, and a feedback loop design.","inputs":[{"label":"change/decision/update"},{"label":"audience"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"reason"},{"label":"who\'s affected and how"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Core message** (1 sentence)\\n> \\"We\'re moving [process] to [new tool] over the next 8 weeks so [outcome] — and we\'re keeping [thing they care about] exactly as it is.\\"\\n\\n**FAQ (sample 3 of 10)**\\n- Q: Why now? A: [specific reason + signal]\\n- Q: What changes for me? A: [day-1 impact, week-1 impact]\\n- Q: What if I disagree? A: [exact path + when]\\n\\n**Timeline**\\n- Week 0: leader pre-brief\\n- Week 1: all-hands announcement + FAQ doc\\n- Week 2: 1:1s for top concerns\\n- Week 4: midpoint pulse survey\\n- Week 8: retro\\n\\n**Feedback loop:** anonymous form + biweekly office hours; ship one visible change in response.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","jasper"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Explain Anything in Plain English","prompt":"Explain [concept or topic] to me as if I have no background in it. Use an analogy, give me the 3 key things I need to know, and tell me what I can ignore for now.","tags":["learning","explainer","beginner","quick"],"best_for":"Anyone who wants to understand something fast","outcome":"A jargon-free explanation with an analogy and the three things that actually matter.","inputs":[{"label":"concept or topic"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**The concept:** Kubernetes\\n\\n**Analogy:** Think of your apps like shipping containers. Kubernetes is the shipping port — it decides which ships (servers) carry which containers, automatically reroutes if a ship has problems, and scales up when demand surges.\\n\\n**3 things you need to know:**\\n1. It auto-heals: if your app crashes, Kubernetes restarts it\\n2. It scales: add more traffic, it adds more instances automatically\\n3. It abstracts infrastructure: you describe *what* you want, not *where* it runs\\n\\n**You can ignore for now:** etcd, control plane internals, CNI plugins — those are ops concerns unless you\'re running the cluster yourself.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Summarise Any Document or Article","prompt":"Summarise the following [document type] in 5 bullet points. Highlight the single most important takeaway, flag any risks or open questions, and note one action I could take today.\\n\\n[paste content]","tags":["summary","reading","quick","productivity"],"best_for":"Anyone who reads a lot and needs the key points fast","outcome":"5-bullet summary with the top insight, risks flagged, and one concrete action.","inputs":[{"label":"document type"},{"label":"paste content"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Summary: Q3 Investor Update**\\n\\n- Revenue hit $4.2M ARR (+18% QoQ) driven by enterprise expansion, not new logos\\n- Churn ticked up to 3.2% — two large accounts left citing \\"missing integrations\\"\\n- Hiring plan is 6 engineers by year-end; currently 2 offers outstanding\\n- Runway is 22 months at current burn; Series B target is Q1 next year\\n- Product roadmap: API v2 is the top priority for Q4\\n\\n**Most important takeaway:** Growth is healthy but churn signal on integrations needs immediate product response.\\n\\n**Risk:** If the two outstanding offers don\'t close, engineering plan slips and API v2 is at risk.\\n\\n**Action today:** Schedule a 30-min call with the two churned accounts to validate the integration gap before roadmap is locked.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Rewrite This More Clearly","prompt":"Rewrite the following text to be clearer and more direct. Remove jargon, shorten sentences, and keep the core meaning intact. Also give me one sentence explaining the main change you made.\\n\\n[paste text]","tags":["editing","clarity","writing","quick"],"best_for":"Anyone who wants to communicate more clearly","outcome":"A polished, plain-English rewrite plus a one-line explanation of the key edit.","inputs":[{"label":"paste text"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Original:** \\"In order to facilitate the optimisation of our cross-functional synergy initiatives, we will be leveraging a new paradigm of collaborative frameworks going forward.\\"\\n\\n**Rewritten:** \\"We\'re rolling out a new approach to help teams work together better.\\"\\n\\n**Main change:** Removed every piece of corporate jargon and cut from 27 words to 11 without losing meaning.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Draft a Quick Reply Email","prompt":"Write a brief email reply to the following message. Keep it under 80 words, be friendly but professional, answer the key question directly, and end with a clear next step.\\n\\n[paste the email you received]","tags":["email","communication","quick","writing"],"best_for":"Anyone with a full inbox who wants to reply faster","outcome":"A concise, professional reply under 80 words with a clear next step.","inputs":[{"label":"paste the email you received"}],"tools":["Claude","Gmail","Outlook"],"output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"Hi Sarah,\\n\\nThanks for reaching out — yes, we can move the Thursday call to 3 PM instead of 2 PM. Works perfectly.\\n\\nI\'ll send a revised invite now. Looking forward to walking through the Q4 plan with you.\\n\\nBest,\\nAlex","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Turn Meeting Notes into Action Items","prompt":"I have rough notes from a meeting. Extract all action items in a clean table with: Owner, Action, Deadline (if mentioned). Then write a 2-sentence meeting summary I can paste into Slack.\\n\\nNotes: [paste meeting notes]","tags":["meetings","productivity","notes","quick"],"best_for":"Anyone who takes meeting notes and needs to distribute them fast","outcome":"Structured action item table + a 2-sentence Slack-ready summary.","inputs":[{"label":"paste meeting notes"}],"tools":["Claude","Notion","Slack"],"output_kind":"table","sample_output":"**Action Items**\\n\\n| Owner | Action | Deadline |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| Priya | Send revised pricing deck to enterprise accounts | Friday EOD |\\n| Marcus | Book venue for Q4 kickoff | Next Wednesday |\\n| Team | Review updated OKRs before next sync | Thursday AM |\\n\\n**Slack summary:**\\nWe aligned on Q4 priorities — pricing update and venue booking are the two blockers. Full action list in Notion.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Generate a Pro/Con List","prompt":"I need to decide between [option A] and [option B] in the context of [your situation]. Give me a structured pro/con table for each, weight the most important factors, and give me your recommendation with a one-sentence rationale.","tags":["decision-making","planning","quick","analysis"],"best_for":"Anyone facing a decision who wants a structured view fast","outcome":"A weighted pro/con table for both options plus a clear recommendation.","inputs":[{"label":"option A"},{"label":"option B"},{"label":"your situation"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"output_kind":"table","sample_output":"**Option A: Hire a full-time designer**\\n\\n| Pro | Con |\\n|---|---|\\n| Deep brand consistency | 3-month ramp time |\\n| Embedded in team | $90k+ cost |\\n| Long-term asset | Risk if workload drops |\\n\\n**Option B: Use a design agency**\\n\\n| Pro | Con |\\n|---|---|\\n| Fast start (1–2 weeks) | Less brand ownership |\\n| Flexible scope | Higher per-hour cost |\\n| No hiring risk | Communication overhead |\\n\\n**Recommendation:** Start with the agency. Your product roadmap is still shifting — locking in a full-time hire before the design direction is settled is premature.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Create a Template from a One-Off Doc","prompt":"Turn the following one-off document into a reusable template. Replace specific names, dates, and numbers with clear [PLACEHOLDER] labels. Add a short instruction comment above each placeholder explaining what to fill in.\\n\\n[paste document]","tags":["templates","documentation","reuse","quick"],"best_for":"Anyone who writes the same type of document repeatedly","outcome":"A clean, labelled template with placeholder instructions ready to reuse.","inputs":[{"label":"paste document"}],"tools":["Claude","Notion","Google Docs"],"output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**PROJECT KICKOFF BRIEF**\\n\\n<!-- Project name: e.g. \\"Website Redesign Q1\\" -->\\n**Project:** [PROJECT NAME]\\n\\n<!-- One sentence describing the goal -->\\n**Objective:** [PROJECT OBJECTIVE]\\n\\n<!-- Format: Month DD, YYYY -->\\n**Launch date:** [TARGET LAUNCH DATE]\\n\\n<!-- List 2-4 people and their role -->\\n**Team:**\\n- [NAME] — [ROLE]\\n- [NAME] — [ROLE]\\n\\n<!-- What does success look like? List 2-3 measurable outcomes -->\\n**Success metrics:**\\n1. [METRIC 1]\\n2. [METRIC 2]","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Write a LinkedIn Post from a Rough Idea","prompt":"Turn this rough idea into a LinkedIn post: [your rough idea or bullet points]. Make it engaging but not cringe. Open with a hook, share one insight or story, end with a question or takeaway. Keep it under 200 words.","tags":["linkedin","social-media","writing","quick"],"best_for":"Professionals who want to build a presence but hate writing from scratch","outcome":"A 200-word LinkedIn post with a hook opening and clear takeaway.","inputs":[{"label":"your rough idea or bullet points"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"We almost launched the wrong product.\\n\\nThree months ago, we were convinced users wanted a dashboard. We built mockups, wrote specs, and had the engineers ready to start.\\n\\nThen we did 8 customer calls.\\n\\nNobody cared about the dashboard. They cared about one thing: getting their data out faster. The dashboard was just how they thought they\'d use it.\\n\\nWe killed the dashboard. Built a one-click export instead. Shipped in 2 weeks. NPS jumped 18 points.\\n\\nThe lesson: users describe solutions, not problems. Your job is to ask one layer deeper — *why* do you want that?\\n\\nWhat\'s the last assumption a customer call killed for you?","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Image Generation","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Write Your First Image Generation Prompt","prompt":"I want to create an image of [what you want to see]. Help me write a detailed Midjourney or DALL-E prompt that will produce a great result. Include: subject, style, lighting, mood, composition, and any negative prompts to avoid. Give me 3 variations at different style directions.","tags":["image-generation","midjourney","dalle","prompt-engineering"],"best_for":"Anyone new to AI image generation","outcome":"Three ready-to-use image prompts at different style directions, with negative prompts included.","inputs":[{"label":"what you want to see"}],"tools":["Midjourney","DALL-E 3","Stable Diffusion"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Variation 1 — Cinematic Photo**\\n`/imagine a lone lighthouse on rocky cliffs at golden hour, stormy ocean in background, dramatic god rays through clouds, shot on Hasselblad, f/2.8, cinematic color grade, 8k --ar 16:9 --v 6`\\n*Negative:* cartoonish, flat, oversaturated, text\\n\\n**Variation 2 — Oil Painting**\\n`/imagine lighthouse on sea cliffs, oil painting in the style of J.M.W. Turner, impressionistic brushwork, warm ochre and deep navy palette, museum quality, impasto texture --ar 4:3 --stylize 800`\\n*Negative:* photorealistic, digital, modern\\n\\n**Variation 3 — Minimal Illustration**\\n`/imagine minimalist vector illustration of lighthouse, flat design, 3-color palette of cream/navy/coral, geometric shapes, editorial style, negative space composition --ar 1:1 --style raw`\\n*Negative:* complex, detailed, photographic","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["midjourney","dall-e-3","runway"]},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Image Generation","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","title":"AI Product Photography Brief","prompt":"I\'m shooting [product name] using AI image generation. Create a detailed photography brief for 5 different shots: lifestyle, detail, comparison, hero, and social square. For each shot include the full AI prompt, lighting setup, background, mood, and intended platform use.","tags":["product-photography","e-commerce","midjourney","brand"],"best_for":"E-commerce brands, product marketers, studio directors","outcome":"5-shot AI photography brief with full prompts, lighting, and platform specs for each.","inputs":[{"label":"product name"}],"tools":["Midjourney","DALL-E 3","Adobe Firefly"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Shot 1 — Hero**\\nPrompt: `minimalist ceramic coffee mug, studio white background, single soft key light from upper left, long shadow, shot on Phase One, product photography, hyper-detail --ar 4:5`\\nPlatform: Homepage hero, email header\\n\\n**Shot 2 — Lifestyle**\\nPrompt: `ceramic mug on weathered oak desk, morning light through linen curtains, MacBook open, small succulent, warm lifestyle photography, film grain --ar 16:9`\\nPlatform: Instagram, blog\\n\\n**Shot 3 — Detail**\\nPrompt: `extreme close-up ceramic texture, matte glaze, micro detail, macro lens, soft bokeh background, neutral tones --ar 1:1`\\nPlatform: PDPs, Amazon\\n...","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["midjourney","dall-e-3","runway"]},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Image Generation","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","title":"Midjourney Style Guide for a Brand","prompt":"Create a Midjourney style guide for [brand name] with the following brand values: [list 3 values] and target audience: [describe audience]. Include: a core prompt suffix all images should use, 5 approved style references with example prompts, 3 things to always avoid, and a color palette description to include in prompts.","tags":["brand","midjourney","style-guide","visual-identity"],"best_for":"Brand designers, marketing teams, creative directors","outcome":"A reusable Midjourney style guide with core suffix, 5 style references, and brand-safe guardrails.","inputs":[{"label":"brand name"},{"label":"list 3 values"},{"label":"describe audience"}],"tools":["Midjourney","Notion"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Brand:** Forma Studio (minimal architecture firm)\\n\\n**Core suffix** (append to every prompt):\\n`--style raw --ar 16:9 --v 6.1 :: warm ivory and slate tones, natural light, architectural precision, editorial calm`\\n\\n**Approved styles:**\\n1. Exterior — `concrete and glass building, golden hour, aerial perspective, Zaha Hadid influence`\\n2. Interior — `open plan living space, floor-to-ceiling windows, linen furniture, minimal decor`\\n...\\n\\n**Always avoid:** busy patterns, bright saturated colors, people in foreground, text overlays, fantasy elements\\n\\n**Color palette to include:** ivory (#F7F4EE), slate (#4A5568), warm sand (#C9B99A)","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["midjourney","dall-e-3","runway"]},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Video & Motion","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","title":"AI Video Script and Shot List","prompt":"Write a 60-second video script and shot list for [video concept] targeting [target audience]. Format it as a production doc with: VO script column, visual description column, shot type, and AI video prompt for each scene (suitable for Runway, Pika, or Sora). Aim for 6-8 scenes.","tags":["video","runway","sora","scriptwriting","production"],"best_for":"Content creators, video producers, social media managers","outcome":"A 60-second production doc with VO script, shot descriptions, and AI video prompts for each scene.","inputs":[{"label":"video concept"},{"label":"target audience"}],"tools":["Runway","Pika","Sora","CapCut"],"output_kind":"deck","sample_output":"**VIDEO: \\"Morning Ritual\\" — Cold Brew Brand | 60 sec**\\n\\n| Scene | VO Script | Visual | Shot | AI Prompt |\\n|---|---|---|---|---|\\n| 1 (0–5s) | \\"Some mornings ask more of you.\\" | Alarm clock 5:47am, dark room | Close-up | `alarm clock glowing in dark bedroom, cinematic, slow motion, film grain, cool tones` |\\n| 2 (5–12s) | \\"So we made a cold brew that answers back.\\" | Hands wrapping around glass | Medium | `hands holding glass of cold brew coffee, morning light, condensation on glass, warm tones` |\\n...","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["midjourney","dall-e-3","runway"]},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Image Generation","skill_level":"ADVANCED","title":"Character Design Sheet with AI","prompt":"I\'m designing a character: [character description]. Create a complete AI art direction document for generating a consistent character across multiple images. Include: a canonical base prompt, 4 pose variants, 3 expression variants, lighting setup for hero vs. action shots, and a LoRA/style consistency note for Stable Diffusion.","tags":["character-design","stable-diffusion","concept-art","game-art"],"best_for":"Game designers, illustrators, concept artists, indie developers","outcome":"A full character art direction sheet with canonical prompt, pose/expression variants, and SD consistency notes.","inputs":[{"label":"character description"}],"tools":["Stable Diffusion","Midjourney","ComfyUI"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Character:** Lyra — young mage, silver hair, emerald eyes, worn leather coat, staff\\n\\n**Canonical base prompt:**\\n`lyra, 20s female mage, silver hair swept back, emerald eyes glowing faintly, worn brown leather duster, wooden staff with orb, fantasy, detailed illustration, artstation quality`\\n\\n**Pose variants:**\\n- Standing neutral: `standing pose, three-quarter view, neutral expression`\\n- Casting spell: `dynamic casting pose, hands raised, magical energy swirling`\\n\\n**SD consistency tip:** Train a LoRA on 15-20 approved outputs. Use `lyra_v1:0.8` in prompt weight to maintain face/costume consistency across scenes.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["midjourney","dall-e-3","runway"]},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Design Tools","skill_level":"ADVANCED","title":"Generate a Full UI Design System Prompt Library","prompt":"I\'m building a [product type] app with these design principles: [list 3 principles]. Create a prompt library for generating UI assets with AI image tools: icon set style prompt, illustration style prompt, hero image prompt, onboarding screen mood board prompt, and empty state illustration prompt. Each should be immediately usable in Midjourney or DALL-E.","tags":["ui-design","design-system","midjourney","product-design"],"best_for":"Product designers, UI/UX designers, design system leads","outcome":"5 reusable AI prompts covering icons, illustrations, heroes, onboarding, and empty states — all in a consistent visual language.","inputs":[{"label":"product type"},{"label":"list 3 principles"}],"tools":["Midjourney","DALL-E 3","Figma"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**App:** Wellness tracker | Principles: calm, human, minimal\\n\\n**Icon set:** `line icon set, wellness and health theme, 24px grid, 1.5px stroke, rounded caps, monochrome, clean minimal style, SVG-ready, white on dark --ar 1:1`\\n\\n**Illustration:** `gentle pastel illustration, person meditating in nature, flat design, soft gradients, breathing space, Headspace-adjacent style, no text --ar 4:3`\\n\\n**Hero image:** `serene landscape at dawn, soft golden light, person on hill, minimalist, editorial photography feel, lots of sky --ar 16:9`\\n\\n**Empty state:** `friendly abstract shape, no data yet, pastel tones, encouraging feeling, tiny character looking up, white background --ar 3:2`","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["midjourney","dall-e-3","runway"]},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Image Generation","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"AI Interior Design Concepts","prompt":"I want to redesign my [room type] in the style of [design style]. Generate 3 interior design concept prompts I can use in Midjourney or DALL-E. Include furniture, lighting, palette, and the specific mood for each concept. Make each concept distinctly different.","tags":["interior-design","home","midjourney","visualization"],"best_for":"Homeowners, renters, interior design enthusiasts","outcome":"Three distinct interior design concept prompts ready for AI image generation.","inputs":[{"label":"room type"},{"label":"design style"}],"tools":["Midjourney","DALL-E 3","Interior AI"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Concept 1 — Warm Japandi**\\n`living room interior, japandi style, warm oak furniture, cream boucle sofa, washi paper pendant light, low coffee table with single book and plant, tatami-inspired textures, golden hour light --ar 16:9`\\n\\n**Concept 2 — Cool Minimalist**\\n`living room, brutalist minimalism, concrete floor, slate grey sectional, single arc floor lamp, large art print, negative space, cool natural light --ar 16:9`\\n\\n**Concept 3 — Cosy Eclectic**\\n`boho living room, warm amber light, mixed textiles, vintage Persian rug, gallery wall, trailing houseplants, low warm lighting, layered --ar 16:9`","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["midjourney","dall-e-3","runway"]},{"domain":"Game Development","section":"Game Design","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","title":"Design a Core Game Loop","prompt":"I\'m building a [game genre] game for [target platform]. Help me design the core game loop. Define: the player\'s primary action, the immediate feedback, the short-term goal (session), the long-term goal (progression), and the re-engagement hook. Then identify the 3 biggest risks that could make the loop feel unsatisfying.","tags":["game-design","game-loop","mechanics","prototyping"],"best_for":"Indie developers, game designers, students learning game design","outcome":"A structured core loop design with action/feedback/goals mapped out and 3 risk areas identified.","inputs":[{"label":"game genre"},{"label":"target platform"}],"tools":["Claude","Notion","Unity","Godot"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Game:** Tower Defense Roguelite (Mobile)\\n\\n**Core loop:**\\n- **Primary action:** Place and upgrade towers using earned currency\\n- **Immediate feedback:** Visual + haptic pop when a tower kills an enemy; currency counter ticks up\\n- **Session goal (5–10 min):** Survive N waves and reach the boss\\n- **Progression goal:** Unlock permanent upgrades, new tower types, harder maps\\n- **Re-engagement hook:** Daily challenge with unique constraint; streak reward system\\n\\n**Top 3 risks:**\\n1. **Upgrade overwhelm** — Too many options at once kills mobile pacing. Solution: gate by wave milestone.\\n2. **No comeback mechanic** — If a run goes bad early, players quit. Add a \'Last Stand\' emergency ability.\\n3. **Progression plateau** — If permanent upgrades cap out, endgame feels flat. Plan a prestige system from day one.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","cursor"]},{"domain":"Game Development","section":"Narrative & Dialogue","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","title":"Write Branching NPC Dialogue","prompt":"Write branching dialogue for an NPC named [NPC name] who is [personality description] in a [game setting]. The player needs to [player goal in this interaction]. Create 3 conversation paths: friendly approach, aggressive approach, and clever/persuasion approach. Each path should have 3 exchanges and end with a different outcome.","tags":["narrative","dialogue","npc","rpg","game-writing"],"best_for":"Game writers, narrative designers, RPG developers","outcome":"Three fully-written branching dialogue paths with distinct outcomes for different player approaches.","inputs":[{"label":"NPC name"},{"label":"personality description"},{"label":"game setting"},{"label":"player goal in this interaction"}],"tools":["Claude","Twine","Ink","Unity"],"output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**NPC:** Maren — tired city guard, underpaid, secretly sympathetic\\n\\n**PATH A — Friendly**\\nPlayer: \\"Rough shift?\\"\\nMaren: \\"You have no idea. Third double this week. What do you need?\\"\\nPlayer: \\"Just trying to get into the merchants\' quarter.\\"\\nMaren: *sighs* \\"Gate closes at ninth bell. But… I didn\'t see you walk through just now. Move quick.\\"\\n*Outcome: Passage granted, +5 reputation with City Guard faction*\\n\\n**PATH B — Aggressive**\\nPlayer: \\"Get out of my way.\\"\\nMaren: \\"Excuse me? You want to try that again?\\"\\n*Outcome: Hostile, -10 City Guard reputation, forced combat or retreat*\\n\\n**PATH C — Persuasion**\\nPlayer: \\"I heard the captain skims the gate fees. Must be frustrating doing the work and seeing none of it.\\"\\nMaren: *quietly* \\"Who told you that?\\" *pause* \\"Fine. But you didn\'t hear this from me.\\"\\n*Outcome: Access + quest hook: Expose corrupt captain*","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","cursor"]},{"domain":"Game Development","section":"Programming","skill_level":"ADVANCED","title":"Generate Unity C# Game Systems","prompt":"I\'m building a [game type] in Unity. Write a clean, commented C# script for [specific system]. The system should: [list 3 requirements]. Use Unity best practices: SerializeField for inspector exposure, coroutines where appropriate, and the observer pattern via events for decoupling. Include a brief architecture note at the top.","tags":["unity","csharp","game-programming","systems"],"best_for":"Unity developers, indie game programmers, CS students","outcome":"A production-quality Unity C# script with architecture notes, events-based design, and full comments.","inputs":[{"label":"game type"},{"label":"specific system"},{"label":"list 3 requirements"}],"tools":["Unity","Visual Studio","Claude"],"output_kind":"code","sample_output":"```csharp\\n// InventorySystem.cs\\n// Architecture: Uses event-driven design to decouple UI from inventory logic.\\n// Subscribe to OnInventoryChanged to update any UI without direct references.\\n\\nusing UnityEngine;\\nusing System;\\nusing System.Collections.Generic;\\n\\npublic class InventorySystem : MonoBehaviour\\n{\\n    public static event Action<List<Item>> OnInventoryChanged;\\n\\n    [SerializeField] private int maxSlots = 20;\\n    private List<Item> _items = new List<Item>();\\n\\n    public bool AddItem(Item item)\\n    {\\n        if (_items.Count >= maxSlots) return false;\\n        _items.Add(item);\\n        OnInventoryChanged?.Invoke(_items);\\n        return true;\\n    }\\n\\n    public void RemoveItem(Item item)\\n    {\\n        if (_items.Remove(item))\\n            OnInventoryChanged?.Invoke(_items);\\n    }\\n}\\n```","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","cursor"]},{"domain":"Game Development","section":"Game Design","skill_level":"ADVANCED","title":"Balance a Game Economy","prompt":"I have a [game genre] with this economy: [describe currency, sources, and sinks]. Players are reporting that [specific problem: inflation / deflation / pay-to-win feeling / etc]. Diagnose the root cause, propose 3 fixes with trade-offs, and give me a spreadsheet schema I can use to model the economy before implementing changes.","tags":["game-economy","balancing","monetization","design"],"best_for":"Game designers, live ops teams, monetization designers","outcome":"Root-cause diagnosis, 3 fixes with trade-offs, and a spreadsheet schema for economy modeling.","inputs":[{"label":"game genre"},{"label":"describe currency, sources, and sinks"},{"label":"specific problem: inflation / deflation / pay-to-win feeling / etc"}],"tools":["Claude","Google Sheets","Excel"],"output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Diagnosis:** Soft currency inflation\\n\\nYour daily quest rewards (500 coins) outpace the primary sink (upgrades average 800 coins but only needed every 3 days). Players accumulate ~1,500 coins/day with nowhere to spend them, making purchases feel meaningless.\\n\\n**Fix 1 — Add a time-limited sink**\\nFlash merchant appears daily with exclusive cosmetics for 2,000 coins. *Trade-off:* Requires art/content overhead.\\n\\n**Fix 2 — Reduce quest rewards by 30%**\\nSimple lever, ships fast. *Trade-off:* Risk of player backlash; needs communication.\\n\\n**Fix 3 — Add a prestige/conversion system**\\n10,000 coins → 1 premium token. Creates an aspirational sink. *Trade-off:* Competitive pressure with IAP.\\n\\n**Spreadsheet schema:**\\n| Day | Coins earned | Coins spent | Net | Running total | Active sinks |","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","cursor"]},{"domain":"Game Development","section":"AI & Agents","skill_level":"EXPERT","title":"Design an LLM-Powered NPC Brain","prompt":"I want to build an NPC in [game engine] that uses an LLM for dynamic dialogue and decision-making. Design the complete architecture: context window management strategy, memory system (short + long term), personality consistency mechanism, cost-control approach, and fallback for offline/slow responses. Include a sample system prompt and the API call structure.","tags":["llm","ai-npc","game-ai","agents","architecture"],"best_for":"Advanced game developers, AI engineers building game AI","outcome":"Full LLM-NPC architecture with memory design, cost controls, system prompt, and API structure.","inputs":[{"label":"game engine"}],"tools":["Claude API","OpenAI API","Unity","Unreal Engine"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Architecture: LLM NPC Brain v1**\\n\\n**Context window strategy:**\\n- Fixed system prompt: ~800 tokens (personality, world, current state)\\n- Rolling dialogue window: last 10 exchanges (~600 tokens)\\n- Injected memory summary: top 3 relevant memories (~200 tokens)\\n- Total budget: 1,600 tokens in, 200 tokens out\\n\\n**Memory system:**\\n- Short-term: last 10 messages in RAM\\n- Long-term: vector DB (Chroma) — embed each exchange, retrieve top-3 by cosine similarity at query time\\n\\n**System prompt skeleton:**\\n```\\nYou are Aldric, a suspicious tavern keeper in the city of Veth.\\nPersonality: guarded, dry humour, loyal to paying customers.\\nCurrent state: {npc_mood}, {time_of_day}, {player_reputation}\\nRecent memory: {memory_summary}\\nRespond in 1-2 sentences. Stay in character. Never break the fourth wall.\\n```\\n\\n**Cost control:** Cache system prompt with Anthropic prompt caching. Use Haiku for ambient chatter, Sonnet for quest-critical dialogue.","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","cursor"]},{"domain":"Game Development","section":"Procedural Generation","skill_level":"EXPERT","title":"Procedural Level Design System","prompt":"Design a procedural level generation system for a [game genre]. Define: the grammar rules (what elements can follow what), the constraint system (difficulty curve, pacing, accessibility), the seeded random approach, and the validation step that ensures every generated level is beatable. Give me pseudocode for the generator and a sample level output.","tags":["procedural-generation","level-design","algorithms","game-programming"],"best_for":"Advanced game developers, technical designers","outcome":"A complete procedural level design specification with grammar rules, constraints, pseudocode, and sample output.","inputs":[{"label":"game genre"}],"tools":["Claude","Python","Unity","Godot"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**System: Dungeon Crawler Level Generator**\\n\\n**Grammar rules:**\\nRoom types: [ENTRANCE, COMBAT, TREASURE, PUZZLE, BOSS]\\nSequence: ENTRANCE → (COMBAT|PUZZLE)+ → TREASURE? → BOSS\\nConstraint: No two COMBAT rooms adjacent; TREASURE only after COMBAT\\n\\n**Difficulty curve:**\\nEnemy HP = base × (1 + 0.15 × roomIndex)\\nRoom count = 8 + floor(level/3)\\n\\n**Pseudocode:**\\n```\\nfunction generateLevel(seed, difficulty):\\n  rng = SeededRandom(seed)\\n  rooms = [ENTRANCE]\\n  while not valid(rooms):\\n    rooms = buildChain(rng, difficulty)\\n  return connectRooms(rooms, rng)\\n\\nfunction validate(rooms):\\n  return isReachable(rooms) and hasBoss(rooms) and difficultyInBounds(rooms)\\n```\\n\\n**Sample output (seed 4821, difficulty 2):**\\nENTRANCE → COMBAT(3 goblins) → PUZZLE(pressure plates) → COMBAT(5 goblins + archer) → TREASURE(rare sword) → BOSS(Lich, 240HP)","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","cursor"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"AI & Agents","skill_level":"ADVANCED","title":"Build a Personal Finance AI Agent","prompt":"I want to build a local AI agent that connects to my bank accounts via [bank API or CSV export], stores transactions in a local SQLite database, and runs a daily summary that categorises spending, flags anomalies, and suggests actions. Design the full agent architecture: data ingestion pipeline, categorisation prompt, anomaly-detection logic, and the daily briefing prompt template. Include Python pseudocode for the main loop and the schema for the local DB.","tags":["personal-finance","ai-agent","automation","plaid","sqlite","budgeting"],"best_for":"Developers who want AI-driven personal finance automation without relying on third-party apps","source":"Wes Roth — \\"AI just BROKE the ENTIRE INDUSTRY...\\"","outcome":"Full architecture for a self-hosted personal finance AI agent with ingestion pipeline, DB schema, categorisation logic, anomaly detection, and daily briefing template.","inputs":[{"label":"bank API or CSV export"},{"label":"spending categories"},{"label":"monthly budget targets"}],"tools":["Claude API","Plaid API","Python","SQLite"],"est_time":"3–5 hours","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Agent Architecture: Personal Finance AI**\\n\\n**DB Schema (SQLite):**\\n```sql\\nCREATE TABLE transactions (\\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\\n  date TEXT, amount REAL, merchant TEXT,\\n  category TEXT, raw_category TEXT, flagged INTEGER DEFAULT 0\\n);\\nCREATE TABLE daily_summaries (date TEXT PRIMARY KEY, json TEXT);\\n```\\n\\n**Ingestion pipeline:**\\n1. Pull transactions via Plaid /transactions/sync (or parse CSV)\\n2. Upsert into SQLite (dedup by transaction id)\\n3. For each uncategorised row, call Claude with merchant name + amount → returns category\\n\\n**Categorisation prompt:**\\n```\\nClassify this transaction into one of: [Food, Transport, Housing, Subscriptions, Shopping, Health, Entertainment, Other].\\nMerchant: {merchant}  Amount: ${amount}\\nReturn only the category name.\\n```\\n\\n**Anomaly detection logic:**\\n- Flag if amount > 2× rolling 30-day average for that category\\n- Flag if merchant appears for the first time and amount > $50\\n\\n**Daily briefing prompt:**\\n```\\nGiven these transactions from {date}: {json}\\nAnd monthly budget targets: {targets}\\nWrite a 5-bullet morning briefing covering: total spend, top category, biggest single charge, any flagged anomalies, and one actionable suggestion.\\n```","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Financial Planning & Analysis","skill_level":"ADVANCED","title":"Tax Strategy Finder (CPA-Level Automation)","prompt":"Act as a senior CPA and tax strategist. I will give you my [income sources], [filing status], [major expenses], and [investment portfolio]. Identify the top 5 tax optimisation strategies available to me, explain the mechanism of each deduction or deferral, estimate the potential savings, flag any risks or thresholds I need to stay under, and give me a prioritised action checklist for this tax year. Reference relevant IRS code sections or equivalent for [country].","tags":["tax","tax-strategy","cpa","deductions","financial-planning","irs"],"best_for":"Self-employed professionals, investors, and business owners looking to reduce tax liability","source":"Wes Roth — \\"AI just BROKE the ENTIRE INDUSTRY...\\"","outcome":"Ranked list of tax strategies with mechanisms, estimated savings, risk flags, and a concrete action checklist for the current tax year.","inputs":[{"label":"income sources (salary, freelance, dividends, etc.)"},{"label":"filing status (single, MFJ, etc.)"},{"label":"major expenses (home office, vehicle, health, education)"},{"label":"investment portfolio (taxable, IRA, 401k balances)"},{"label":"country"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"30 minutes","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Top 5 Tax Strategies for Your Profile**\\n\\n**1. Max Solo 401(k) — estimated savings: $14,280**\\nAs a self-employed person you can contribute up to $66,000 (2024). The employer contribution side (25% of net self-employment income) is deductible on Schedule 1. *IRC §401(a).* Action: open a Solo 401(k) by Dec 31; fund by tax deadline.\\n\\n**2. Home Office Deduction (Simplified Method) — ~$1,500**\\n$5/sq ft × up to 300 sq ft. No depreciation recapture risk. *IRC §280A.* Action: measure dedicated workspace, document with photos.\\n\\n**3. SEP-IRA vs Solo 401(k) comparison**\\nSEP-IRA simpler to open, but Solo 401(k) allows employee deferrals — better if income < $200k.\\n\\n**4. Qualified Business Income (QBI) Deduction — up to 20% of net income**\\nAvailable for pass-through entities below $182,050 (single). *IRC §199A.* Risk: phase-out applies to specified service trades.\\n\\n**5. Tax-Loss Harvesting on taxable portfolio**\\nRealise ~$8k in unrealised losses to offset gains. Beware 30-day wash-sale rule. *IRC §1091.*\\n\\n**Action checklist:**\\n- [ ] Open Solo 401(k) before Dec 31\\n- [ ] Calculate exact home office sq footage\\n- [ ] Review taxable account for harvesting candidates\\n- [ ] Confirm QBI eligibility with your business type","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Personal Productivity","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","title":"AI Health Data Tracker & Interpreter","prompt":"I will paste the results from my recent [blood work / health metrics]. Interpret each value, flag anything outside the optimal range (not just the lab reference range), explain what each flagged value might indicate, suggest 3 lifestyle or dietary adjustments I could discuss with my doctor, and format the output as a clear summary table followed by the action points. Do not diagnose — focus on pattern recognition and evidence-based context.","tags":["health","blood-work","biometrics","wellness","personal-data","tracking"],"best_for":"Health-conscious individuals who want to understand their lab results and prepare smarter doctor conversations","source":"Wes Roth — \\"AI just BROKE the ENTIRE INDUSTRY...\\"","outcome":"Clear interpretation of health metrics with optimal vs. reference range comparison, pattern flags, lifestyle suggestions, and a ready-to-use doctor conversation summary.","inputs":[{"label":"blood work or health metrics (paste raw values)"},{"label":"age and biological sex"},{"label":"known conditions or medications (optional)"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"10 minutes","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Health Metrics Summary**\\n\\n| Marker | Your Value | Lab Range | Optimal Range | Status |\\n|---|---|---|---|---|\\n| LDL Cholesterol | 142 mg/dL | <160 | <100 | ⚠️ Elevated |\\n| HbA1c | 5.8% | <5.7 pre-diabetic | <5.4 | ⚠️ Borderline |\\n| Vitamin D | 24 ng/mL | 20–50 | 40–60 | ⚠️ Sub-optimal |\\n| Ferritin | 68 ng/mL | 12–300 | 50–150 | ✅ Good |\\n| TSH | 2.1 mIU/L | 0.4–4.0 | 0.5–2.5 | ✅ Good |\\n\\n**Flagged patterns:**\\n- LDL + borderline HbA1c together suggest early metabolic stress worth monitoring.\\n- Low-normal Vitamin D may be contributing to fatigue.\\n\\n**Lifestyle adjustments to discuss with your doctor:**\\n1. Mediterranean-style diet to address LDL and glycaemic trends simultaneously.\\n2. Vitamin D3 + K2 supplementation (2,000–4,000 IU/day) — confirm dose with doctor.\\n3. 150 min/week moderate cardio — independently improves all three flagged markers.\\n\\n*This is pattern recognition, not medical advice. Bring this table to your next appointment.*","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"AI & Agents","skill_level":"EXPERT","title":"Ghost Database for AI Agents","prompt":"Design a persistent memory and knowledge layer — a \'ghost database\' — for a long-running AI agent system built with [framework/stack]. The system must support: short-term episodic memory (recent conversation turns), long-term semantic memory (vector search over past interactions and documents), structured fact storage (key-value entities the agent can update), and a retrieval strategy that selects the right memory type at inference time. Provide the full schema, the retrieval orchestration logic, a sample system-prompt injection template, and guidance on when to write vs. read from each store.","tags":["ai-agent","memory","vector-db","architecture","rag","persistent-state","llm-ops"],"best_for":"AI engineers building autonomous agents that need reliable long-term memory and context management","source":"Wes Roth — \\"AI just BROKE the ENTIRE INDUSTRY...\\"","outcome":"Complete ghost-database architecture spec with schemas for all three memory types, retrieval orchestration pseudocode, system-prompt injection template, and write/read decision rules.","inputs":[{"label":"framework/stack (LangChain, custom Python, etc.)"},{"label":"agent\'s primary domain or task"},{"label":"expected conversation volume (light / heavy)"}],"tools":["Claude API","OpenAI API","Chroma","Pinecone","Redis","PostgreSQL","Python"],"est_time":"2–4 hours","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Ghost Database Architecture**\\n\\n**Memory layers:**\\n\\n| Layer | Store | TTL | Use case |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| Episodic (short-term) | Redis list (sliding window) | Last 20 turns | Recent dialogue context |\\n| Semantic (long-term) | ChromaDB / Pinecone | Permanent | Past interactions, docs |\\n| Structured facts | PostgreSQL key-value table | Permanent, mutable | User prefs, entity state |\\n\\n**Structured facts schema:**\\n```sql\\nCREATE TABLE agent_facts (\\n  agent_id TEXT, key TEXT, value JSONB,\\n  confidence REAL, updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ,\\n  PRIMARY KEY (agent_id, key)\\n);\\n```\\n\\n**Retrieval orchestration (pseudocode):**\\n```python\\ndef build_context(query, agent_id):\\n  episodic  = redis.lrange(f\'ep:{agent_id}\', 0, 19)      # always include\\n  semantic  = chroma.query(query, n_results=4)             # top-4 semantic hits\\n  facts     = pg.fetch(\'SELECT key, value FROM agent_facts WHERE agent_id=$1\', agent_id)\\n  return format_context(episodic, semantic, facts)\\n```\\n\\n**System-prompt injection template:**\\n```\\n[MEMORY]\\nRecent context: {episodic_summary}\\nRelevant past knowledge: {semantic_hits}\\nKnown facts about user: {facts_json}\\n[/MEMORY]\\n```\\n\\n**Write rules:**\\n- After every turn → append to episodic Redis list, pop oldest if > 20\\n- After task completion → embed summary → upsert to vector DB\\n- When agent learns a stable fact (name, preference, goal) → upsert to PostgreSQL facts table","dateAdded":"2025-01-01","related_tools":["cursor","github-copilot","claude-code"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Build Any Power BI Chart with a Natural Language Prompt","prompt":"\\"I want to create a [chart type, e.g. waterfall / line / scatter / donut] in Power BI.\\n\\nMy data includes:\\n- Fact table: [table name + relevant columns]\\n- Date table: [table name]\\n- Key metric: [e.g. Revenue, Units Sold, Gross Margin]\\n- Breakdown dimension: [e.g. Region, Product, Month]\\n\\nI want to show: [describe the story, e.g. \'how revenue has changed vs. prior year by month\']\\n\\nPlease give me:\\n1. The exact prompt to paste into Power BI Copilot to build this chart\\n2. Which visual type to select and why\\n3. Any simple DAX measure I need beforehand\\n4. Two formatting tips to make it presentation-ready\\"","tags":["power-bi","copilot","ai-charts","natural-language","beginner"],"best_for":"Power BI users who want to skip manual chart setup and use Copilot to generate visuals instantly","source":"How to Power BI — \\"AI Can Now Build ANY Power BI Chart You Want\\" (2026)","outcome":"A ready-to-paste Copilot prompt, the correct visual type with justification, a starter DAX measure, and two formatting tips.","inputs":[{"label":"chart type, e.g. waterfall / line / scatter / donut"},{"label":"fact table name and relevant columns"},{"label":"date table name"},{"label":"key metric, e.g. Revenue, Units Sold"},{"label":"breakdown dimension, e.g. Region, Product, Month"},{"label":"describe the story you want to show"}],"tools":["Power BI Copilot","Power BI Desktop"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Copilot prompt to paste:**\\n\\"Create a waterfall chart showing monthly Revenue variance versus prior year. Use the [Sales] table with [Revenue] and [Date].[Month]. Highlight positive months in teal and negative months in red.\\"\\n\\n**Visual type:** Waterfall — best for showing how each month\'s delta builds up to the total annual variance.\\n\\n**DAX measure to create first:**\\n```dax\\nRevenue vs PY =\\n[Total Revenue]\\n  - CALCULATE([Total Revenue], SAMEPERIODLASTYEAR(\'Date\'[Date]))\\n```\\n\\n**Formatting tips:**\\n- Enable data labels to show the exact delta on each bar\\n- Pin the Y-axis to zero so gains and losses are visually comparable","dateAdded":"2026-05-23","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notebooklm"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Auto-Generate DAX Measures from Plain English","prompt":"\\"I need a DAX measure for Power BI. Here is what I want it to calculate in plain English:\\n\\n[Describe the calculation, e.g. \'Year-to-date revenue compared to the same period last year, expressed as a % change\']\\n\\nData model context:\\n- Fact table: [name + key columns]\\n- Date table: [name + date column, is it marked as a date table? yes/no]\\n- Related dimensions: [e.g. Customer, Product, Region tables]\\n- Existing base measures I can reference: [list, e.g. [Total Revenue], [Units Sold]]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Write the DAX measure using VAR/RETURN style\\n2. Explain each function in one plain-English sentence\\n3. Flag any edge cases (blanks, missing periods, filter context issues)\\n4. Provide a simplified version for a less experienced colleague\\"","tags":["dax","power-bi","measures","ai-assisted","data-modelling"],"best_for":"Power BI developers who want faster measure writing or need to explain DAX to business stakeholders","source":"How to Power BI — \\"AI Can Now Build ANY Power BI Chart You Want\\" (2026)","outcome":"A production-ready DAX measure in VAR/RETURN style, plain-English explanations of every function, edge-case warnings, and a simplified version.","inputs":[{"label":"describe the calculation in plain English"},{"label":"fact table name and key columns"},{"label":"date table name and whether it is marked as a date table"},{"label":"related dimension tables"},{"label":"existing base measures to reference"}],"tools":["Claude Sonnet","Power BI Desktop","Power BI Copilot"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Production measure:**\\n```dax\\nRevenue YoY % =\\nVAR _Curr = [Total Revenue]\\nVAR _Prev = CALCULATE([Total Revenue], SAMEPERIODLASTYEAR(\'Date\'[Date]))\\nRETURN\\n    DIVIDE(_Curr - _Prev, _Prev, BLANK())\\n```\\n\\n**Function explanations:**\\n- `CALCULATE` — re-evaluates a measure under a modified filter context\\n- `SAMEPERIODLASTYEAR` — shifts the date filter back exactly 12 months\\n- `DIVIDE` — safe division that returns BLANK() instead of an error when the denominator is zero\\n\\n**Edge cases:**\\n- Returns BLANK() for periods with no prior-year data — visuals handle this cleanly\\n- Requires a marked date table; if not marked, replace with `DATEADD(\'Date\'[Date], -1, YEAR)`\\n- Slicer selections (e.g. Region) are automatically respected via filter context\\n\\n**Simplified version:**\\n```dax\\nRevenue YoY % Simple =\\nDIVIDE(\\n    [Total Revenue] - CALCULATE([Total Revenue], SAMEPERIODLASTYEAR(\'Date\'[Date])),\\n    CALCULATE([Total Revenue], SAMEPERIODLASTYEAR(\'Date\'[Date]))\\n)\\n```","dateAdded":"2026-05-23","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notebooklm"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Design a Full Power BI Report Page with AI","prompt":"\\"I need to design a Power BI report page for [audience, e.g. Sales Director / CFO / Operations team].\\n\\nCore business question this page must answer:\\n[e.g. \'Are we on track to hit our Q3 revenue target, and which regions are behind?\']\\n\\nAvailable tables: [list: e.g. Sales, Date, Customer, Product, Region, Targets]\\nKey KPIs to show (3–5): [list with desired format, e.g. \'Revenue — currency, 0 decimals\']\\nDesired interactions: [e.g. slicer by Region, drill-through to product detail]\\n\\nPlease produce:\\n1. A page layout blueprint (label each panel: visual type, size, position)\\n2. The DAX for each KPI card\\n3. The Copilot prompt to auto-generate this page in Power BI Service\\n4. One design tip for this specific audience\\"","tags":["power-bi","report-design","copilot","kpi","dashboard","layout"],"best_for":"BI analysts who need to build executive-facing dashboards quickly with a structured, AI-assisted design process","source":"How to Power BI — \\"AI Can Now Build ANY Power BI Chart You Want\\" (2026)","outcome":"A labelled page layout blueprint, DAX for every KPI card, a ready-to-use Copilot prompt, and one tailored design tip.","inputs":[{"label":"audience, e.g. Sales Director / CFO / Operations team"},{"label":"core business question the page must answer"},{"label":"list available tables"},{"label":"3–5 KPIs with desired format"},{"label":"desired interactions/slicers"}],"tools":["Claude Sonnet","Power BI Copilot","Power BI Desktop"],"est_time":"45 min","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Page layout blueprint:**\\n```\\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\\n│ KPI Row: [Revenue] [vs Target %] [YoY %] [Open Pipeline] │\\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\\n│ Main (60% width): Line — Monthly Revenue vs Target by Region │\\n│ Right (40% width): Bar — Top 10 Accounts by Revenue  │\\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\\n│ Bottom: Matrix — Region × Product (heat map colour scale)  │\\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\\nSlicer: Region (top-right, horizontal pill style)\\n```\\n\\n**DAX — Revenue vs Target %:**\\n```dax\\nRevenue vs Target % =\\nVAR _A = [Total Revenue]\\nVAR _T = SUM(\'Targets\'[Revenue Target])\\nRETURN DIVIDE(_A - _T, _T)\\n```\\n\\n**Copilot prompt:**\\n\\"Create a sales performance page with a KPI row (Total Revenue, Revenue vs Target %, YoY Growth, Open Pipeline), a line chart of Monthly Revenue vs Target by Region, a Top 10 Accounts bar chart, and a Region × Product matrix. Add a Region slicer.\\"\\n\\n**Design tip for Sales Director:** Lead with the traffic-light KPI row — executives scan top-left first. Use conditional formatting (red/green) on the matrix so underperforming cells are instantly visible without reading numbers.","dateAdded":"2026-05-23","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notebooklm"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Prepare Your Power BI Semantic Model for AI & Copilot","prompt":"\\"I want to optimise my Power BI semantic model so that Copilot and AI Q&A give accurate, reliable answers.\\n\\nModel overview:\\n- Key tables: [list]\\n- Most important measures: [list 5–10 with a brief description of each]\\n- Main relationships: [describe, e.g. Sales[CustomerID] → Customer[ID], many-to-one]\\n- Primary audience: [e.g. Finance team, regional sales managers]\\n- Fiscal calendar: [standard Jan–Dec / custom — specify start month]\\n\\nPlease produce:\\n1. Field-level descriptions for the 8 most Copilot-critical columns (plain English, ≤ 2 sentences each)\\n2. The full AI Instructions text for the \'Prepare data for AI\' panel in Power BI Service\\n3. A synonym list for the top 5 measures (natural-language aliases your audience would use)\\n4. A gap analysis: list the 5 most likely natural-language questions your audience will ask, and flag which ones your current model cannot answer and why\\"","tags":["power-bi","semantic-model","copilot","ai-prep","data-modelling","field-descriptions"],"best_for":"BI developers and data engineers who want Copilot to work reliably instead of returning vague or wrong answers","source":"How to Power BI — \\"AI Can Now Build ANY Power BI Chart You Want\\" (2026)","outcome":"Eight field descriptions, complete AI Instructions text, synonym list, and a gap analysis flagging which natural-language questions your model can and cannot yet answer.","inputs":[{"label":"list key tables"},{"label":"list 5–10 important measures with brief descriptions"},{"label":"describe main relationships"},{"label":"primary audience"},{"label":"fiscal calendar — standard or custom start month"}],"tools":["Claude Sonnet","Power BI Desktop","Power BI Service"],"est_time":"1.5 hours","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Field descriptions (sample):**\\n- `Net Revenue`: Total sales after discounts and returns, in USD. Excludes intercompany and contra-revenue items.\\n- `Gross Margin %`: Gross profit divided by Net Revenue. Use this — not Revenue — to compare profitability across segments.\\n- `Close Date`: Date a deal was marked Won in Salesforce. Use for period reporting; distinct from Invoice Date.\\n- `ARR`: Annual Recurring Revenue. Annualised value of active subscriptions; excludes one-time fees.\\n\\n**AI Instructions text:**\\n> \\"This model covers B2B Sales performance for the Americas region. \'Revenue\' always means Net Revenue after returns. For \'targets\', use the [Quota] table, not [Forecast]. Our fiscal year starts February 1 — when asked about \'this year\' or \'YTD\', use fiscal year. Default to current fiscal period unless the user specifies otherwise. \'Churn\' refers to the [Churned ARR] measure.\\"\\n\\n**Synonyms:**\\n- Net Revenue → Sales, Bookings, Income, Top Line\\n- Gross Margin % → Margin, Profitability, GM%\\n- Churned ARR → Churn, Lost Revenue, Cancellations\\n\\n**Gap analysis:**\\n- ✅ \'What is our revenue this quarter?\' — answerable\\n- ✅ \'Which region is furthest behind target?\' — answerable\\n- ❌ \'Why did churn spike in March?\' — needs a narrative/commentary measure; model has no causal layer\\n- ❌ \'What will Q4 look like?\' — no forecast table connected; add [Forecast] table\\n- ⚠️ \'Show me deals at risk\' — partial: pipeline data exists but no risk-score measure","dateAdded":"2026-05-23","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notebooklm"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Ask Your Power BI Dashboard Questions in Plain English","prompt":"\\"I have a Power BI dashboard and I want to use Copilot\'s Q&A feature to explore data with natural language instead of building visuals manually.\\n\\nMy dashboard covers: [topic, e.g. sales performance / HR headcount / inventory levels]\\nKey measures available: [list 3–5, e.g. Revenue, Headcount, Stock Levels]\\nI typically need to answer these business questions: [list 3–5 real questions your team asks]\\n\\nFor each of my questions, write:\\n1. The exact natural-language query to type into Power BI Copilot / Q&A\\n2. What type of visual it will likely return\\n3. A follow-up question to drill deeper\\n4. One tip to refine the answer if the first result is off\\"","tags":["power-bi","q-and-a","natural-language","copilot","self-service-bi","beginner"],"best_for":"Business users who want to explore Power BI data without asking the BI team to build new reports","source":"How to Power BI — \\"AI Can Now Build ANY Power BI Chart You Want\\" (2026)","outcome":"An exact natural-language query for each of your business questions, the expected visual type, a drill-down follow-up, and a refinement tip per question.","inputs":[{"label":"dashboard topic, e.g. sales performance / inventory levels"},{"label":"list 3–5 available key measures"},{"label":"list 3–5 real business questions your team asks regularly"}],"tools":["Power BI Copilot","Power BI Q&A visual"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Q1: \'Are we hitting our sales target?\'**\\n- Query to type: *\\"Show revenue vs target by region this quarter as a bar chart\\"*\\n- Expected visual: Clustered bar — Actual vs Target side by side per region\\n- Follow-up: *\\"Which sales rep in the bottom region has the largest gap?\\"*\\n- Refinement tip: If Copilot uses the wrong date range, add *\\"for Q3 FY2026\\"* explicitly\\n\\n**Q2: \'Which product is selling the most?\'**\\n- Query to type: *\\"Top 10 products by units sold this year\\"*\\n- Expected visual: Ranked bar chart, descending\\n- Follow-up: *\\"Show the same top 10 by revenue margin instead of units\\"*\\n- Refinement tip: Say *\\"by product name not SKU\\"* if it returns codes instead of readable names\\n\\n**Q3: \'How is this month trending vs last month?\'**\\n- Query to type: *\\"Daily revenue this month vs last month as a line chart\\"*\\n- Expected visual: Dual-line chart with month comparison\\n- Follow-up: *\\"Highlight the days where this month fell below last month\\"*\\n- Refinement tip: If it shows weekly not daily, add *\\"daily granularity\\"* to your prompt","dateAdded":"2026-05-23","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notebooklm"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"AI-Built FP&A Dashboard in Power BI — Step by Step","prompt":"\\"I want to build a Finance / FP&A dashboard in Power BI using AI to accelerate every step.\\n\\nDashboard purpose: [e.g. Monthly P&L review / Budget vs Actual / Cash flow monitoring]\\nAudience: [e.g. CFO + Finance team]\\nData sources: [e.g. ERP export in Excel, General Ledger CSV, Headcount table]\\nKey financial metrics to show: [list 5–8, e.g. Revenue, COGS, Gross Margin, OPEX, EBITDA, Headcount]\\nFiscal year: [Jan–Dec / Feb–Jan / other]\\n\\nFor each stage of the build, give me:\\n1. DATA PREP — the AI prompt to clean and structure the source data in Power Query\\n2. MODELLING — the DAX measures to create (with code)\\n3. VISUAL DESIGN — the Copilot prompt to build each chart/KPI\\n4. COMMENTARY — the AI prompt to auto-write the CFO narrative for this month\\n5. SHARING — how to set up row-level security so each region only sees their own data\\"","tags":["power-bi","fpa","finance","dashboard","dax","copilot","cfo","p-and-l"],"best_for":"FP&A analysts building their first Power BI finance dashboard or replacing a static Excel/PowerPoint pack","source":"How to Power BI — \\"AI Can Now Build ANY Power BI Chart You Want\\" (2026)","outcome":"End-to-end build guide: Power Query AI prompts, DAX for all financial measures, Copilot design prompts per visual, a CFO commentary template, and row-level security setup instructions.","inputs":[{"label":"dashboard purpose, e.g. Monthly P&L / Budget vs Actual"},{"label":"audience, e.g. CFO + Finance team"},{"label":"data sources, e.g. ERP export, GL CSV"},{"label":"list 5–8 key financial metrics"},{"label":"fiscal year start month"}],"tools":["Power BI Desktop","Power BI Copilot","Claude Sonnet","Power Query","Excel"],"est_time":"3–4 hours","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**1. DATA PREP — Power Query AI prompt:**\\n\\"Clean this General Ledger export: remove blank rows, split the Account Code column into Department and Account Number, standardise all date formats to YYYY-MM-DD, and flag any negative Revenue lines as \'Adjustment\' in a new Type column.\\"\\n\\n**2. KEY DAX MEASURES:**\\n```dax\\nGross Margin % =\\nDIVIDE([Gross Profit], [Total Revenue], BLANK())\\n\\nBudget Variance % =\\nDIVIDE([Total Revenue] - SUM(\'Budget\'[Revenue]), SUM(\'Budget\'[Revenue]))\\n\\nEBITDA =\\n[Gross Profit] - [Total OPEX] + [D&A]\\n```\\n\\n**3. COPILOT VISUAL PROMPT:**\\n\\"Build a P&L summary page with: a KPI row (Revenue, Gross Margin %, EBITDA, Headcount), a waterfall chart showing Revenue → Gross Profit → EBITDA bridge, and a small multiples line chart of Revenue by Department vs prior year. Add a Month slicer.\\"\\n\\n**4. CFO COMMENTARY PROMPT:**\\n\\"Write a 3-paragraph CFO commentary for [Month] [Year]. Revenue was [X] vs budget [Y] ([Z]%). Gross margin was [A]% vs [B]% prior year. OPEX was [C] vs budget [D]. Tone: direct, no jargon, flag two risks and one positive. Format: bullet summary + 2-sentence paragraph per metric.\\"\\n\\n**5. ROW-LEVEL SECURITY:**\\nIn Power BI Desktop → Modelling → Manage Roles → create role \'Region Manager\' with filter: `[Region] = USERPRINCIPALNAME()`. Publish and assign users in Power BI Service → Dataset → Security.","dateAdded":"2026-05-23","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"title":"AI Amplifier Readiness Assessment","domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Financial Planning & Analysis","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","best_for":"Finance leaders and FP&A managers evaluating AI adoption readiness","outcome":"A structured readiness report identifying which processes will amplify good outcomes vs. which will amplify existing problems — with a prioritised action list before rolling out AI tools.","inputs":[{"label":"your team size and structure (e.g., 5-person FP&A team, 3 senior analysts)"},{"label":"list your top 5 FP&A processes (e.g., monthly close, budget review, variance analysis)"},{"label":"your current data infrastructure (e.g., SAP, Excel, Power BI)"},{"label":"your biggest current pain points (e.g., manual consolidation, late data from regions)"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"45 minutes","output_kind":"analysis","prompt":"You are an AI adoption strategist applying the \'AI as Amplifier\' framework to FP&A.\\n\\nContext: AI doesn\'t create good processes — it amplifies existing ones. Teams with solid fundamentals get dramatically more productive. Teams with weak processes generate confusion faster.\\n\\nMy team: [your team size and structure]\\n\\nOur top 5 FP&A processes:\\n[list your top 5 FP&A processes]\\n\\nData infrastructure:\\n[your current data infrastructure]\\n\\nBiggest pain points:\\n[your biggest current pain points]\\n\\nFor each of our 5 processes, evaluate:\\n1. AMPLIFY WELL ✅ or AMPLIFY PROBLEMS ⚠️ — and why\\n2. What specifically breaks at 10× AI-generated output volume?\\n3. What must be fixed BEFORE deploying AI here?\\n\\nThen give me:\\n- A prioritised sequence for AI adoption (where to start, where to wait)\\n- 3 governance checkpoints needed before scaling\\n- A one-sentence \'AI readiness verdict\' per process","sample_output":"**AI Amplifier Readiness Assessment**\\n\\n| Process | Verdict | 10× Risk | Fix Before AI |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| Monthly close | ✅ Amplifies well | Reconciliation queue depth | Document the 3-step close checklist |\\n| Budget review | ⚠️ Amplifies problems | 10× more versions, no single owner | Establish one source of truth in SAP |\\n| Variance analysis | ✅ Amplifies well | Narrative quality depends on context | Create standard commentary template |\\n| Board deck | ⚠️ Amplifies problems | Inconsistent metrics across slides | Lock 12 KPI definitions first |\\n| Forecast accuracy | ✅ Amplifies well | Model proliferation risk | Version-control models now |\\n\\n**Prioritised adoption sequence:**\\n1. Start: Variance analysis (solid foundation, high volume, clear templates)\\n2. Next: Monthly close (after checklist is documented)\\n3. Wait: Budget review (fix data governance first — AI creates 10× more confusion otherwise)\\n\\n**3 governance checkpoints:**\\n- [ ] All KPIs have locked, approved definitions\\n- [ ] Every AI output has a named human reviewer\\n- [ ] Version control on models before any agentic workflows\\n\\n**Verdict:** Variance and forecast processes are AI-ready today. Budget and board deck need 6 weeks of governance work first.","tags":["ai-strategy","fpna","readiness","governance","amplifier"],"dateAdded":"2026-05-24","source":"Adam Bender, Google I/O 2026 — \'Software Engineering at the Tipping Point\'","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"title":"Second-Order Effects Analysis for AI Automation","domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Strategic Analysis","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🔵","best_for":"Technical leads, product managers, and strategists planning AI automation rollouts","outcome":"A structured analysis of what will break at scale when a proposed AI automation goes live — covering review bottlenecks, testing load, version control, API surface, cost curves, and intellectual control.","inputs":[{"label":"describe the AI automation you\'re planning (e.g., AI writes first-draft code, AI generates monthly reports)"},{"label":"expected volume increase (e.g., from 10 reports/month to 100)"},{"label":"your current review and QA process"},{"label":"your team size and who currently reviews output"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"analysis","prompt":"You are a systems-thinking consultant applying the \'Second-Order Effects\' framework from Adam Bender\'s Google I/O 2026 talk on Software Ecology.\\n\\nThe automation I\'m considering:\\n[describe the AI automation you\'re planning]\\n\\nExpected volume change: [expected volume increase]\\n\\nCurrent review process: [your current review and QA process]\\n\\nTeam: [your team size and who currently reviews output]\\n\\nAnalyse the following second-order effects at 10× and 100× volume:\\n\\n1. **Review bottleneck** — Can humans still meaningfully review this volume? At what point does review become a rubber stamp?\\n2. **QA scaling** — How does testing/validation scale — linearly or quadratically?\\n3. **Cost / Jevons Paradox** — At cheaper unit costs, what new uses proliferate? What does the actual cost curve look like?\\n4. **API surface** — What internal systems will AI agents now access that weren\'t designed for agent use?\\n5. **Agentic conflicts** — Where could two AI agents produce conflicting outputs or edit wars?\\n6. **Intellectual control** — At what volume do humans lose the ability to reason about what the system is doing?\\n\\nFor each: describe the failure mode, estimate the volume at which it triggers, and give one concrete mitigation.","sample_output":"**Second-Order Effects Analysis: AI-Generated Monthly Reports**\\n\\n**1. Review bottleneck**\\nAt 10× volume (100 reports/month), 1 senior analyst is at capacity. At 100×, sign-off becomes a rubber stamp — unread.\\n→ Mitigation: Triage by materiality; auto-approve reports below a $50K variance threshold.\\n\\n**2. QA scaling**\\nTests grow quadratically — 10× more reports × 10× more edge cases = 100× test cases needed.\\n→ Mitigation: Parameterised test suites against a golden dataset; not manual review.\\n\\n**3. Jevons Paradox**\\nAt $0.001/report (vs. $50 analyst-hour), departments request 20× more ad-hoc analyses. Monthly AI cost: $500 → $10,000.\\n→ Mitigation: Per-department budget caps, not per-request.\\n\\n**4. API surface**\\nAgents discover the ERP read endpoint and query production data for draft reports at 3am without audit trail.\\n→ Mitigation: Read-only agent service accounts with rate limiting and full audit logging.\\n\\n**5. Agentic conflicts**\\nFX-adjusted and non-adjusted versions of the same report generated simultaneously; executive receives both, neither labelled canonical.\\n→ Mitigation: Single-output rule per report type; version locking before distribution.\\n\\n**6. Intellectual control**\\nAt 500 auto-generated reports/month, no human has read them all. Systematic prompt bias goes undetected for quarters.\\n→ Mitigation: Monthly red-team sample — 5 random reports read in full by a senior analyst.","tags":["ai-strategy","second-order","systems-thinking","governance","scale"],"dateAdded":"2026-05-24","source":"Adam Bender, Google I/O 2026 — \'Software Engineering at the Tipping Point\'","related_tools":["perplexity","claude","elicit"]},{"title":"Calculadora de Pix para Pequenos Negócios","domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Gestão Financeira","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","best_for":"Empreendedores e donos de pequenos negócios no Brasil que usam Pix como meio de pagamento","outcome":"Um resumo claro dos fluxos de Pix do negócio, identificando os horários de pico, limites relevantes e recomendações para otimizar o caixa.","inputs":[{"label":"volume médio de transações Pix por dia"},{"label":"ticket médio por transação"},{"label":"seus horários de pico de vendas"},{"label":"tipo de negócio (MEI, ME, EPP ou empresa de médio porte)"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"10 min","output_kind":"analysis","prompt":"Você é um consultor financeiro especializado em pequenos negócios brasileiros.\\n\\nMeu negócio:\\n- Tipo: [tipo de negócio]\\n- Volume médio de Pix: [volume médio de transações Pix por dia] transações/dia\\n- Ticket médio: R$ [ticket médio por transação]\\n- Horários de pico: [seus horários de pico de vendas]\\n\\nCom base nessas informações, elabore:\\n1. **Projeção mensal de recebimentos via Pix** (dias úteis vs. fins de semana)\\n2. **Limites relevantes do Banco Central** para o meu perfil (Pix noturno, limites por chave, etc.)\\n3. **Riscos de caixa** — quando posso ter apertos de liquidez?\\n4. **3 recomendações práticas** para otimizar o fluxo de Pix e reduzir inadimplência\\n5. **Checklist de boas práticas de segurança Pix** para o meu tipo de negócio\\n\\nResponda em português do Brasil, com linguagem acessível.","sample_output":"**Análise de Fluxo Pix — Restaurante MEI**\\n\\n**Projeção mensal:**\\n- Dias úteis (22 dias × 45 transações × R$35): R$ 34.650\\n- Fins de semana (8 dias × 80 transações × R$45): R$ 28.800\\n- **Total estimado: R$ 63.450/mês**\\n\\n**Limites relevantes (Banco Central 2026):**\\n- Pix noturno (20h–6h): R$ 1.000 por transação para pessoa física; empresas MEI podem solicitar aumento\\n- Limite diário padrão: definido pelo banco — revise no aplicativo\\n\\n**Riscos de caixa:**\\n- Semanas com feriados emendados reduzem volume ~30%\\n- Chargeback via Pix (MED) pode bloquear saldo em D+1\\n\\n**Recomendações:**\\n1. Habilite chave Pix CNPJ separada da chave pessoal para controle fiscal\\n2. Configure alerta de recebimento no app e registre no DRE semanal\\n3. Mantenha reserva de 2 semanas de custo fixo para períodos de baixo movimento\\n\\n**Segurança:**\\n- [ ] Nunca compartilhe QR Code estático em redes sociais\\n- [ ] Use QR Code dinâmico para valores acima de R$ 200\\n- [ ] Ative autenticação de dois fatores no banco","tags":["pix","brasil","finanças","mei","caixa"],"dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","source":"Banco Central do Brasil — regulamentação Pix 2026","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"title":"Guia de Abertura de MEI com IA","domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Gestão Financeira","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","best_for":"Autônomos e profissionais liberais no Brasil que querem formalizar o negócio como MEI","outcome":"Um guia passo a passo personalizado para abrir o MEI, com enquadramento de CNAE, obrigações mensais e dicas de gestão financeira.","inputs":[{"label":"sua atividade profissional principal (ex: fotógrafo, designer, eletricista)"},{"label":"faturamento mensal estimado"},{"label":"você já tem outros vínculos empregatícios? (sim/não)"},{"label":"estado (UF) onde você vai atuar"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"plan","prompt":"Você é um contador especializado em MEI (Microempreendedor Individual) no Brasil.\\n\\nMinha situação:\\n- Atividade: [sua atividade profissional principal]\\n- Faturamento estimado: R$ [faturamento mensal estimado]/mês\\n- Vínculo empregatício: [você já tem outros vínculos empregatícios]\\n- Estado: [estado (UF) onde você vai atuar]\\n\\nElabore um guia completo com:\\n1. **Verificação de elegibilidade** — posso ser MEI? (limites de faturamento, restrições de sócio)\\n2. **CNAE mais adequado** para minha atividade\\n3. **Passo a passo para abertura no Portal do Empreendedor** (gov.br)\\n4. **Obrigações mensais** — DAS, DASN, DEFIS\\n5. **Tributação** — quanto pago de imposto por faixa de faturamento\\n6. **3 erros comuns** de MEI que geram problemas com a Receita Federal\\n7. **Ferramentas gratuitas** recomendadas para gestão financeira do MEI\\n\\nResponda em português, com linguagem simples e prática.","sample_output":"**Guia MEI — Designer Gráfico Freelancer, SP**\\n\\n**Elegibilidade:**\\n✅ Pode ser MEI — atividade permitida, faturamento dentro do limite de R$ 81.000/ano (R$ 6.750/mês)\\n⚠️ Se tiver sócio em outra empresa, verifique restrição de participação societária\\n\\n**CNAE recomendado:** 7410-2/02 — Design de interiores / 7410-2/03 — Design gráfico e de produto\\n\\n**Passo a passo (Portal do Empreendedor):**\\n1. Acesse gov.br/mei com CPF e senha\\n2. Clique em \'Formalize-se\' → preencha dados pessoais\\n3. Escolha o CNAE → confirme endereço comercial\\n4. Receba CNPJ em menos de 5 minutos\\n\\n**Obrigações mensais:**\\n- DAS: R$ 75,90/mês (INSS + ISS, valor 2026)\\n- DASN: declaração anual (prazo: 31 de maio)\\n\\n**3 erros comuns:**\\n1. Não emitir nota fiscal — obrigatória para pessoas jurídicas\\n2. Ultrapassar o limite anual sem trocar para ME\\n3. Esquecer de atualizar dados no CCMEI após mudança de endereço","tags":["mei","brasil","empreendedorismo","cnpj","tributação"],"dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","source":"Portal do Empreendedor — governo.br 2026","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"title":"Otimizador de Declaração do Imposto de Renda (IRPF)","domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Planejamento Fiscal","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","best_for":"Contribuintes brasileiros que precisam decidir entre declaração simplificada e completa e maximizar deduções legais","outcome":"Uma análise comparativa entre declaração simplificada e completa, com lista personalizada de deduções e alertas de malha fina.","inputs":[{"label":"renda tributável anual (salário + pró-labore + aluguéis, etc.)"},{"label":"despesas médicas totais pagas no ano (com recibos)"},{"label":"filhos ou dependentes (idades e relação)"},{"label":"contribuições à previdência privada (PGBL/VGBL) e oficial (INSS)"},{"label":"despesas com educação (escola, faculdade, cursos)"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"analysis","prompt":"Você é um contador especializado em IRPF (Imposto de Renda Pessoa Física) no Brasil, atualizado com as regras vigentes em 2025/2026.\\n\\nMinha situação fiscal:\\n- Renda tributável anual: R$ [renda tributável anual]\\n- Despesas médicas: R$ [despesas médicas totais pagas no ano]\\n- Dependentes: [filhos ou dependentes]\\n- Previdência privada (PGBL): R$ [contribuições à previdência privada]\\n- INSS recolhido: R$ [incluído nas contribuições]\\n- Despesas com educação: R$ [despesas com educação]\\n\\nRealice uma análise completa:\\n1. **Comparativo simplificado × completo** — qual resulta em menor imposto?\\n2. **Lista de deduções legais** que se aplicam ao meu perfil\\n3. **Limites de dedução** vigentes (médico, educação, PGBL)\\n4. **Alertas de malha fina** — o que pode chamar atenção da Receita?\\n5. **Documentos que devo guardar** por 5 anos\\n6. **Prazo e multa** por atraso na entrega\\n\\nResponda em português, com cálculos exemplificativos e linguagem acessível.","sample_output":"**Análise IRPF 2025 — Analista de TI, solteiro, SP**\\n\\n**Comparativo:**\\n| Modalidade | Base de cálculo | Imposto estimado |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| Simplificada (20% desc.) | R$ 72.000 | R$ 8.400 |\\n| Completa (deduções reais) | R$ 58.200 | R$ 6.100 |\\n→ **Recomendação: Declaração completa — economia de ~R$ 2.300**\\n\\n**Deduções aplicáveis:**\\n- Dependentes: R$ 2.275,08/filho (2 filhos = R$ 4.550)\\n- Despesas médicas: R$ 12.000 (dedução integral)\\n- Educação: R$ 3.561,50 (limite 2025)\\n- PGBL: R$ 4.800 (até 12% da renda tributável)\\n\\n**Alertas de malha fina:**\\n⚠️ Despesas médicas sem CPF do prestador — cruzamento automático\\n⚠️ Rendimentos de aluguel não declarados por inquilino\\n\\n**Documentos por 5 anos:**\\n- Recibos médicos com CPF/CNPJ\\n- Comprovantes de escola/faculdade\\n- Informes de rendimento do empregador","tags":["irpf","imposto de renda","brasil","finanças","deduções"],"dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","source":"Receita Federal do Brasil — tabela IRPF 2025","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"title":"Análise Fundamentalista de Ações na B3","domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Investimentos","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","best_for":"Investidores pessoas físicas no Brasil que querem analisar ações da B3 com base em fundamentos antes de investir","outcome":"Uma análise fundamentalista completa de uma ação, com avaliação de indicadores financeiros, riscos setoriais e comparação com pares.","inputs":[{"label":"ticker da ação (ex: PETR4, ITUB4, VALE3)"},{"label":"setor de atuação da empresa"},{"label":"seu horizonte de investimento (curto prazo <1 ano, médio 1-5 anos, longo >5 anos)"},{"label":"indicadores disponíveis: P/L, P/VP, ROE, dívida líquida/EBITDA (se souber)"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"25 min","output_kind":"analysis","prompt":"Você é um analista de investimentos especializado em Bolsa de Valores brasileira (B3), com amplo conhecimento em análise fundamentalista.\\n\\nAção analisada:\\n- Ticker: [ticker da ação]\\n- Setor: [setor de atuação da empresa]\\n- Horizonte: [seu horizonte de investimento]\\n- Indicadores conhecidos: [indicadores disponíveis]\\n\\nElabore uma análise fundamentalista estruturada:\\n1. **Perfil do negócio** — modelo de negócios, posicionamento competitivo, moat\\n2. **Análise dos indicadores** — interprete cada indicador fornecido e compare com a média do setor\\n3. **Principais riscos** — setoriais, macroeconômicos, regulatórios e específicos da empresa\\n4. **Catalisadores** — o que pode valorizar a ação no horizonte definido?\\n5. **Pontos de atenção** — red flags nos fundamentos\\n6. **Score fundamentalista simplificado** (1-10) com justificativa\\n7. **Próximas datas relevantes** — ex.: divulgação de resultados, pagamento de dividendos\\n\\n⚠️ Lembre-se: isso é uma análise educacional — não é recomendação de investimento. Sempre consulte um assessor certificado.\\n\\nResponda em português.","sample_output":"**Análise Fundamentalista — ITUB4 (Itaú Unibanco)**\\n\\n**Perfil:** Maior banco privado da América Latina por ativos, com forte presença no varejo e no corporate. Moat sólido: base de clientes de 60M+, custos de mudança elevados e escala regulatória.\\n\\n**Indicadores:**\\n| Indicador | ITUB4 | Média setor |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| P/L | 8,2× | 9,1× | Levemente descontado |\\n| P/VP | 1,8× | 2,0× | Em linha |\\n| ROE | 21% | 18% | Acima da média |\\n| Div. Líq./EBITDA | — | — | N/A para bancos |\\n\\n**Riscos:**\\n- Aumento da inadimplência em ciclos de juros altos\\n- Regulação do Banco Central sobre margens\\n- Fintechs (Nubank) pressionando margens no varejo jovem\\n\\n**Catalisadores:**\\n- Ciclo de queda de juros melhora carteira de crédito\\n- Expansão em seguros e wealth management\\n\\n**Score: 7,5/10** — fundamentos sólidos, valuation justo para longo prazo\\n\\n⚠️ *Análise educacional — não é recomendação de investimento*","tags":["b3","ações","brasil","investimentos","fundamentalista"],"dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"medium","last_verified":"2026-05-24","source":"CVM — Comissão de Valores Mobiliários","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"title":"Templates de Mensagens para WhatsApp Business","domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Marketing Digital","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","best_for":"Empreendedores e equipes de vendas no Brasil que usam WhatsApp Business para atendimento e vendas","outcome":"Um conjunto de templates de mensagens para WhatsApp Business cobrindo boas-vindas, follow-up, confirmação de pedido, cobrança e recuperação de carrinho abandonado.","inputs":[{"label":"tipo de negócio (ex: loja de roupas, clínica, restaurante, serviço de TI)"},{"label":"tom da marca (formal, descontraído, técnico)"},{"label":"produto ou serviço principal"},{"label":"nome da empresa e nome do atendente ou bot"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"10 min","output_kind":"templates","prompt":"Você é um especialista em marketing digital e vendas pelo WhatsApp Business no mercado brasileiro.\\n\\nMeu negócio:\\n- Tipo: [tipo de negócio]\\n- Tom: [tom da marca]\\n- Produto/serviço: [produto ou serviço principal]\\n- Empresa: [nome da empresa] | Atendente/Bot: [nome do atendente ou bot]\\n\\nCrie 8 templates de mensagens prontos para uso no WhatsApp Business, cobrindo:\\n1. **Boas-vindas** — primeiro contato do cliente\\n2. **Resposta fora do horário** — mensagem automática\\n3. **Confirmação de pedido/agendamento**\\n4. **Follow-up pós-compra** — satisfação do cliente\\n5. **Lembrete de pagamento** (cobrança amigável)\\n6. **Recuperação de carrinho abandonado**\\n7. **Promoção relâmpago** (urgência sem spam)\\n8. **Pesquisa de satisfação NPS** simples\\n\\nRegras:\\n- Cada template deve ter ≤ 160 caracteres para mensagens de texto simples\\n- Use emojis com moderação, respeitando o tom da marca\\n- Inclua variáveis entre {{chaves}} onde personalizável\\n- Adicione uma versão curta e uma versão completa para os templates mais importantes\\n\\nResponda em português do Brasil.","sample_output":"**Templates WhatsApp Business — Clínica de Estética Bella Vista**\\n\\n**1. Boas-vindas:**\\nOlá, {{nome}}! 😊 Seja bem-vindo(a) à Bella Vista. Sou a Mari, sua consultora. Como posso ajudar você hoje?\\n\\n**2. Fora do horário:**\\nOi! Recebemos sua mensagem. Nossa equipe atende de seg. a sáb., 9h–19h. Retornaremos em breve! 🌸\\n\\n**3. Confirmação de agendamento:**\\n✅ Agendamento confirmado!\\n📅 {{data}} às {{horário}}\\n💆 Serviço: {{procedimento}}\\n📍 Rua das Flores, 123 — Pinheiros\\nAté lá! 😍\\n\\n**4. Follow-up pós-atendimento:**\\nOlá, {{nome}}! Como foi seu procedimento de {{serviço}} conosco? Seu feedback é muito importante! ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐\\n\\n**5. Cobrança amigável:**\\nOi {{nome}}, tudo bem? 🙏 Passando para lembrar do pagamento referente a {{serviço}} no valor de R$ {{valor}}. Qualquer dúvida, estou aqui!","tags":["whatsapp","brasil","marketing","vendas","atendimento"],"dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","source":"Meta Business — WhatsApp Business API 2026","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","jasper"]},{"title":"Checklist de Conformidade LGPD para Pequenas Empresas","domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Conformidade Legal","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","best_for":"Gestores e empreendedores de PMEs brasileiras que precisam adequar seus negócios à Lei Geral de Proteção de Dados (LGPD)","outcome":"Um diagnóstico de conformidade LGPD personalizado com checklist priorizado, políticas-chave e próximos passos para PMEs.","inputs":[{"label":"porte da empresa (MEI, ME, EPP ou média empresa)"},{"label":"tipos de dados pessoais coletados (ex: nome, CPF, email, dados de saúde, dados financeiros)"},{"label":"como você coleta esses dados (formulário online, WhatsApp, sistema de CRM, papel)"},{"label":"você já tem Política de Privacidade publicada? (sim/não)"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"analysis","prompt":"Você é um especialista jurídico em LGPD (Lei Geral de Proteção de Dados — Lei 13.709/2018) no Brasil, com foco em adequação para pequenas e médias empresas.\\n\\nPerfil da empresa:\\n- Porte: [porte da empresa]\\n- Dados coletados: [tipos de dados pessoais coletados]\\n- Meios de coleta: [como você coleta esses dados]\\n- Política de Privacidade: [você já tem Política de Privacidade publicada]\\n\\nElabore um diagnóstico LGPD completo:\\n1. **Análise de risco** — quais dados coletados são sensíveis e exigem cuidados extras?\\n2. **Bases legais** — qual fundamento jurídico justifica cada tipo de tratamento?\\n3. **Checklist de conformidade** (priorizado: crítico → importante → recomendável)\\n4. **Documentos obrigatórios** que precisam ser criados ou atualizados\\n5. **Direitos dos titulares** — como responder a solicitações de acesso, exclusão e portabilidade\\n6. **Multas e riscos** — o que a ANPD pode aplicar para o meu porte\\n7. **Plano de ação em 90 dias** com tarefas sequenciais\\n\\nResponda em português, com linguagem clara e sem jargão jurídico desnecessário.","sample_output":"**Diagnóstico LGPD — Clínica Médica ME, São Paulo**\\n\\n**⚠️ Dados sensíveis detectados:** Dados de saúde (categoria especial) exigem consentimento específico e medidas de segurança reforçadas.\\n\\n**Bases legais aplicáveis:**\\n- Prestação do serviço médico: Execução de contrato\\n- Dados de saúde: Proteção da saúde (Art. 11, II, f)\\n- Marketing por WhatsApp: Consentimento (requer opt-in explícito)\\n\\n**Checklist Crítico (faça agora):**\\n- [ ] Publicar Política de Privacidade no site com link visível\\n- [ ] Nomear DPO (Encarregado) — pode ser o próprio sócio em PMEs\\n- [ ] Mapear todos os dados coletados e onde são armazenados\\n- [ ] Criar formulário de consentimento para coleta de dados de saúde\\n\\n**Plano 90 dias:**\\nSemanas 1-2: Mapeamento de dados\\nSemanas 3-4: Política de Privacidade + consentimento\\nMês 2: Treinamento da equipe\\nMês 3: Auditoria e ajustes\\n\\n**Multas ANPD:** Até 2% do faturamento, limitado a R$ 50M por infração","tags":["lgpd","brasil","privacidade","conformidade","pme"],"dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","source":"ANPD — Autoridade Nacional de Proteção de Dados 2026","related_tools":["perplexity","claude","elicit"]},{"title":"Gerador de Nota Fiscal de Serviço (NFS-e)","domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Gestão Fiscal","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","best_for":"Prestadores de serviços e MEIs brasileiros que precisam emitir NFS-e corretamente","outcome":"Um guia completo para emissão de NFS-e com os dados corretos, alíquotas de ISS por município e orientações para evitar erros comuns.","inputs":[{"label":"cidade/município onde você presta o serviço"},{"label":"descrição do serviço prestado"},{"label":"valor total do serviço (R$)"},{"label":"CNPJ ou CPF do tomador (cliente)"},{"label":"você é MEI, ME ou empresa de outro porte?"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"10 min","output_kind":"templates","prompt":"Você é um contador especializado em tributação de serviços no Brasil.\\n\\nInformações da nota:\\n- Município: [cidade/município onde você presta o serviço]\\n- Serviço: [descrição do serviço prestado]\\n- Valor: R$ [valor total do serviço]\\n- Tomador: [CNPJ ou CPF do tomador]\\n- Porte do prestador: [você é MEI, ME ou empresa de outro porte]\\n\\nForneça:\\n1. **Código de serviço LC 116** mais adequado para minha atividade\\n2. **Alíquota de ISS** vigente no município informado\\n3. **Campos obrigatórios da NFS-e** com valores corretos preenchidos\\n4. **Retenção na fonte** — o tomador deve reter ISS? (regra: tomador PJ em municípios com essa obrigação)\\n5. **Erros comuns** que geram rejeição automática no portal municipal\\n6. **Link para o portal NFS-e** do município informado (se disponível no PNDF — Padrão Nacional)\\n7. **Prazo para emissão** após a prestação do serviço\\n\\nResponda em português do Brasil.","sample_output":"**Guia NFS-e — Designer Gráfico MEI, São Paulo**\\n\\n**Código LC 116:** 17.06 — Propaganda e publicidade\\n\\n**ISS em São Paulo (2026):** 2% sobre o valor do serviço\\nValor do ISS nesta nota: R$ 100 × 2% = R$ 2,00\\n\\n**Campos obrigatórios:**\\n- Discriminação do serviço: \'Criação de identidade visual para marca XYZ, conforme briefing acordado\'\\n- Código do serviço: 17.06\\n- Alíquota: 2%\\n- Valor líquido: R$ 5.000\\n\\n**Retenção:** MEI não tem ISS retido — o imposto está incluído no DAS fixo mensal.\\n\\n**Erros comuns:**\\n- Descrição genérica (\'serviços prestados\') → use descrição técnica\\n- CNPJ do tomador com dígito errado → sistema rejeita automaticamente\\n\\n**Portal NFS-e SP:** nfse.prefeitura.sp.gov.br\\n**Prazo de emissão:** No ato da prestação ou até o último dia útil do mês","tags":["nfe","nota fiscal","brasil","iss","mei"],"dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","source":"Prefeituras brasileiras — Padrão Nacional NFS-e 2026","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"title":"Consultor de Direitos Trabalhistas CLT","domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Direito do Trabalho","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","best_for":"Trabalhadores brasileiros regidos pela CLT que têm dúvidas sobre seus direitos em situações específicas","outcome":"Uma análise clara dos direitos e obrigações trabalhistas em situações concretas, com referências à CLT e orientações sobre o que fazer.","inputs":[{"label":"descreva sua situação trabalhista (ex: demissão sem justa causa, horas extras não pagas, assédio, férias negadas)"},{"label":"tipo de contrato (CLT, terceirizado, PJ com vínculo, aprendiz)"},{"label":"tempo de empresa"},{"label":"estado (UF) — para normas coletivas estaduais"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"analysis","prompt":"Você é um advogado trabalhista especializado na CLT (Consolidação das Leis do Trabalho) e na Reforma Trabalhista de 2017, com conhecimento das decisões recentes do TST (Tribunal Superior do Trabalho).\\n\\nMinha situação:\\n- Situação: [descreva sua situação trabalhista]\\n- Contrato: [tipo de contrato]\\n- Tempo de empresa: [tempo de empresa]\\n- Estado: [estado (UF)]\\n\\nAnalise meu caso e forneça:\\n1. **Seus direitos** — o que a lei garante nessa situação?\\n2. **Artigos da CLT** aplicáveis (cite os artigos relevantes)\\n3. **O que o empregador pode e não pode fazer** legalmente\\n4. **Prazos** — há prescrição ou decadência?\\n5. **Passos práticos** — o que você deve fazer agora (registrar, notificar, buscar o sindicato)\\n6. **Quando acionar a Justiça do Trabalho** — avalie a viabilidade de ação\\n7. **Documentos que você deve guardar** como prova\\n\\n⚠️ Este é um guia educacional — não substitui consulta com advogado. Para seu caso específico, consulte um profissional habilitado.\\n\\nResponda em português do Brasil.","sample_output":"**Análise CLT — Demissão sem justa causa após 3 anos, SP**\\n\\n**Seus direitos:**\\n- Aviso prévio: 33 dias (30 dias + 3 dias por ano trabalhado)\\n- FGTS: saldo + multa de 40%\\n- Seguro-desemprego: 3 a 5 parcelas conforme histórico\\n- Férias proporcionais + 1/3 constitucional\\n- 13º salário proporcional\\n\\n**Artigos aplicáveis:** CLT Art. 477, 487, 496; FGTS Lei 8.036/90, Art. 18\\n\\n**O empregador não pode:**\\n- Descontar o aviso prévio se ele for dispensado pelo empregador\\n- Reter a CTPS por mais de 48h\\n- Condicionar pagamento de verbas à assinatura de qualquer documento\\n\\n**Prazo:** 2 anos para reclamar após demissão (prescrição trabalhista)\\n\\n**Passos imediatos:**\\n1. Exija homologação na DRT ou pelo sindicato\\n2. Guarde contracheques, cartão de ponto e e-mails\\n3. Confira os valores na calculadora da Receita Federal","tags":["clt","brasil","direitos trabalhistas","demissão","emprego"],"dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","source":"CLT — Consolidação das Leis do Trabalho, TST 2026","related_tools":["perplexity","claude","elicit"]},{"title":"Fluxo de Caixa para PME Brasileira","domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Gestão Financeira","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","best_for":"Donos e gestores financeiros de pequenas e médias empresas brasileiras que precisam estruturar ou melhorar o fluxo de caixa","outcome":"Um modelo de fluxo de caixa estruturado para 90 dias, com identificação de ciclo financeiro, sazonalidades e recomendações para melhorar a liquidez.","inputs":[{"label":"faturamento médio mensal (R$)"},{"label":"principais despesas fixas mensais (aluguel, folha, tributos)"},{"label":"prazo médio de recebimento dos clientes (dias)"},{"label":"prazo médio de pagamento aos fornecedores (dias)"},{"label":"setor de atuação e sazonalidade (ex: pico no Natal, queda em janeiro)"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"30 min","output_kind":"table","prompt":"Você é um consultor financeiro especializado em gestão de caixa para PMEs no Brasil, com expertise em capital de giro e ciclo financeiro.\\n\\nDados da empresa:\\n- Faturamento médio: R$ [faturamento médio mensal]/mês\\n- Despesas fixas: [principais despesas fixas mensais]\\n- Prazo de recebimento: [prazo médio de recebimento dos clientes] dias\\n- Prazo de pagamento: [prazo médio de pagamento aos fornecedores] dias\\n- Setor/sazonalidade: [setor de atuação e sazonalidade]\\n\\nElabore uma análise completa de fluxo de caixa:\\n1. **Ciclo financeiro** — calcule o ciclo de caixa (prazo médio de recebimento − prazo médio de pagamento)\\n2. **Necessidade de Capital de Giro (NCG)** — quanto dinheiro fica \'preso\' no ciclo?\\n3. **Projeção de fluxo 90 dias** — tabela mensal com entradas, saídas e saldo projetado\\n4. **Pontos críticos** — meses de maior pressão sobre o caixa\\n5. **5 ações práticas** para melhorar o ciclo financeiro\\n6. **Indicadores de alerta** — quando o caixa está em risco?\\n7. **Reserva de emergência recomendada** para o meu porte\\n\\nResponda em português, com tabela de fluxo e linguagem acessível.","sample_output":"**Análise de Fluxo de Caixa — Distribuidora de Alimentos, RS**\\n\\n**Ciclo financeiro:** 45 dias recebimento − 30 dias pagamento = **+15 dias** (capital de giro necessário)\\n\\n**Necessidade de Capital de Giro:**\\nR$ 80.000/mês ÷ 30 × 15 = **R$ 40.000 travados no ciclo**\\n\\n**Projeção 90 dias:**\\n| Mês | Entradas | Saídas | Saldo |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| Jul | R$ 78.000 | R$ 72.000 | R$ 6.000 |\\n| Ago | R$ 82.000 | R$ 74.000 | R$ 8.000 |\\n| Set | R$ 95.000 | R$ 78.000 | R$ 17.000 |\\n\\n**5 ações práticas:**\\n1. Negociar desconto para pagamento antecipado (2% para clientes que pagam em 15 dias)\\n2. Solicitar prazo de 45 dias com fornecedores estratégicos\\n3. Oferecer parcelamento via cartão para reduzir inadimplência\\n4. Usar antecipação de recebíveis em meses de pico de despesas\\n5. Criar conta separada para reserva operacional\\n\\n**Reserva recomendada:** 3 meses de despesas fixas = R$ 90.000","tags":["fluxo de caixa","pme","brasil","capital de giro","finanças"],"dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","source":"SEBRAE Brasil — Guia de Gestão Financeira para PMEs","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"title":"Pitch Deck para Investidores Brasileiros","domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Captação de Recursos","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🔵","best_for":"Fundadores de startups brasileiras que buscam captação de capital semente ou Série A com investidores locais como Redpoint, Valor Capital, Monashees ou angels da ABVCAP","outcome":"Um roteiro completo de pitch deck em 12 slides adaptado ao mercado brasileiro, com narrativa, métricas-chave e respostas às perguntas mais frequentes de investidores de VC brasileiro.","inputs":[{"label":"nome e descrição em uma frase da sua startup"},{"label":"problema que você resolve e tamanho do mercado endereçável no Brasil (TAM/SAM/SOM)"},{"label":"métricas atuais (MRR, crescimento MoM, churn, CAC, LTV)"},{"label":"quanto você está captando e para quê (runway desejado)"},{"label":"diferencial competitivo — por que você ganha no Brasil?"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"2 horas","output_kind":"deck","prompt":"Você é um advisor especializado em captação de venture capital no ecossistema de startups brasileiro, com experiência em deals com Redpoint eventures, Valor Capital, Monashees, Kaszek e angels da ABVCAP.\\n\\nMinha startup:\\n- Nome e missão: [nome e descrição em uma frase da sua startup]\\n- Problema e mercado: [problema que você resolve e tamanho do mercado endereçável no Brasil]\\n- Métricas: [métricas atuais]\\n- Captação: [quanto você está captando e para quê]\\n- Diferencial: [diferencial competitivo]\\n\\nCrie um roteiro completo para pitch deck de 12 slides, com:\\n\\n1. **Slide 1 — Abertura:** título, tagline de uma linha, logo\\n2. **Slide 2 — Problema:** quantifique a dor, mostre a ineficiência atual no contexto brasileiro\\n3. **Slide 3 — Solução:** proposta de valor clara, demo ou print do produto\\n4. **Slide 4 — Mercado (TAM/SAM/SOM):** metodologia bottom-up para o Brasil\\n5. **Slide 5 — Produto:** funcionalidades, diferencial de UX, roadmap de 12 meses\\n6. **Slide 6 — Tração:** métricas de crescimento, logo de clientes, NPS\\n7. **Slide 7 — Modelo de negócios:** receita, unit economics, payback\\n8. **Slide 8 — Competição:** mapa competitivo honesto, por que você ganha\\n9. **Slide 9 — Go-to-market:** canais de aquisição, CAC por canal, parceiros estratégicos\\n10. **Slide 10 — Time:** fundadores, advisors, gaps a preencher com o capital\\n11. **Slide 11 — Financeiro:** projeção 3 anos, premissas, milestones do fundraise\\n12. **Slide 12 — The Ask:** valor, uso dos recursos, valuation range, próximos passos\\n\\nPara cada slide: conteúdo sugerido + as 2 perguntas que investidores brasileiros SEMPRE fazem.\\n\\nResponda em português.","sample_output":"**Pitch Deck — FinTech de Crédito para PMEs**\\n\\n**Slide 1 — Abertura:**\\n\'Liberacred: crédito justo para os 17 milhões de MEIs e PMEs invisíveis para os grandes bancos\'\\n\\n**Slide 2 — Problema:**\\n- 65% dos MEIs recusados por bancos tradicionais\\n- Taxa média de crédito PME: 4,2% ao mês (vs. 0,8% para grandes empresas)\\n- 40% do PIB gerado por PMEs — mas <15% do crédito bancário vai para elas\\n→ Perguntas dos VCs: \'Qual o LTV do cliente que você atinge?\' / \'Como você mede o tamanho real do problema vs. os dados do BCB?\'\\n\\n**Slide 7 — Unit Economics:**\\n- CAC: R$ 180 (performance digital)\\n- LTV médio: R$ 2.400 (18 meses × ticket médio)\\n- LTV/CAC: 13×\\n- Payback: 4,2 meses\\n→ Perguntas: \'Como evolui o CAC com escala?\' / \'Qual o churn por safra de crédito?\'\\n\\n**Perguntas extras que investidores brasileiros fazem:**\\n- \'Qual o risco regulatório com o Banco Central?\'\\n- \'Por que você não vai ser esmagado pela conta PJ do Nubank?\'\\n- \'Como você consegue funding para os empréstimos além do equity?\'","tags":["startup","brasil","pitch","venture capital","captação"],"dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","source":"ABVCAP — Associação Brasileira de Private Equity e Venture Capital 2026","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Meeting Notes to Action Items","prompt":"Convert these meeting notes into a clean action item list.\\n\\nMeeting notes:\\n[paste your meeting notes]\\n\\nOutput:\\n- Bullet list of action items\\n- Owner for each item (if mentioned)\\n- Due date (if mentioned)\\n- Any open questions that need follow-up","tags":["meetings","productivity","action-items","quick"],"best_for":"Anyone who attends meetings and needs to extract next steps fast","outcome":"A clean, scannable action item list extracted from raw meeting notes in under a minute.","inputs":[{"label":"paste your meeting notes"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"2 min","output_kind":"plan","sample_output":"**Action Items — Product Sync May 24**\\n\\n- [ ] **Ana** — Share updated roadmap deck by Friday\\n- [ ] **Carlos** — Fix login bug before Thursday release\\n- [ ] **Team** — Review Q3 OKRs before next Monday\'s all-hands\\n- [ ] **Marketing** — Draft launch copy for Feature X by EOW\\n\\n**Open questions:**\\n- Who owns the dashboard redesign?\\n- What\'s the budget approval timeline for the new tool?","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notion-ai","otter-ai"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Rewrite This Email to Sound More Professional","prompt":"Rewrite this email to sound more professional and clear, without losing the original meaning. Keep it concise.\\n\\nOriginal email:\\n[paste your email draft]\\n\\nTone: [formal / friendly-professional / direct]\\nContext: [who you\'re writing to — e.g., a client, your manager, a new contact]","tags":["email","writing","professional","communication"],"best_for":"Anyone who wants their emails to make a better first impression","outcome":"A polished, professional version of your email that\'s cleaner and more effective.","inputs":[{"label":"paste your email draft"},{"label":"formal / friendly-professional / direct"},{"label":"who you\'re writing to"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"3 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Original:** hey mark just wanted to check in on the proposal thing, can you send it over when you get a chance? thanks\\n\\n**Rewritten (friendly-professional):**\\n\\nHi Mark,\\n\\nI wanted to follow up on the proposal — could you send it over when you have a moment? Happy to discuss any questions.\\n\\nThanks,\\n[Your name]","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","grammarly"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Write a Compelling Blog Introduction","prompt":"Write 3 alternative introductions (first paragraph only) for a blog post.\\n\\nTopic: [your blog post topic]\\nTarget audience: [who will read this]\\nMain argument or takeaway: [what the post is about]\\n\\nMake each intro use a different hook style:\\n1. Bold contrarian statement\\n2. Specific surprising statistic or fact\\n3. Short story or concrete scenario","tags":["blog","writing","intro","content"],"best_for":"Content creators and marketers who want a strong opening","outcome":"Three ready-to-use blog introductions, each using a different hook approach.","inputs":[{"label":"your blog post topic"},{"label":"who will read this"},{"label":"what the post is about"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"5 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Topic:** Why most team OKRs fail\\n\\n**1. Contrarian:**\\nOKRs don\'t fail because teams set bad goals. They fail because the entire ritual is designed to look productive rather than be productive.\\n\\n**2. Statistic:**\\nOnly 16% of knowledge workers say their OKRs helped them prioritize their daily work, according to a 2025 Lattice survey. The other 84% are writing them for their managers.\\n\\n**3. Story:**\\nLast quarter, Sofia\'s team hit every single OKR. They also shipped nothing their customers cared about. Here\'s what that taught them about goal-setting.","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","jasper"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"One-Line TLDR for Any Article","prompt":"Read this text and give me:\\n1. A one-sentence TLDR (under 20 words)\\n2. Three key points in bullet form\\n3. One question this article leaves unanswered\\n\\nText:\\n[paste the article or text]","tags":["reading","summary","research","quick"],"best_for":"Anyone who needs to triage long content fast","outcome":"A one-line TLDR, three key bullets, and one unanswered question — in under 30 seconds.","inputs":[{"label":"paste the article or text"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 min","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**TLDR:** Google\'s 2026 earnings beat expectations as Gemini API revenue grew 3× year-on-year.\\n\\n**Key points:**\\n- Gemini API now generates $4.2B annualised revenue, up from $1.4B in 2025\\n- Cloud division operating margin expanded to 32%, up 5pp\\n- Search ad revenue declined 3% as AI overviews reduce click-through rates\\n\\n**Open question:** How much of the Gemini API growth is internal (Google products) vs. external developer usage?","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Prioritize Your Task List by Impact and Effort","prompt":"Help me prioritize this task list using the impact/effort 2×2 matrix.\\n\\nMy tasks:\\n[paste your task list]\\n\\nFor each task, rate:\\n- Impact (1-3): how much does it move the needle?\\n- Effort (1-3): how much time/energy does it require?\\n\\nThen sort them into four quadrants:\\n- Quick wins (high impact, low effort) — DO FIRST\\n- Strategic (high impact, high effort) — SCHEDULE\\n- Fill-ins (low impact, low effort) — DO WHEN FREE\\n- Drop (low impact, high effort) — CONSIDER SKIPPING","tags":["productivity","prioritization","tasks","quick"],"best_for":"Anyone feeling overwhelmed by a long to-do list","outcome":"Your task list organized into four clear quadrants with a recommended do-first order.","inputs":[{"label":"paste your task list"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"3 min","output_kind":"table","sample_output":"**Task Prioritization — Impact/Effort Matrix**\\n\\n| Quadrant | Tasks |\\n|---|---|\\n| ⚡ Quick Wins | Reply to the Acme contract email, update README, cancel unused subscription |\\n| 📅 Strategic | Rebuild onboarding flow, write Q3 strategy doc |\\n| 💤 Fill-ins | Organize Notion archive, clean up Slack channels |\\n| ✂️ Drop | Rewrite legacy Python script nobody uses |\\n\\n**Do first today:** Reply to Acme contract email (15 min, high stakes, low effort)","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Turn Any Feedback into a Constructive Response","prompt":"Help me reframe this feedback I received so I can respond to it professionally and constructively.\\n\\nFeedback I received:\\n[paste the feedback]\\n\\nContext: [who gave it and in what setting — e.g., performance review, Slack message, client email]\\n\\nGive me:\\n1. What the person likely intended to communicate\\n2. The valid point inside the feedback (even if it felt harsh)\\n3. A draft response that acknowledges it without being defensive","tags":["feedback","communication","professional","mindset"],"best_for":"Anyone who wants to respond to difficult feedback without getting defensive","outcome":"A clear interpretation of the feedback and a professional, non-defensive draft response.","inputs":[{"label":"paste the feedback"},{"label":"who gave it and in what setting"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"5 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Feedback received:** \'Your presentation was a bit all over the place. It was hard to follow your argument.\'\\n\\n**What they likely meant:** The structure wasn\'t clear enough for the audience to track the logic from slide to slide.\\n\\n**The valid point:** The narrative thread was probably missing — each slide made sense individually but the through-line was unclear.\\n\\n**Draft response:**\\nThanks for the honest feedback — I appreciate it. I think you\'re right that the structure could have been clearer. I\'ll work on building a stronger narrative thread next time, probably by leading with the conclusion and working backwards. Happy to talk through what would have helped.","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Write a Resume Bullet That Shows Impact","prompt":"Rewrite this resume bullet point to show measurable impact using the format: [Action verb] + [what you did] + [result / number].\\n\\nOriginal bullet:\\n[paste your current resume bullet]\\n\\nContext: [what the role was and what team/company you were at]\\n\\nIf I don\'t have exact numbers, suggest 2-3 ways I could estimate or describe impact without fabricating data.","tags":["resume","career","impact","writing"],"best_for":"Job seekers who want resume bullets that get past ATS and impress hiring managers","outcome":"A polished, impact-first resume bullet with a result, plus tips if you lack exact metrics.","inputs":[{"label":"paste your current resume bullet"},{"label":"what the role was and what team/company"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"3 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Original:** Worked on improving the customer onboarding process\\n\\n**Rewritten options:**\\n\\n1. Redesigned customer onboarding flow, reducing time-to-first-value from 14 days to 4 days and increasing 30-day activation by 22%\\n2. Led cross-functional onboarding project that cut support tickets in first 30 days by approximately 35% (based on pre/post comparison)\\n3. Rebuilt onboarding documentation and in-app guidance for 2,000+ new customers per month\\n\\n**If you lack metrics:**\\n- Ask your manager or check your team\'s dashboards\\n- Use relative language: \'reduced by ~X%\' or \'eliminated\'\\n- Describe scale: \'serving 10,000 users\' or \'across 5 product lines\'","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Generate Team Icebreaker Questions","prompt":"Generate 10 icebreaker questions for a [type of meeting: e.g., remote team kickoff / workshop / onboarding session].\\n\\nTeam type: [e.g., engineering team, client workshop, mixed seniority]\\nTone: [light/fun / professional / thought-provoking]\\nTime available for icebreaker: [e.g., 5 minutes / 10 minutes]\\n\\nMix of:\\n- Quick-answer questions (can be answered in 5 seconds)\\n- Light professional questions (work-related but not boring)\\n- One deeper question (optional, for longer sessions)","tags":["team","icebreaker","meetings","remote"],"best_for":"Managers and facilitators running team meetings, workshops, or onboardings","outcome":"10 ready-to-use icebreaker questions tailored to your team type and tone.","inputs":[{"label":"type of meeting"},{"label":"team type"},{"label":"light/fun / professional / thought-provoking"},{"label":"time available"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"2 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Icebreakers — Engineering Team Kickoff (10 min, thought-provoking)**\\n\\nQuick (5-second answers):\\n1. Coffee or tea?\\n2. Dark mode or light mode?\\n3. What tab do you always have open?\\n\\nProfessional:\\n4. What\'s one tool or practice you discovered this year that actually stuck?\\n5. What\'s one thing you\'re hoping to learn in this project?\\n6. What\'s something you\'re still bad at that you want to improve?\\n\\nDeeper:\\n7. What\'s one assumption about software development you used to believe that you\'ve changed your mind on?","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Explain a Technical Error Message in Plain English","prompt":"Explain this error message in plain English and tell me how to fix it.\\n\\nError:\\n[paste the full error message or stack trace]\\n\\nContext:\\n- Language/framework: [e.g., Python, React, SQL, Docker]\\n- What I was trying to do: [describe what you were doing when it happened]\\n\\nGive me:\\n1. What the error means in simple terms\\n2. The most likely cause in my specific context\\n3. The fastest fix to try first\\n4. One thing to check if the fast fix doesn\'t work","tags":["debugging","error","developer","quick"],"best_for":"Developers and non-developers who need to understand and fix error messages fast","outcome":"A plain-English explanation of your error plus a step-by-step fix to try immediately.","inputs":[{"label":"paste the full error message or stack trace"},{"label":"language/framework"},{"label":"what you were trying to do"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT","cursor","github-copilot"],"est_time":"3 min","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Error:** `TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading \'map\')` (React, line 47)\\n\\n**What it means:** You\'re calling `.map()` on a variable that is `undefined` — JavaScript can\'t loop over something that doesn\'t exist yet.\\n\\n**Most likely cause:** Your data is fetched asynchronously and `items` is `undefined` on the first render before the API call returns.\\n\\n**Fastest fix:**\\n```jsx\\nconst items = data?.items ?? []; // default to empty array\\n```\\nOr add a loading check:\\n```jsx\\nif (!items) return <Spinner />;\\n```\\n\\n**If that doesn\'t fix it:** `console.log(data)` right before line 47 — you\'ll see exactly what shape it has.","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","cursor"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Simplify a Legal or Technical Clause","prompt":"Simplify this legal or technical clause into plain language that a non-expert can understand.\\n\\nClause:\\n[paste the clause or paragraph]\\n\\nTell me:\\n1. What it means in 1-2 plain sentences\\n2. What I am agreeing to or what it requires of me\\n3. Any potential risk or catch I should be aware of\\n\\nDo not give me legal advice — just help me understand the language.","tags":["legal","contracts","plain-language","quick"],"best_for":"Anyone who needs to understand a contract, terms of service, or policy clause","outcome":"A plain-English breakdown of the clause: what it means, what it requires, and any gotchas.","inputs":[{"label":"paste the clause or paragraph"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"2 min","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Clause:** \'The licensor reserves the right to modify, suspend, or terminate the service, or any portion thereof, at any time without notice, and shall not be liable for any resulting loss or damage.\'\\n\\n**What it means:** The company can change, pause, or shut down the service whenever they want, and they don\'t have to tell you first.\\n\\n**What it requires of you:** Nothing — this is one-sided. It only restricts what you can claim against them.\\n\\n**Potential catch:** If you\'re relying on this service for your business, you have no contractual protection if they disappear or change the product significantly. Check if there\'s an SLA or enterprise agreement available that provides uptime guarantees.","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Write 5 Subject Line Variants for an Email Campaign","prompt":"Write 5 subject line variants for this email campaign. Each should use a different copywriting approach.\\n\\nEmail topic: [describe what the email is about]\\nAudience: [who you\'re sending to]\\nGoal: [what you want them to do — open? click? reply?]\\n\\nApproaches to use:\\n1. Curiosity gap\\n2. Benefit-first (what\'s in it for them)\\n3. Urgency or scarcity\\n4. Personal / conversational\\n5. Question","tags":["email","marketing","subject-line","copywriting"],"best_for":"Email marketers and founders who want to A/B test subject lines","outcome":"5 ready-to-test subject lines using 5 different proven copywriting techniques.","inputs":[{"label":"what the email is about"},{"label":"who you\'re sending to"},{"label":"what you want them to do"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"5 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Email:** Product update email — new AI feature for enterprise customers\\n\\n1. **Curiosity gap:** The one Claude integration most enterprise teams haven\'t tried yet\\n2. **Benefit-first:** Cut your report review time by 60% — here\'s the feature that does it\\n3. **Urgency:** Early access closes Friday — your team\'s spot is reserved\\n4. **Conversational:** Quick question about your Q3 reporting workflow\\n5. **Question:** What if your team spent 3 hours less on reports every week?","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","jasper","copy-ai"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Write a Cover Letter Opening Paragraph","prompt":"Write 3 opening paragraph options for a cover letter.\\n\\nRole I\'m applying to: [job title and company]\\nMy background in one sentence: [your relevant background]\\nWhy I want this specific role: [your genuine reason]\\n\\nMake each opening use a different angle:\\n1. Lead with a specific result or achievement\\n2. Lead with a connection to the company\'s mission or product\\n3. Lead with a bold claim about what you\'d bring to the role\\n\\nKeep each paragraph to 3-4 sentences.","tags":["career","cover-letter","job-search","writing"],"best_for":"Job seekers who want a strong cover letter opening that gets them to the next round","outcome":"Three differentiated cover letter openings, each with a distinct strategy.","inputs":[{"label":"job title and company"},{"label":"your relevant background"},{"label":"your genuine reason for wanting this role"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"5 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Role:** Senior Product Manager at Linear\\n\\n**Option 1 (Achievement):** At my last company, I took a product from 3,000 to 50,000 monthly active users in 18 months by narrowing the value proposition and cutting three features. I want to bring that same bias for focus to Linear\'s developer tooling roadmap.\\n\\n**Option 2 (Mission):** Linear\'s bet that software teams deserve tools as fast as their thinking is one I\'ve believed in since I watched engineers close Linear tabs to open Jira. The speed-first philosophy is something I want to contribute to, not just use.\\n\\n**Option 3 (Bold claim):** I\'m the kind of PM who has an opinion about your changelog page, your pricing page, and why your \'New Issue\' keyboard shortcut isn\'t as fast as it could be. I\'d like to bring that level of product obsession to your team.","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Create a Negotiation Script for a Salary Conversation","prompt":"Help me write a negotiation script for a salary conversation.\\n\\nSituation: [e.g., new job offer, annual review, counter-offer]\\nCurrent offer / current salary: [amount or \'undisclosed\']\\nMy target: [what you\'re aiming for]\\nMy strongest argument: [why you deserve the increase — skills, market rate, results]\\n\\nGive me:\\n1. An opening line to anchor the conversation\\n2. How to respond if they say \'this is the best we can do\'\\n3. How to respond if they ask \'what are you currently making?\'\\n4. A closing line if I want to accept or ask for time to consider","tags":["salary","negotiation","career","scripts"],"best_for":"Anyone preparing for a salary negotiation who wants words, not just tips","outcome":"A ready-to-use negotiation script with lines for the most common pushbacks.","inputs":[{"label":"situation (new offer / review / counter-offer)"},{"label":"current offer or salary"},{"label":"your target number"},{"label":"your strongest argument"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"5 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Situation:** New job offer — $110K offered, targeting $125K\\n\\n**Opening anchor:**\\n\'I\'m really excited about this role and I\'d love to make it work. Based on my research on market rates for this role in this city and my seven years of experience in this domain, I was expecting a number closer to $125,000. Is there flexibility to get there?\'\\n\\n**If they say \'best we can do\':**\\n\'I appreciate the transparency. Are there other levers we could explore — additional equity, a signing bonus, or an earlier review cycle — that might bridge the gap?\'\\n\\n**If they ask current salary:**\\n\'I\'d prefer to focus on what the role requires and what I\'d bring to it — I\'m targeting $125K based on market data and the scope of this position.\'\\n\\n**Closing (if accepting):**\\n\'I appreciate you working through this with me. I\'m happy to accept at $125K and I\'m looking forward to contributing from day one.\'","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Instant Habit Tracker Design","prompt":"Help me design a simple habit tracking system I can start today.\\n\\nHabits I want to track: [list 3-5 habits]\\nMy schedule: [morning person or evening? how many minutes can I commit to tracking?]\\nPreferred format: [paper notebook / spreadsheet / phone app / Notion]\\n\\nGive me:\\n1. A minimal daily check-in format (should take under 2 minutes)\\n2. A weekly review question I can ask myself on Sundays\\n3. The single most common reason people quit habit trackers — and how to avoid it\\n4. A 30-day milestone I should aim for before changing anything","tags":["habits","productivity","health","self-improvement"],"best_for":"Anyone who wants to start tracking habits without over-engineering it","outcome":"A minimal, sustainable habit tracking system you can start using today.","inputs":[{"label":"list 3-5 habits"},{"label":"your schedule"},{"label":"preferred format"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"5 min","output_kind":"plan","sample_output":"**Habits:** Exercise 20 min, read 10 pages, no phone after 9pm\\n\\n**Daily check-in (Notion, 90 seconds):**\\n```\\nDate: __\\nExercise:  ☐ Done  ☐ Skip — reason: __\\nReading:   ☐ Done  ☐ Skip — reason: __\\nNo phone:  ☐ Done  ☐ Partial  ☐ Failed\\nOne word for today: __\\n```\\n\\n**Weekly review question (Sunday):** \'Which habit had the most skips this week, and was it a circumstance or a decision?\'\\n\\n**Why people quit:** They track too many things. Start with your 3, add nothing for 30 days.\\n\\n**30-day milestone:** Aim for 20/30 days completed on each habit (67%) — not perfection. At day 30, ask: which habit costs the most friction to start? That\'s the one to improve.","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notion-ai"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Turn a Wall of Text into a Skimmable Summary","prompt":"Reformat this wall of text into a skimmable, scannable document.\\n\\nOriginal text:\\n[paste your text]\\n\\nApply these formatting rules:\\n- Add a bolded headline every 3-4 sentences\\n- Break long sentences into shorter ones (under 20 words when possible)\\n- Convert any lists hidden in the prose into actual bullet points\\n- Add a one-line TL;DR at the top\\n- Preserve all the original information — just restructure it","tags":["writing","formatting","readability","documents"],"best_for":"Anyone who needs to make a dense document easier to read","outcome":"Your original text reformatted with headlines, bullets, and a TL;DR for fast scanning.","inputs":[{"label":"paste your text"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"2 min","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**TL;DR:** The new expense policy requires digital receipts and manager approval for all purchases over $50, effective June 1.\\n\\n**What\'s changing**\\nStarting June 1, all expense claims must include a digital receipt. Paper receipts will no longer be accepted in the reimbursement portal.\\n\\n**Approval requirements**\\n- Under $50: self-approve in Expensify\\n- $50–$500: manager approval required\\n- Over $500: finance + VP sign-off\\n\\n**How to submit**\\n- Upload receipts within 7 days of the expense\\n- Use the Expensify mobile app for same-day capture\\n- Tag each expense with your cost centre code","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Brand Strategy","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Brand Voice and Tone Guide","prompt":"Create a brand voice and tone guide for my company.\\n\\nCompany: [company name and what it does]\\nTarget audience: [who your customers are]\\nBrand personality in 3 words: [e.g., bold, human, precise]\\nCompetitors to sound different from: [name 1-2 competitors]\\n\\nInclude:\\n1. Voice pillars (3-4 core characteristics with a definition of each)\\n2. Tone spectrum — how voice shifts across contexts (e.g., social post vs. error message vs. sales email)\\n3. Do/don\'t word list (10 words we use, 10 we avoid)\\n4. 3 before/after examples rewriting generic copy in our voice\\n5. One-paragraph \'voice test\' to check any new content","tags":["brand","voice","copywriting","marketing"],"best_for":"Founders, marketers, and content leads building a consistent brand identity","outcome":"A practical brand voice guide your whole team can use to write consistently.","inputs":[{"label":"company name and what it does"},{"label":"who your customers are"},{"label":"brand personality in 3 words"},{"label":"1-2 competitors to differentiate from"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"45 min","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Brand Voice Guide — Volta (B2B SaaS for energy teams)**\\n\\n**Voice Pillars:**\\n1. **Precise** — We say exactly what we mean. No vague claims, no jargon for its own sake.\\n2. **Grounded** — We speak like a smart colleague, not a pitch deck. Real examples over abstractions.\\n3. **Understated confident** — We don\'t sell hard. We show, let the numbers speak, and trust our audience to get it.\\n\\n**Tone Spectrum:**\\n- Product UI: Direct, minimal (verb + object — \'Add meter\', not \'Start adding your meter now\')\\n- Blog: Conversational with data — short paragraphs, specific numbers\\n- Error messages: Honest + helpful (\'Your file format isn\'t supported. Try CSV or XLSX.\')\\n\\n**Do say:** specific, measurable, because, exactly, trade-off\\n**Don\'t say:** revolutionary, seamless, world-class, leverage, synergize","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","jasper"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Sales & Outreach","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Cold Email Sequence (3-Touch)","prompt":"Write a 3-email cold outreach sequence to [target persona] for [your product or service].\\n\\nProduct/service: [what you sell]\\nTarget: [job title and company type]\\nKey pain point: [main problem you solve]\\nProof point: [one specific result or case study]\\n\\nEmail 1 (Day 1): Problem-focused, short, single CTA\\nEmail 2 (Day 4): Social proof or case study angle, 25% shorter than email 1\\nEmail 3 (Day 9): Break-up email — give them an out, make it easy to say yes or no\\n\\nEach email: max 100 words, no feature lists, one CTA only.","tags":["cold-email","sales","outreach","copywriting"],"best_for":"Sales reps and founders doing outbound prospecting","outcome":"A 3-touch cold email sequence that feels human, avoids spam triggers, and gets replies.","inputs":[{"label":"what you sell"},{"label":"target job title and company type"},{"label":"main pain point you solve"},{"label":"one specific result or case study"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Sequence: AI analytics platform → Head of Data at mid-market SaaS**\\n\\n**Email 1 (Day 1) — Subject: Your dashboards vs. your decisions**\\nHi [Name], most BI dashboards tell you what happened. They rarely tell you what to do next.\\nWe help data teams at SaaS companies surface actionable signals — not just charts.\\nWorth 20 minutes to show you how [similar company] cut their reporting cycle by 40%?\\n[Calendly link]\\n\\n**Email 2 (Day 4) — Subject: How [Company X] reduced firefighting by half**\\n[Name], quick follow-up. [Company X]\'s data team was spending 60% of their time on ad hoc requests.\\nAfter six weeks with us, that dropped to 30%.\\nSame team, same tools — just smarter prioritization. Happy to show you the setup.","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","copy-ai"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"PR & Communications","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Product Launch Announcement","prompt":"Write a product launch announcement for [channel: press release / email to users / social post thread].\\n\\nProduct/feature: [what you\'re launching]\\nLaunch date: [date or \'today\']\\nTop 3 benefits for users: [not features — what users can do now that they couldn\'t before]\\nProof or credibility: [beta user results, awards, partnerships]\\nCTA: [what you want them to do: try, sign up, read more]\\n\\nFormat: [choose channel from above]\\nTone: [excited-but-grounded / formal / conversational]","tags":["launch","PR","announcement","marketing"],"best_for":"Product teams and marketers announcing new features or products","outcome":"A launch announcement in your chosen format that leads with benefits, not features.","inputs":[{"label":"product/feature being launched"},{"label":"launch date"},{"label":"top 3 user benefits"},{"label":"proof or credibility"},{"label":"CTA and channel"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Email to users — AI scheduling assistant launch**\\n\\nSubject: You asked for fewer calendar conflicts. Here\'s your answer.\\n\\nStarting today, your calendar syncs automatically.\\n\\nEvery time you mark a meeting as \'important\', your assistant learns your patterns and protects the time around it — so deep work blocks stop getting eaten by ad hoc requests.\\n\\nIn beta, 1,200 users recovered an average of 6 hours per week.\\n\\n**What\'s new:**\\n✓ Smart buffer time — 15-minute recovery blocks auto-added after back-to-backs\\n✓ Focus mode detection — your status updates automatically\\n✓ Calendar health score — see your week before it happens\\n\\n[Turn it on in Settings → Calendar Sync]","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","jasper"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Thought Leadership","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🔵","title":"LinkedIn Thought Leadership Post","prompt":"Write a high-performing LinkedIn thought leadership post.\\n\\nMy perspective or argument: [the contrarian or insightful take you want to share]\\nMy relevant experience: [what gives you credibility to say this]\\nAudience: [who follows you — industry, seniority]\\nOptional: a recent event or data point that makes this timely\\n\\nFormat rules:\\n- First line must stand alone as a hook (no preamble)\\n- Short paragraphs (1-3 lines)\\n- No bullet points until the last third if at all\\n- End with a question that invites comments\\n- 200-300 words","tags":["linkedin","thought-leadership","content","personal-brand"],"best_for":"Founders, executives, and practitioners building a professional personal brand","outcome":"A 200-300 word LinkedIn post with a scroll-stopping hook and a comment-driving close.","inputs":[{"label":"your perspective or argument"},{"label":"your relevant experience"},{"label":"target audience"},{"label":"optional timely event or data point"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"Most AI product launches are just feature dumps with a press release.\\n\\nI\'ve reviewed 40+ AI product launches in the past year as part of a VC due diligence process. The ones that converted were almost never the most technically impressive.\\n\\nThey had three things in common:\\n\\nThey led with a before/after story — not a capability list. They named a specific pain and then showed evidence it was gone.\\n\\nThey had a number that was easy to remember. Not \'47.3% improvement\'. Just \'half the time.\'\\n\\nThey made the first action stupidly easy. Not \'sign up\', not \'book a demo\'. \'Paste your first document.\'\\n\\nThe launches that flopped had one thing in common: they explained what the product does. The successful ones explained what your life is like after you use it.\\n\\nWhat\'s the most effective AI product announcement you\'ve seen recently — and why did it work?","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Technical Writing","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Rewrite Technical Documentation for Non-Technical Readers","prompt":"Rewrite this technical documentation so a non-technical business stakeholder can understand it.\\n\\nOriginal documentation:\\n[paste the technical documentation]\\n\\nAudience: [e.g., finance director, marketing manager, C-suite executive]\\nTheir main concern: [what they care about — cost? risk? timeline? business impact?]\\n\\nRules:\\n- No acronyms without explanation\\n- Replace every technical term with an analogy or plain description\\n- Lead with business impact, not technical details\\n- Keep the same structure but simplify the language\\n- Add a \'What this means for you\' section at the end","tags":["documentation","technical-writing","communication","stakeholders"],"best_for":"Engineers and product managers who need to communicate technical concepts to business stakeholders","outcome":"A business-readable version of your technical docs with a \'what this means for you\' summary.","inputs":[{"label":"paste the technical documentation"},{"label":"audience"},{"label":"their main concern"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Original:** \'The system uses a horizontally scalable microservices architecture with Redis caching and a PostgreSQL read replica for query optimization, achieving p99 latency of <200ms.\'\\n\\n**Rewritten for CFO:**\\nThe platform is built to handle 10× more users without any additional investment in infrastructure. Think of it like a restaurant that can seat 10 people or 100 — same kitchen, same quality, just more tables.\\n\\nWhen the system gets busy, it serves information from a fast local copy instead of doing all the work from scratch — the same way a barista keeps common orders ready at the counter.\\n\\nNinety-nine percent of requests complete in under 200 milliseconds (less than the blink of an eye).\\n\\n**What this means for you:** No performance-related surprises as we scale to new markets, and no need for a platform infrastructure upgrade in the next 18 months.","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","notion-ai"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Content Strategy","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Podcast Episode Outline and Show Notes","prompt":"Create a podcast episode outline and show notes for an interview episode.\\n\\nGuest: [guest name and 1-sentence bio]\\nTopic/angle: [what the episode is about]\\nKey question you want answered: [the one insight listeners should leave with]\\nAudience: [who listens to your podcast]\\nEpisode length: [e.g., 30 min / 60 min / 90 min]\\n\\nDeliver:\\n1. Episode title (3 options)\\n2. 5-minute structured outline with timing\\n3. 8-10 interview questions in order (mix of warm-up, substance, and provocation)\\n4. Show notes template (150 words, written for SEO and listener skimming)\\n5. 3 social media pull-quotes to tease the episode","tags":["podcast","content","interview","production"],"best_for":"Podcast hosts and content producers preparing interview episodes","outcome":"A complete episode package: title options, outline, questions, show notes, and social teasers.","inputs":[{"label":"guest name and bio"},{"label":"episode topic/angle"},{"label":"key insight you want"},{"label":"your audience"},{"label":"episode length"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"30 min","output_kind":"plan","sample_output":"**Guest:** Lena Richter, ex-Google PM, founder of Compass AI\\n**Topic:** Why most AI product teams are measuring the wrong things\\n\\n**Title options:**\\n1. \'The Metric That\'s Killing Your AI Product\'\\n2. \'What Google Taught Me About Measuring AI\'\\n3. \'Stop Tracking Accuracy — With Lena Richter\'\\n\\n**Outline (60 min):**\\n0:00 — Intro + guest background (5 min)\\n5:00 — The problem: how AI teams track success today (10 min)\\n15:00 — The Compass framework: what to measure instead (15 min)\\n30:00 — Real examples: what improved when teams changed metrics (10 min)\\n40:00 — Audience pushback + Lena\'s responses (10 min)\\n50:00 — One thing listeners can do this week (5 min)\\n55:00 — Closing + where to find Lena (5 min)","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","otter-ai"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"PR & Communications","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Press Release That Gets Picked Up","prompt":"Write a press release for [announcement].\\n\\nAnnouncement: [what you\'re announcing]\\nCompany: [company name, one-line description]\\nDate: [release date]\\nQuote from spokesperson: [give me a real quote or I\'ll draft one for you]\\nRelevant context or data: [any numbers, partnerships, or market context that makes it newsworthy]\\nTarget journalists/outlets: [tech press? business press? vertical media?]\\n\\nFormat: AP style, inverted pyramid, under 500 words.\\nInclude: dateline, headline, subheadline, boilerplate, contact info placeholder.","tags":["press-release","PR","media","communications"],"best_for":"PR professionals, founders, and comms teams pitching media","outcome":"A publication-ready press release in AP style with all standard elements.","inputs":[{"label":"announcement"},{"label":"company name and description"},{"label":"release date"},{"label":"spokesperson quote or ask to draft"},{"label":"data or market context"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE\\n\\n**Volta Energy Raises $40M Series B to Scale AI-Powered Grid Management Across Latin America**\\n\\n*Funding will accelerate deployment in Brazil and Colombia as demand for smart grid infrastructure surges*\\n\\nSÃO PAULO, May 24, 2026 — Volta Energy, the AI platform helping utilities reduce grid losses by up to 35%, today announced a $40 million Series B led by Redpoint eventures, with participation from IFC and Valor Capital Group.\\n\\nThe funding arrives as Brazil\'s National Electric Energy Agency (ANEEL) mandates smart metering for all utilities serving over 100,000 customers by 2028.\\n\\n\'Every percentage point of grid loss recovered goes directly back to lower consumer bills,\' said Maria Souza, Volta\'s CEO. \'This funding lets us scale what we\'ve proven in São Paulo across the entire country.\'\\n\\n###\\n\\n**About Volta Energy:** [Company boilerplate]\\n**Media Contact:** [Name, email, phone]","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Customer Success","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Customer Case Study from Raw Interview Notes","prompt":"Turn these customer interview notes into a polished case study.\\n\\nCustomer: [company name, industry, size]\\nChallenge (before): [what problem they had]\\nSolution: [what they used / did]\\nResults: [specific metrics and outcomes]\\nQuote from customer: [direct quote or paraphrase]\\n\\nFormat:\\n- Headline: result-first (e.g., \'How [Company] Cut X by Y%\')\\n- 3 sections: Challenge / Solution / Results\\n- Pull quote in the middle\\n- 300-400 words\\n- Sidebar: 3 key metrics in bold\\n\\nTone: credible and specific — no marketing hyperbole.","tags":["case-study","customer-success","marketing","proof"],"best_for":"Marketing and customer success teams turning wins into sales collateral","outcome":"A polished, credible case study with a results-first headline and a sidebar of key metrics.","inputs":[{"label":"customer name, industry, size"},{"label":"their challenge before"},{"label":"solution used"},{"label":"specific results and metrics"},{"label":"customer quote"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"30 min","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**How Meridian Health Reduced Patient No-Shows by 43%**\\n\\n**The Challenge**\\nMeridian Health\'s network of 12 clinics was losing $2.1 million annually to appointment no-shows. Their reminder system — a single SMS sent 24 hours before — wasn\'t working for patients with complex schedules or language barriers.\\n\\n**The Solution**\\nMeridian deployed an AI reminder system that sent personalized multi-channel reminders in the patient\'s preferred language, timed based on historical show-up patterns per patient segment.\\n\\n**The Results**\\nWithin 90 days, no-show rates dropped from 22% to 12.5% — a 43% reduction. Recovered appointment slots generated $890,000 in incremental revenue in the first quarter alone. Staff hours spent on manual reminder calls dropped by 70%.\\n\\n\'We tried everything — calls, SMS, even postcards,\' said Operations Director Priya Nair. \'The difference was personalization at scale. Patients actually showed up because the reminder felt like it was meant for them.\'\\n\\n| Metric | Result |\\n|---|---|\\n| No-show reduction | 43% |\\n| Incremental Q1 revenue | $890K |\\n| Staff time saved | 70% |","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Sales","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🔵","title":"Sales Deck Narrative Script","prompt":"Write the spoken narrative script for a sales presentation.\\n\\nProduct/service: [what you sell]\\nDeal context: [who you\'re presenting to — company, role, known pain points]\\nDeck structure: [list your slide titles or sections]\\nKey objection to pre-empt: [the objection you always hear]\\nDesired outcome: [what you want them to do after the meeting]\\n\\nFor each slide, write:\\n- What to say (2-4 sentences)\\n- What NOT to read from the slide\\n- One question to check understanding or create engagement\\n\\nTotal talking time: [e.g., 20 minutes]","tags":["sales","presentation","deck","storytelling"],"best_for":"Account executives and founders delivering high-stakes sales presentations","outcome":"A speaker-ready script for each slide with talk tracks, engagement questions, and objection pre-emption.","inputs":[{"label":"product/service"},{"label":"who you\'re presenting to"},{"label":"list your slide titles"},{"label":"key objection to pre-empt"},{"label":"total talking time"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT","gamma"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"deck","sample_output":"**Slide 3: The Problem**\\n\\n**Say:** \'Your team is making pricing decisions every day. Some of those decisions recover margin. A lot of them leave money on the table — and you probably don\'t know which ones. That\'s not a people problem. It\'s a visibility problem.\'\\n\\n**Don\'t read:** The bullet points on screen — let them read those while you talk.\\n\\n**Engagement question:** \'Before I go on — how does your team currently know when a discount was worth giving?\'\\n\\n---\\n**Slide 5: Objection Pre-emption**\\n\\n**Say:** \'I know what you\'re thinking — we already have Salesforce data for this. Here\'s the difference: Salesforce tells you what happened. We tell you what the discount did to LTV 6 months later, and whether giving it was worth it. That\'s a different question.\'","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","gamma"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Crisis Communications","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🔵","title":"Apology Email That Rebuilds Trust","prompt":"Write a genuine apology email that rebuilds trust after a service failure or mistake.\\n\\nWhat happened: [describe the issue or failure]\\nWho was affected: [customers, employees, partners?]\\nRoot cause (if known): [what actually caused it]\\nWhat you\'ve fixed or are fixing: [concrete actions taken]\\nWhat you\'re offering as remedy: [credit, refund, extra support, etc.]\\n\\nRules:\\n- No passive voice (\'mistakes were made\' → \'we made a mistake\')\\n- No \'we apologize for any inconvenience\' (cliché)\\n- Acknowledge the impact, not just the event\\n- Be specific about what changed\\n- Short sentences. No PR spin.","tags":["crisis","email","trust","customer-service"],"best_for":"Customer-facing teams, CEOs, and product managers handling service failures","outcome":"A sincere, specific apology email that takes accountability and offers a concrete remedy.","inputs":[{"label":"what happened"},{"label":"who was affected"},{"label":"root cause if known"},{"label":"what you\'ve fixed"},{"label":"what you\'re offering"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Subject: We let you down last Tuesday — here\'s what happened and what we changed**\\n\\nOn May 20th, our platform was down for 4 hours and 17 minutes. During that window, you couldn\'t access your data or run reports.\\n\\nThat\'s unacceptable. We know some of you had client meetings. Some of you had board reports due.\\n\\n**What caused it:** A database migration we ran at 2am UTC hit an edge case we hadn\'t tested. Our rollback took longer than it should have because our runbook for this scenario was out of date.\\n\\n**What we\'ve fixed:**\\n- Updated rollback runbook and tested it twice\\n- Added monitoring for the edge case that triggered the failure\\n- Moving all infrastructure changes to a 72-hour review window\\n\\n**What we\'re giving you:** 15 days of credit added to your account automatically.\\n\\nIf you were directly affected and want to talk through what happened, reply and I\'ll call you.\\n\\n— [Name], CEO","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Saúde","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Guia para Conseguir Consulta pelo SUS","prompt":"Você é um assistente especializado no Sistema Único de Saúde (SUS) brasileiro.\\n\\nMinha situação:\\n- Estado/município: [seu estado e cidade]\\n- Especialidade que preciso: [ex: cardiologista, ortopedista, psiquiatra]\\n- Urgência: [urgente / pode aguardar / rotina]\\n- Tenho UBS de referência? [sim/não]\\n\\nMe ajude com:\\n1. **Passo a passo** para agendar pelo SUS no meu município\\n2. **Documentos necessários** para levar na UBS\\n3. **Direito à prioridade** — tenho algum? (idoso, gestante, criança, deficiência)\\n4. **Tempo médio de espera** para essa especialidade no SUS\\n5. **O que fazer se a espera for muito longa** — alternativas gratuitas ou de baixo custo\\n6. **Consultas online gratuitas** disponíveis pelo SUS em 2026\\n\\nResponda em português do Brasil, linguagem simples.","tags":["sus","saúde","brasil","consulta"],"best_for":"Cidadãos brasileiros que precisam acessar serviços de saúde pelo SUS","outcome":"Um guia passo a passo para conseguir consulta médica pelo SUS, com documentação, direitos e alternativas.","inputs":[{"label":"seu estado e cidade"},{"label":"especialidade médica que precisa"},{"label":"urgente / pode aguardar / rotina"},{"label":"tem UBS de referência? sim/não"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"5 min","output_kind":"plan","sample_output":"**Guia SUS — Cardiologista, São Paulo, rotina**\\n\\n**Passo a passo:**\\n1. Vá à sua UBS de referência com RG, CPF e Cartão SUS\\n2. Solicite encaminhamento ao cardiologista\\n3. O médico da UBS emite guia de referência\\n4. Regulação CROSS agenda a consulta no especialista\\n5. Você recebe SMS/WhatsApp com data e local\\n\\n**Documentos:**\\n- RG ou CNH\\n- CPF\\n- Cartão Nacional de Saúde (ou solicite na UBS)\\n- Comprovante de residência (últimos 3 meses)\\n\\n**Direitos à prioridade:**\\n- Idosos +60 anos: atendimento preferencial\\n- Gestantes: fila prioritária para pré-natal\\n- Pessoas com deficiência: prioritário em todas as filas\\n\\n**Tempo médio SP:** 45–90 dias para cardiologia\\n\\n**Alternativas gratuitas:** Faculdades de medicina (USP, UNIFESP) atendem gratuitamente e têm filas menores","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Saúde","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Como Contestar Negativa do Plano de Saúde","prompt":"Você é um especialista em direito do consumidor e regulação de planos de saúde no Brasil (ANS).\\n\\nMinha situação:\\n- Procedimento/tratamento negado: [descreva o que foi negado]\\n- Meu plano: [operadora e tipo do plano — individual, coletivo empresarial, etc.]\\n- Motivo alegado pelo plano: [o que disseram na negativa]\\n- Médico solicitou? [sim/não — e qual especialidade]\\n\\nMe ajude com:\\n1. **Fundamento legal** — a negativa é legal? (ROL ANS 2026, RN 465/2021)\\n2. **Protocolo de recurso interno** ao plano — prazo e como fazer\\n3. **Reclamação na ANS** — passo a passo pelo app/site disque.ans.gov.br\\n4. **Ação no Procon ou Juizado Especial** — quando e como escalar\\n5. **Modelo de carta de contestação** para enviar ao plano\\n\\nResponda em português.","tags":["plano de saúde","ans","brasil","direitos"],"best_for":"Beneficiários de plano de saúde que tiveram procedimento negado","outcome":"Um guia completo para contestar negativa de plano de saúde, com fundamentos legais, recurso e modelo de carta.","inputs":[{"label":"procedimento ou tratamento negado"},{"label":"operadora e tipo do plano"},{"label":"motivo alegado pelo plano na negativa"},{"label":"médico solicitou? sim/não"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Análise: Negativa de Ressonância Magnética de Joelho**\\n\\n**Fundamento legal:**\\nRessonância magnética consta no ROL ANS 2026 como procedimento coberto. Negativa sem justificativa clínica válida viola a RN 465/2021, Art. 4º.\\n\\n**Passo 1 — Recurso interno (prazo: imediato):**\\nSolicite revisão por médico diferente do plano. Envie laudos médicos, relatório do especialista e exames anteriores. O plano tem 24h para procedimentos urgentes e 10 dias úteis para eletivos.\\n\\n**Passo 2 — ANS (se negado pelo plano):**\\n1. Acesse www.ans.gov.br ou app ANS\\n2. Abra NIP (Notificação de Intermediação Preliminar)\\n3. O plano tem 5 dias úteis para responder\\n\\n**Modelo de carta:**\\n\'Pela presente, contesto a negativa referente ao procedimento [RM de joelho], solicitado pelo Dr. [nome], CRM [número], em [data]. Tal procedimento consta no ROL de Procedimentos da ANS (Resolução Normativa 465/2021), sendo obrigatória a cobertura pelo plano de saúde...\'","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Saúde","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Verificador de Interações Medicamentosas","prompt":"Você é um assistente de saúde que ajuda a verificar possíveis interações medicamentosas. AVISO IMPORTANTE: esta é uma ferramenta educacional — sempre consulte seu médico ou farmacêutico antes de alterar qualquer medicação.\\n\\nMeus medicamentos atuais:\\n[liste todos os medicamentos que você toma, com doses se souber]\\n\\nCondições de saúde relevantes: [ex: hipertensão, diabetes, tireoide]\\nIdade: [sua idade]\\n\\nMe diga:\\n1. **Interações significativas** entre esses medicamentos (se houver)\\n2. **O que monitorar** — sintomas que podem indicar interação\\n3. **Horários de tomada** — há medicamentos que não devem ser tomados juntos?\\n4. **Alimentos ou suplementos** que podem interagir\\n5. **Perguntas para fazer ao meu médico** na próxima consulta\\n\\n⚠️ Lembre sempre: apenas um profissional de saúde pode recomendar ou alterar medicações.","tags":["medicamentos","saúde","interações","brasil"],"best_for":"Pacientes que tomam múltiplos medicamentos e querem se preparar para conversa com médico","outcome":"Um relatório educacional de possíveis interações medicamentosas e perguntas para levar ao médico.","inputs":[{"label":"liste todos os medicamentos que você toma"},{"label":"condições de saúde relevantes"},{"label":"sua idade"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"10 min","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**⚠️ Aviso: análise educacional — consulte sempre seu médico**\\n\\n**Medicamentos analisados:** Losartana 50mg, Metformina 850mg, Atorvastatina 20mg, AAS 100mg\\n\\n**Interações a conhecer:**\\n- AAS + Losartana: o ácido acetilsalicílico em doses altas pode reduzir levemente o efeito anti-hipertensivo. Em 100mg (baixa dose), o risco é mínimo.\\n- Atorvastatina: evitar suco de toranja (grapefruit) — pode aumentar a concentração do medicamento no sangue.\\n\\n**Horários recomendados:**\\n- Losartana: de manhã\\n- Metformina: com as refeições para reduzir desconforto gástrico\\n- Atorvastatina: à noite (fígado sintetiza colesterol preferencialmente à noite)\\n- AAS: com café da manhã\\n\\n**Perguntas para o médico:**\\n1. \'Preciso monitorar algum exame específico por causa dessa combinação?\'\\n2. \'Posso tomar anti-inflamatórios como ibuprofeno com esses medicamentos?\'","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"medium","last_verified":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Saúde","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Plano de Manejo de Doença Crônica","prompt":"Você é um assistente de saúde especializado em manejo de condições crônicas. Esta ferramenta é educacional e não substitui orientação médica.\\n\\nMinha condição: [ex: diabetes tipo 2, hipertensão, hipotireoidismo]\\nDiagnóstico há quanto tempo: [tempo]\\nMedicações atuais: [liste ou coloque \'não sei\']\\nMinha maior dificuldade: [ex: lembrar de tomar remédio, controlar alimentação, manter rotina]\\n\\nCrie um plano de manejo semanal que inclua:\\n1. **Rotina de monitoramento** — o que medir, quando e com que frequência\\n2. **Alertas** — quando ligar para o médico ou ir à UPA\\n3. **Aplicativos gratuitos** recomendados para monitoramento em 2026\\n4. **Dicas de alimentação** adaptadas para o Brasil (alimentos acessíveis, preço acessível)\\n5. **Checklist para consulta médica** — o que levar e perguntar\\n\\nResponda em português, com linguagem simples e prática.","tags":["doença crônica","saúde","brasil","monitoramento"],"best_for":"Brasileiros que convivem com doenças crônicas e querem melhorar o autocuidado","outcome":"Um plano semanal de manejo com rotina, alertas, apps gratuitos e checklist para consulta médica.","inputs":[{"label":"sua condição crônica"},{"label":"há quanto tempo tem o diagnóstico"},{"label":"medicações atuais ou \'não sei\'"},{"label":"sua maior dificuldade no manejo"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"plan","sample_output":"**Plano de Manejo — Diabetes Tipo 2**\\n\\n**Monitoramento diário:**\\n- Glicemia de jejum: em casa, todo dia antes do café\\n- Anotar no caderno ou app: valor, horário e o que comeu na noite anterior\\n- Pressão arterial: 3× por semana (manhã, em repouso)\\n\\n**Alertas — vá ao médico ou UPA imediatamente se:**\\n- Glicemia > 300 mg/dL com sintomas (visão turva, muita sede, confusão)\\n- Ferida no pé que não cicatriza em 3 dias\\n- Tontura ou sudorese intensa sem motivo\\n\\n**Apps gratuitos (2026):**\\n- MySugr (diabetes)\\n- Minha Pressão (hipertensão)\\n- Lembrar Remédio (alarmes)\\n\\n**Alimentação acessível:**\\n- Feijão + arroz integral: carboidrato de baixo índice glicêmico\\n- Ovo: proteína barata para saciar e estabilizar glicemia\\n- Folhas verdes: espinafre, couve, acelga — fibra que desacelera absorção","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"medium","last_verified":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Saúde","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Perguntas para Fazer na Emergência","prompt":"Você é um assistente de orientação em saúde. Esta ferramenta é educacional.\\n\\nSintomas atuais: [descreva os sintomas da pessoa]\\nIdade da pessoa: [idade]\\nCondições pré-existentes: [ex: hipertensa, diabética, ou \'nenhuma conhecida\']\\nLocalização: [cidade — para saber se UPA ou Pronto-Socorro é melhor]\\n\\nMe ajude com:\\n1. **Nível de urgência** — UPA / Pronto-Socorro / SAMU 192 / aguardar UBS?\\n2. **O que descrever ao médico** — lista de perguntas e informações a levar\\n3. **O que NÃO fazer** antes de ir à emergência\\n4. **Documentos para levar** (SUS ou convênio)\\n5. **Sinais de piora** que exigem chamar SAMU imediatamente\\n\\n⚠️ Em caso de dúvida sobre urgência, ligue 192 (SAMU) antes de ir.","tags":["emergência","saúde","sus","brasil"],"best_for":"Familiares e cuidadores que precisam decidir rapidamente o nível de cuidado médico","outcome":"Orientação de triagem de urgência com o que fazer, o que levar e quando chamar o SAMU.","inputs":[{"label":"descreva os sintomas"},{"label":"idade da pessoa"},{"label":"condições pré-existentes"},{"label":"cidade"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"3 min","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**⚠️ Em emergência real, ligue 192 (SAMU) antes de consultar qualquer app**\\n\\n**Sintomas:** Dor no peito + falta de ar, 58 anos, hipertensa\\n\\n**Nível de urgência: ALTO — vá ao Pronto-Socorro agora**\\nNão espere UBS. Dor no peito em hipertensa pode ser infarto ou embolia.\\n\\n**O que falar ao médico:**\\n- \'Dor iniciou há X minutos/horas\'\\n- \'Intensidade de 1-10: [número]\'\\n- \'Irradia para braço, mandíbula ou costas?\'\\n- \'Última medicação tomada: [nome e horário]\'\\n\\n**Não faça:**\\n- Não tome AAS por conta própria sem orientação\\n- Não dirija sozinha — peça carona ou chame SAMU\\n\\n**Documentos:**\\n- Cartão SUS ou carteirinha do plano\\n- Lista de medicamentos ou caixinha dos remédios\\n\\n**Chame SAMU se:** perda de consciência, confusão, lábios roxos, dor 8+/10","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"medium","last_verified":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Educação","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Plano de Estudos para o ENEM","prompt":"Você é um professor especializado em preparação para o ENEM.\\n\\nMinha situação:\\n- Data da prova: [mês e ano]\\n- Horas disponíveis por semana: [número]\\n- Matérias mais fracas: [liste as que você tem mais dificuldade]\\n- Matérias mais fortes: [liste as que vai melhor]\\n- Meta de nota: [sua meta no ENEM]\\n- Estudo sozinho ou cursinho? [sozinho/cursinho/combinado]\\n\\nCrie:\\n1. **Cronograma semanal** de estudos (distribuição por matéria)\\n2. **Prioridades** — quais temas têm mais peso no ENEM?\\n3. **Recursos gratuitos recomendados** (YouTube, Descomplica, Khan Academy, etc.)\\n4. **Estratégia para a redação** — como melhorar 50 pontos em 3 meses\\n5. **Simulados** — quando e como usar para medir progresso\\n6. **Rotina de revisão** espaçada para memorização eficiente\\n\\nResponda em português, prático e motivador.","tags":["enem","educação","brasil","estudos"],"best_for":"Estudantes brasileiros se preparando para o ENEM","outcome":"Um cronograma de estudos personalizado para o ENEM com prioridades, recursos gratuitos e estratégia de redação.","inputs":[{"label":"data da prova (mês e ano)"},{"label":"horas disponíveis por semana"},{"label":"matérias mais fracas"},{"label":"matérias mais fortes"},{"label":"meta de nota"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"plan","sample_output":"**Plano ENEM — 4 meses, 15h/semana, meta 750**\\n\\n**Cronograma semanal:**\\n- 2ª/4ª: Matemática (3h) — álgebra e geometria são 40% das questões\\n- 3ª/5ª: Ciências Humanas (3h) — maior peso em questões interdisciplinares\\n- 6ª: Redação (1h30) — um texto completo por semana\\n- Sábado: Simulado + revisão de erros (4h)\\n- Domingo: Ciências da Natureza (3h)\\n\\n**Prioridades por área:**\\n- Mat: funções, geometria, probabilidade (40% das questões)\\n- CH: Brasil República, geopolítica contemporânea\\n- CN: ecologia, genética, tabela periódica\\n\\n**Recursos gratuitos:**\\n- Redação: Redação Online (corrige com IA)\\n- Matemática: Ferretto Matemática (YouTube)\\n- Geral: Estratégia ENEM (gratuito online)\\n\\n**Meta mensal:** Gabaritar 1 simulado do INEP por mês","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Educação","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Estrutura de Redação para Vestibular","prompt":"Você é um professor de redação especializado em vestibulares brasileiros (ENEM, FUVEST, UNICAMP, VUNESP).\\n\\nTema da redação: [tema que você precisa escrever]\\nBanca: [ENEM / FUVEST / UNICAMP / outra]\\nTempo disponível: [minutos]\\nNível atual: [iniciante / já escrevo mas não sei estruturar / quero tirar acima de 800]\\n\\nMe ajude com:\\n1. **Análise do tema** — o que a banca quer? qual é a polêmica?\\n2. **Tese** — 2 opções de tese para este tema\\n3. **Estrutura parágrafo a parágrafo** (para 30 linhas)\\n4. **Repertório sociocultural** — 3 argumentos ou dados para usar\\n5. **Proposta de intervenção** (para ENEM) — completa com 5 elementos\\n6. **Conectivos e operadores argumentativos** que elevam a nota\\n\\nResponda em português.","tags":["redação","vestibular","enem","escrita"],"best_for":"Vestibulandos que precisam estruturar redações para vestibulares","outcome":"Uma estrutura completa de redação com tese, argumentos, repertório e proposta de intervenção para a banca escolhida.","inputs":[{"label":"tema da redação"},{"label":"banca (ENEM / FUVEST / outra)"},{"label":"minutos disponíveis"},{"label":"seu nível atual"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Tema: Desafios para a saúde mental na era digital — ENEM**\\n\\n**Análise:** A banca quer reflexão crítica sobre o impacto das redes sociais e conectividade permanente na saúde mental, com proposta que envolva Estado, família e escola.\\n\\n**Tese 1:** A exposição excessiva às redes sociais agrava a ansiedade e o isolamento, exigindo políticas de educação digital e acolhimento nas escolas.\\n\\n**Estrutura:**\\n- Parágrafo 1 (intro): contextualização + tese\\n- Parágrafo 2: argumento 1 + evidência\\n- Parágrafo 3: argumento 2 + contraexemplo refutado\\n- Parágrafo 4: proposta de intervenção\\n\\n**Proposta ENEM (5 elementos):**\\nO Ministério da Educação (agente) deve implementar disciplinas de saúde digital (ação) nas escolas públicas (meio), promovendo autocuidado e uso consciente das redes (finalidade), sob pena de suspensão de repasses ao MEC (efeito).","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Educação","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Roteiro de TCC — Do Zero à Estrutura","prompt":"Você é um orientador acadêmico especializado em TCCs (Trabalho de Conclusão de Curso) para graduação e pós-graduação no Brasil.\\n\\nMeu TCC:\\n- Área/curso: [ex: Administração, Direito, Enfermagem]\\n- Tema geral: [sobre o que quer escrever]\\n- Nível: [graduação / pós-graduação / MBA]\\n- Prazo de entrega: [data ou \'não definido\']\\n- Maior dificuldade: [ex: problema de pesquisa, metodologia, revisão bibliográfica]\\n\\nMe ajude a construir:\\n1. **Problema de pesquisa** — 3 versões de pergunta problema para o meu tema\\n2. **Objetivo geral e 3 objetivos específicos**\\n3. **Justificativa** — por que este tema é relevante?\\n4. **Metodologia adequada** — qualitativa/quantitativa/mista? Por quê?\\n5. **Estrutura de capítulos** completa com sugestão de páginas por seção\\n6. **Cronograma de execução** de 4 meses\\n7. **Bases de dados gratuitas** para revisão bibliográfica (SciELO, CAPES, Google Scholar)\\n\\nResponda em português.","tags":["tcc","acadêmico","brasil","pesquisa"],"best_for":"Estudantes de graduação e pós-graduação construindo o TCC","outcome":"Uma estrutura completa de TCC com problema de pesquisa, objetivos, metodologia, cronograma e fontes.","inputs":[{"label":"área e curso"},{"label":"tema geral do TCC"},{"label":"nível (graduação/pós)"},{"label":"prazo de entrega"},{"label":"maior dificuldade atual"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT","perplexity"],"est_time":"30 min","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**TCC — Administração, Gestão de Pessoas, Graduação**\\n\\n**Problema de pesquisa (opção 1):**\\n\'De que modo a implementação do trabalho remoto impacta o engajamento e a produtividade de colaboradores em empresas de médio porte do setor de serviços no Brasil?\'\\n\\n**Objetivo geral:** Analisar o impacto do teletrabalho no engajamento de colaboradores em empresas de serviços de médio porte no Brasil pós-pandemia.\\n\\n**Objetivos específicos:**\\n1. Mapear os modelos de trabalho remoto adotados pelas empresas estudadas\\n2. Identificar fatores que influenciam o engajamento no trabalho remoto\\n3. Propor diretrizes para gestores de RH otimizarem políticas de teletrabalho\\n\\n**Metodologia:** Mista — survey quantitativo (escala Likert) + entrevistas semiestruturadas qualitativas\\n\\n**Cronograma (4 meses):**\\n- Mês 1: Revisão bibliográfica\\n- Mês 2: Coleta de dados\\n- Mês 3: Análise e escrita dos capítulos\\n- Mês 4: Revisão, formatação ABNT e entrega","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Educação","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Explicar Tema de Escola para Pais Ajudarem os Filhos","prompt":"Você é um professor que explica temas escolares de forma simples para que pais possam ajudar os filhos nos estudos.\\n\\nTema da escola: [ex: frações, sistema solar, Revolução Industrial, fotossíntese]\\nAno/série do filho: [ex: 5º ano do fundamental, 1º ano do médio]\\nFilho tem dificuldade em: [o que especificamente não está entendendo]\\n\\nMe explique:\\n1. **O conceito em linguagem simples** (como se eu tivesse 10 anos)\\n2. **Uma analogia do dia a dia** para explicar ao meu filho\\n3. **Um exercício ou atividade prática** que posso fazer com ele em casa\\n4. **Os erros mais comuns** que crianças cometem neste tema\\n5. **Como saber se meu filho entendeu** — pergunta de teste simples\\n\\nResponda em português, prático e sem jargão pedagógico.","tags":["educação","pais","escola","brasil"],"best_for":"Pais brasileiros que querem ajudar os filhos nos estudos em casa","outcome":"Uma explicação simples do tema escolar com analogia, atividade prática e forma de testar o aprendizado.","inputs":[{"label":"tema da escola"},{"label":"ano/série do filho"},{"label":"o que o filho não está entendendo"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"5 min","output_kind":"plan","sample_output":"**Tema: Frações — 5º ano**\\n\\n**Explicação simples:**\\nFração é uma parte de algo inteiro. O número de baixo (denominador) diz em quantas partes você cortou. O número de cima (numerador) diz quantas partes você pegou.\\n\\n**Analogia — pizza:**\\n\'Imagine uma pizza cortada em 8 pedaços. Se você comer 3 pedaços, comeu 3/8 da pizza. O 8 embaixo = quantos pedaços no total. O 3 em cima = quantos você comeu.\'\\n\\n**Atividade prática:**\\nPegue uma barra de chocolate e corte em 6 partes iguais. Pergunte: \'Se você comer 2 partes, que fração da barra você comeu?\' (resposta: 2/6 ou 1/3)\\n\\n**Erros comuns:**\\n- Somar numerador e denominador juntos (2/3 + 1/3 = 3/6 — errado!)\\n- Esquecer de simplificar (2/6 = 1/3)\\n\\n**Teste:** Peça: \'Me mostra 3/4 de um copo de água.\'","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Educação","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Comparador de Cursinhos e Universidades","prompt":"Você é um conselheiro de educação especializado no sistema universitário brasileiro.\\n\\nMeu objetivo: [ex: medicina na USP, engenharia na UNICAMP, direito na FGV]\\nCidade onde posso estudar: [sua cidade ou se pode se mudar]\\nOrçamento mensal para educação: [valor ou \'sem renda — preciso de bolsa\']\\nAno que pretendo entrar: [ano]\\n\\nMe ajude a comparar e decidir:\\n1. **Opções de universidade** — pública vs. privada para o meu curso\\n2. **Notas de corte** no SISU e ENEM para minha meta (últimos 2 anos)\\n3. **Cursinhos recomendados** para minha cidade e orçamento\\n4. **ProUni e FIES** — me explique as regras e se me enquadro\\n5. **Cronograma de inscrições** — ENEM, SISU, vestibulares das federais em 2026/2027\\n6. **Custo real de estudar** em cada opção (mensalidade + moradia + material)\\n\\nResponda em português.","tags":["vestibular","universidade","brasil","educação"],"best_for":"Vestibulandos e pais decidindo entre universidades e cursinhos","outcome":"Uma comparação estruturada entre opções de universidade com notas de corte, financiamento e cronograma.","inputs":[{"label":"curso e universidade alvo"},{"label":"cidade onde pode estudar"},{"label":"orçamento mensal ou \'preciso de bolsa\'"},{"label":"ano que pretende entrar"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT","perplexity"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Objetivo: Medicina — São Paulo, 2027**\\n\\n**Opções públicas:**\\n- USP: nota de corte SISU ~800/1000 | gratuita | ~220 vagas\\n- UNIFESP: nota ~780 | gratuita | ~100 vagas\\n- FMUSP (concurso próprio): vestibular separado do ENEM\\n\\n**Privadas com ProUni:**\\n- Einstein (FMABC): R$8.000–12.000/mês | ProUni bolsa parcial (renda até 3SM)\\n- Anhembi Morumbi: R$6.500/mês | FIES disponível\\n\\n**ProUni — você se enquadra?**\\nRenda bruta familiar ≤ 1,5 salário mínimo per capita → bolsa integral\\nRenda ≤ 3 SM per capita → bolsa parcial 50%\\n\\n**Cronograma 2026/2027:**\\n- Ago 2026: Inscrição ENEM\\n- Nov 2026: Provas ENEM\\n- Jan 2027: SISU + ProUni\\n- Jan-Mar 2027: Vestibulares das federais\\n\\n**Cursinhos SP (orçamento médio):**\\n- Poliedro, Objetivo, Anglo (R$1.200-2.500/mês)\\n- Gratuitos: cursinho pré-vestibular comunitário da USP (seleção por renda)","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"medium","last_verified":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","perplexity"]},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Direito","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Revisão de Contrato de Aluguel","prompt":"Você é um especialista em direito imobiliário e Lei do Inquilinato (Lei 8.245/91) no Brasil.\\n\\nMinha situação:\\n- Tipo de contrato: [residencial / comercial]\\n- Prazo do contrato: [meses]\\n- Valor do aluguel e índice de reajuste: [ex: R$2.000, reajuste IGPM]\\n- Garantia pedida: [caução / fiador / seguro-fiança / título de capitalização]\\n- Cláusulas que me preocupam: [descreva ou cole as cláusulas]\\n\\nAnalise:\\n1. **Cláusulas abusivas** — o que vai contra a Lei do Inquilinato?\\n2. **Reajuste** — IGPM, IPCA ou INPC? qual é mais favorável ao inquilino?\\n3. **Caução** — quanto posso ser cobrado no máximo?\\n4. **Saída antes do prazo** — quais são as penalidades legais?\\n5. **Quem paga o quê** — IPTU, condomínio, reformas: o que a lei determina?\\n6. **3 pontos para negociar antes de assinar**\\n\\n⚠️ Análise educacional — consulte um advogado para o seu caso específico.\\n\\nResponda em português.","tags":["aluguel","brasil","contratos","imóveis"],"best_for":"Inquilinos e locatários brasileiros que querem entender o contrato antes de assinar","outcome":"Uma análise das cláusulas do contrato de aluguel com identificação de pontos abusivos e sugestões de negociação.","inputs":[{"label":"tipo de contrato (residencial/comercial)"},{"label":"prazo e valores"},{"label":"garantia pedida"},{"label":"cláusulas que preocupam"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Análise — Contrato Residencial, 30 meses, São Paulo**\\n\\n**Cláusulas potencialmente abusivas:**\\n- Proibição de animais domésticos: só é válida se houver justificativa; decisões recentes do STJ protegem o direito à posse de animais\\n- Multa por rescisão de 3 aluguéis após 12 meses: abusiva — a lei limita à proporcionalidade do prazo cumprido\\n\\n**Sobre o reajuste:**\\n- IGPM em 2024 chegou a 7,6%, IPCA foi 4,9%\\n- Tente negociar IPCA — mais previsível e favorável ao inquilino\\n- Contrato deve especificar claramente o índice\\n\\n**Caução máximo:** 3 aluguéis (Lei 8.245/91, Art. 38) — se pedirem mais, é ilegal\\n\\n**3 pontos para negociar:**\\n1. Índice de reajuste: IGPM → IPCA\\n2. Prazo de carência para reforma antes da mudança\\n3. Quem paga IPTU proporcional se sair antes do fim do ano","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Direito","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Guia de Divórcio Amigável no Brasil","prompt":"Você é um consultor jurídico especializado em direito de família no Brasil (Código Civil, Lei do Divórcio, Provimento CNJ 83/2019).\\n\\nMinha situação:\\n- Casados há: [tempo de casamento]\\n- Regime de bens: [comunhão parcial / separação total / comunhão universal]\\n- Filhos menores: [sim/não — se sim, quantos e idades]\\n- Bens principais: [imóvel, carro, investimentos, dívidas]\\n- Ambos concordam com o divórcio? [sim/não]\\n\\nElabore um guia com:\\n1. **Divórcio extrajudicial ou judicial** — qual é o meu caso?\\n2. **Documentos necessários** completa lista\\n3. **Divisão de bens** — como funciona no meu regime?\\n4. **Guarda e alimentos** — o que a lei determina se há filhos\\n5. **Passo a passo no Cartório** — se for extrajudicial\\n6. **Custo médio** — cartório, advogado, imposto\\n7. **Prazo estimado** de início ao fim\\n\\n⚠️ Consulte sempre um advogado de família — este guia é educacional.\\n\\nResponda em português.","tags":["divórcio","família","brasil","direito"],"best_for":"Casais brasileiros buscando orientação inicial sobre divórcio consensual","outcome":"Um guia educacional completo do processo de divórcio amigável no Brasil com documentos, custos e prazos.","inputs":[{"label":"tempo de casamento"},{"label":"regime de bens"},{"label":"filhos menores? quantos?"},{"label":"bens principais"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"plan","sample_output":"**Divórcio Amigável — Comunhão Parcial, sem filhos menores**\\n\\n**Via extrajudicial (cartório) — seu caso se enquadra:**\\nSem filhos menores + ambos de acordo = pode fazer em cartório sem precisar de juiz.\\n\\n**Documentos:**\\n- RG e CPF de ambos\\n- Certidão de casamento original\\n- Escritura ou matrícula dos bens a partilhar\\n- Comprovante de residência de cada um\\n- Certidão de nascimento dos filhos (se houver filhos maiores que precisam ser mencionados)\\n\\n**Divisão de bens (Comunhão Parcial):**\\n- Divide-se o que foi adquirido DURANTE o casamento\\n- O que cada um tinha antes fica com quem já era dono\\n- Dívidas contraídas juntos também são divididas\\n\\n**Custo médio SP 2026:**\\n- Cartório: R$1.200–2.500 (tabela TCESP)\\n- Advogado (obrigatório mesmo no extrajudicial): R$1.500–4.000\\n\\n**Prazo:** 15–45 dias (extrajudicial)","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Direito","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Reclamação no Procon — Passo a Passo","prompt":"Você é um especialista em direito do consumidor no Brasil (CDC — Lei 8.078/90).\\n\\nMeu problema:\\n- Empresa: [nome da empresa]\\n- O que aconteceu: [descreva o problema]\\n- Tentei resolver diretamente com a empresa? [sim/não — se sim, quando e o que responderam]\\n- Valor envolvido: [R$ valor ou \'não é financeiro\']\\n- Estado: [seu estado]\\n\\nMe ajude com:\\n1. **Seus direitos no CDC** que se aplicam ao meu caso\\n2. **Prazo para reclamar** — quando prescreve?\\n3. **Passo a passo Procon online** (consumidor.gov.br)\\n4. **Prazo de resposta da empresa** após reclamação\\n5. **Se Procon não resolver** — ANATEL, ANAC, ANEEL, Juizado Especial?\\n6. **Modelo de texto** para a reclamação (objetivo, sem emoção, com fatos e datas)\\n\\nResponda em português.","tags":["procon","consumidor","brasil","direitos"],"best_for":"Consumidores brasileiros que tiveram seus direitos desrespeitados e querem saber como agir","outcome":"Um guia completo para registrar reclamação no Procon com modelo de texto, prazos e escalada se necessário.","inputs":[{"label":"nome da empresa"},{"label":"descrição do problema"},{"label":"já tentou resolver com a empresa? quando?"},{"label":"valor envolvido"},{"label":"seu estado"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"10 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Análise — Cobrança indevida em fatura de celular, São Paulo**\\n\\n**Seus direitos (CDC):**\\n- Art. 42: cobranças indevidas devem ser devolvidas em dobro\\n- Art. 6º: direito à informação clara e correção imediata de erros\\n\\n**Prazo para reclamar:** 5 anos a partir da cobrança (Art. 27 CDC)\\n\\n**Passo a passo consumidor.gov.br:**\\n1. Acesse consumidor.gov.br\\n2. Busque a empresa pelo CNPJ ou nome\\n3. Descreva o problema em até 2.000 caracteres\\n4. Anexe prints, nota fiscal ou boleto\\n5. A empresa tem 10 dias úteis para responder\\n\\n**Modelo de reclamação:**\\n\'Em [data], recebi cobrança de R$[valor] referente a [serviço] que não contratei / já cancelei em [data]. Entrei em contato pelo telefone [número] em [data] e recebi protocolo [número]. Até a presente data, não houve solução. Solicito devolução em dobro conforme Art. 42 do CDC.\'\\n\\n**Escalar para:** ANATEL se for operadora de telefonia (anatel.gov.br)","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Direito","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Modelo de Procuração Simples","prompt":"Você é um advogado que explica documentos legais em linguagem simples para cidadãos brasileiros.\\n\\nO que preciso autorizar: [o que a pessoa com a procuração vai poder fazer]\\nQuem vai receber a procuração (outorgado): [nome completo, CPF e endereço]\\nQuem está dando (outorgante): [seu nome completo, CPF e endereço]\\nPrazo de validade: [data de vencimento ou \'sem prazo definido\']\\nPrecisa de reconhecimento de firma? [sim/não/não sei]\\n\\nMe forneça:\\n1. **Modelo de procuração** completo preenchido com meus dados\\n2. **Como reconhecer firma** — precisa ou não para este caso?\\n3. **Onde registrar** se necessário\\n4. **Cuidados** — o que não devo esquecer de incluir para ser válida\\n5. **Como revogar** se precisar cancelar depois\\n\\n⚠️ Para procurações que envolvem imóveis, herança ou negócios de grande valor, consulte um advogado.\\n\\nResponda em português.","tags":["procuração","documentos","brasil","legal"],"best_for":"Cidadãos brasileiros que precisam delegar poderes a outra pessoa para atos específicos","outcome":"Um modelo de procuração preenchido com seus dados, instruções de reconhecimento de firma e como revogar.","inputs":[{"label":"o que a procuração autoriza fazer"},{"label":"dados do outorgado (nome, CPF)"},{"label":"seus dados (outorgante: nome, CPF)"},{"label":"prazo de validade"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"10 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**PROCURAÇÃO PARTICULAR**\\n\\nPelo presente instrumento particular de procuração,\\n\\nEu, **[SEU NOME COMPLETO]**, brasileiro(a), [estado civil], [profissão], portador(a) do RG nº [número], inscrito(a) no CPF sob o nº [CPF], residente e domiciliado(a) na [endereço completo], nomeio e constituo como meu(minha) bastante procurador(a),\\n\\n**[NOME DO OUTORGADO]**, brasileiro(a), portador(a) do CPF nº [CPF], residente em [endereço],\\n\\na quem confiro poderes para: **[descreva exatamente o que a pessoa pode fazer]**.\\n\\nA presente procuração terá validade até [data] / por prazo indeterminado.\\n\\n[Cidade], [data].\\n\\n____________________________\\n[SEU NOME] — Outorgante\\n\\n**Reconhecimento de firma:**\\nPara bancos, cartórios e DETRAN: sim, necessário. Para uso pessoal simples: geralmente não. Custo: ~R$15-30 em cartório.\\n\\n**Para revogar:** Basta escrever um \'instrumento de revogação\' e notificar o outorgado.","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Direito","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Guia do Juizado Especial Cível (Pequenas Causas)","prompt":"Você é um especialista em acesso à justiça no Brasil, com foco nos Juizados Especiais Cíveis (Lei 9.099/95).\\n\\nMeu caso:\\n- Problema: [descreva o conflito]\\n- Valor envolvido: [R$ valor]\\n- Réu (quem você vai acionar): [empresa / pessoa física / condomínio]\\n- Já tentou resolver sem processo? [sim/não]\\n- Estado: [seu estado]\\n\\nMe ajude com:\\n1. **Meu caso cabe no Juizado Especial?** (limite de 40 salários mínimos, 2026 = até R$56.000)\\n2. **Preciso de advogado?** (causas até 20 SM não precisam)\\n3. **Como dar entrada** — presencialmente ou online (e-JEC)\\n4. **O que levar** na audiência de conciliação\\n5. **Prazo para sentença** — quanto tempo demora?\\n6. **Como elaborar a petição inicial** de forma simples\\n\\nResponda em português.","tags":["juizado especial","brasil","justiça","direitos"],"best_for":"Cidadãos brasileiros que querem processar por conta própria em causas de pequeno valor","outcome":"Um guia prático para entrar com ação no Juizado Especial sem advogado, com modelo de petição e lista de documentos.","inputs":[{"label":"descrição do conflito"},{"label":"valor envolvido"},{"label":"quem vai ser acionado"},{"label":"já tentou resolver sem processo?"},{"label":"seu estado"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"plan","sample_output":"**Análise — Cobrança indevida de seguro em financiamento, R$1.800**\\n\\n**Seu caso cabe?** Sim — R$1.800 está muito abaixo do limite de R$56.000 (40 SM em 2026)\\n\\n**Precisa de advogado?** Não — abaixo de R$14.000 (20 SM) você pode se representar\\n\\n**Como dar entrada:**\\n1. Acesse o portal do TJSP (ou do seu estado)\\n2. Busque \'e-JEC\' ou \'Peticionamento Eletrônico\'\\n3. Preencha formulário: seu nome, CPF, o que aconteceu, o que você quer\\n4. Anexe documentos: contrato, extratos, print de e-mails, protocolo de reclamações\\n\\n**Modelo de petição simples:**\\n\'O requerente [nome], CPF [número], vem propor ação de repetição de indébito em dobro contra [banco], CNPJ [número], pelos seguintes fatos: Em [data], foram cobrados R$1.800 referentes a seguro não contratado (cláusula abusiva — Art. 42 CDC). O requerente solicita devolução em dobro = R$3.600 + danos morais no valor de R$2.000.\'\\n\\n**Prazo médio:** 3-6 meses até sentença (varia por estado)","dateAdded":"2026-05-24","region":"brazil","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-24","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Testing & Quality","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Write Unit Tests","prompt":"Generate a comprehensive unit test suite for the following function.\\n\\nFunction code:\\n[paste your function here]\\n\\nLanguage/framework: [e.g., Python/pytest, JavaScript/Jest, Go/testing]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Write tests for the happy path (expected inputs and outputs)\\n2. Write tests for all edge cases (empty input, null, boundary values, large input)\\n3. Write tests for expected error/exception cases\\n4. Use descriptive test names that explain what is being tested\\n5. Add a brief comment above each test group explaining the scenario\\n6. Follow AAA structure (Arrange, Act, Assert)\\n7. Achieve at least 90% branch coverage\\n\\nOutput: A complete, runnable test file I can copy directly into my project.","tags":["testing","unit-tests","tdd","quality","automation"],"best_for":"Developers who write code before tests or need to backfill test coverage quickly","outcome":"A complete runnable test file with happy-path, edge-case, and error tests covering 90%+ of branches.","inputs":[{"label":"paste your function here"},{"label":"language and test framework (e.g., Python/pytest)"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT","GitHub Copilot"],"est_time":"5 min","output_kind":"code","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","github-copilot"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Code Review","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Code Review Checklist","prompt":"Perform a thorough code review of the following diff/PR. Act as a senior engineer who cares about correctness, maintainability, and security.\\n\\nCode to review:\\n[paste diff or code here]\\n\\nContext: [brief description of what this change is supposed to do]\\n\\nReview it against this checklist and flag any issues:\\n1. Correctness — does the logic do what it claims? Any off-by-one errors, wrong conditions, missed branches?\\n2. Security — SQL injection, XSS, hardcoded secrets, improper auth checks, unvalidated input\\n3. Performance — unnecessary loops, N+1 queries, missing indexes, excessive memory use\\n4. Readability — unclear naming, missing comments on non-obvious logic, overly complex expressions\\n5. Error handling — unhandled exceptions, swallowed errors, unhelpful error messages\\n6. Tests — are new paths covered? Are existing tests still valid?\\n7. Breaking changes — API contract changes, schema migrations, dependency upgrades\\n\\nFor each issue found: state the line/section, the problem, the risk level (High/Medium/Low), and a concrete fix suggestion.","tags":["code-review","pull-request","quality","security","best-practices"],"best_for":"Tech leads and senior engineers who review PRs, or developers who want a self-review before submitting","outcome":"A structured review report with categorized issues, risk levels, and actionable fix suggestions.","inputs":[{"label":"paste diff or code here"},{"label":"brief description of what this change is supposed to do"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"10 min","output_kind":"analysis","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Debugging","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Debug This Error","prompt":"Help me debug the following error. I need to understand the root cause and fix it.\\n\\nError message:\\n[paste the full error message here]\\n\\nStack trace:\\n[paste the full stack trace here]\\n\\nRelevant code:\\n[paste the function or file where the error occurs]\\n\\nWhat I already tried:\\n[describe any fixes you already attempted]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Explain what this error means in plain English\\n2. Identify the most likely root cause based on the stack trace and code\\n3. List up to 3 possible causes ranked by likelihood\\n4. Provide a concrete code fix for the most likely cause\\n5. Suggest how to prevent this class of error in the future\\n6. Recommend any logging or assertions I should add to catch this faster next time","tags":["debugging","error-handling","stack-trace","troubleshooting"],"best_for":"Developers stuck on an error and want systematic root-cause analysis rather than trial-and-error","outcome":"Plain-English explanation of the error, ranked root causes, a concrete code fix, and prevention tips.","inputs":[{"label":"paste the full error message here"},{"label":"paste the full stack trace here"},{"label":"paste the function or file where the error occurs"},{"label":"describe any fixes you already attempted"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT","GitHub Copilot"],"est_time":"5 min","output_kind":"analysis","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt","github-copilot"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"API Design","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Design a REST API","prompt":"Design a RESTful API for the following use case.\\n\\nProduct/feature description: [describe what the product or feature does]\\nTarget consumers: [who will call this API — mobile app, web frontend, third-party partners?]\\nCore entities: [list the main data objects, e.g., User, Order, Product]\\n\\nDeliver a complete API design including:\\n1. Resource hierarchy and all endpoints (method + path + one-line description)\\n2. Request/response JSON schemas for each endpoint (use realistic field names and types)\\n3. Authentication mechanism (JWT, API key, OAuth2 — recommend what fits best and explain why)\\n4. Pagination strategy for list endpoints\\n5. Standard error response format with HTTP status codes (400, 401, 403, 404, 409, 422, 500)\\n6. Versioning strategy (URL prefix vs. header)\\n7. Rate limiting recommendation\\n8. Three potential design pitfalls to watch out for in this specific API\\n\\nFormat the endpoint list as a Markdown table.","tags":["api-design","rest","backend","architecture","openapi"],"best_for":"Backend engineers and architects starting a new service or feature API","outcome":"A complete REST API spec with endpoints, schemas, auth, error codes, and design recommendations.","inputs":[{"label":"describe what the product or feature does"},{"label":"who will call this API"},{"label":"list the main data objects"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"plan","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Databases","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"SQL Query Builder","prompt":"Write a SQL query that satisfies the following requirements.\\n\\nDatabase type: [PostgreSQL / MySQL / SQLite / SQL Server / BigQuery]\\nRequirement in plain English: [describe exactly what data you need and any filters, sorts, or aggregations]\\n\\nRelevant table schemas (paste CREATE TABLE statements or describe columns):\\n[paste schemas here]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Write the complete SQL query\\n2. Add inline comments explaining non-obvious parts (subqueries, window functions, CTEs)\\n3. Identify any indexes that would make this query faster and show the CREATE INDEX statement\\n4. Estimate the query complexity (simple / moderate / heavy) and explain why\\n5. Warn about any correctness risks (e.g., NULL handling, implicit type coercion, timezone pitfalls)\\n6. If the query is heavy, suggest a rewritten alternative that avoids the bottleneck\\n\\nFormat: SQL code block first, then explanation.","tags":["sql","database","query","analytics","backend"],"best_for":"Developers and analysts who need complex queries but want to avoid trial-and-error on production data","outcome":"A complete, commented SQL query with index recommendations, complexity rating, and correctness warnings.","inputs":[{"label":"database type (PostgreSQL, MySQL, etc.)"},{"label":"requirement in plain English"},{"label":"paste table schemas or describe columns"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"5 min","output_kind":"code","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"DevOps & Infrastructure","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Docker Setup","prompt":"Generate a production-ready Docker setup for my project.\\n\\nProject description: [what the app does]\\nLanguage/runtime: [e.g., Node.js 20, Python 3.12, Go 1.22]\\nDependencies/services: [e.g., PostgreSQL 16, Redis 7, nginx]\\nEnvironment variables needed: [list them or say \'unknown\']\\n\\nPlease produce:\\n1. A Dockerfile for the application using a multi-stage build (build stage + minimal runtime stage)\\n2. A docker-compose.yml with all services, health checks, and named volumes\\n3. A .dockerignore file\\n4. An .env.example file with all required variables and placeholder values\\n5. Inline comments explaining non-obvious choices (why alpine, why --no-cache, etc.)\\n6. A one-paragraph explanation of the build and startup sequence\\n7. Three common mistakes to avoid when running this stack in production\\n\\nPrioritize: small final image size, fast rebuild times, and correct startup ordering.","tags":["docker","devops","containerization","docker-compose","infrastructure"],"best_for":"Developers containerizing an app for the first time or modernizing an existing Dockerfile","outcome":"A production-ready Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml, .dockerignore, and .env.example with explanatory comments.","inputs":[{"label":"what the app does"},{"label":"language and runtime version"},{"label":"list of external services (database, cache, etc.)"},{"label":"environment variables needed"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"10 min","output_kind":"code","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Refactoring","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Refactor Legacy Code","prompt":"Refactor the following legacy code to modern standards without changing its external behavior.\\n\\nLegacy code:\\n[paste the code here]\\n\\nLanguage: [e.g., Python 2 → 3.12, JavaScript ES5 → ES2022, Java 8 → 21]\\nKnown pain points: [e.g., \'hard to test\', \'no error handling\', \'global mutable state\', \'spaghetti logic\']\\n\\nRefactoring goals (check all that apply): [list from: readability, testability, performance, security, modularity]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Produce the refactored code with all modernizations applied\\n2. List every change made with a one-line rationale (format: old pattern → new pattern: reason)\\n3. Highlight any behavior that changed even slightly and explain the trade-off\\n4. Identify any remaining tech debt that is out of scope for this refactor\\n5. Suggest 3 follow-up refactors ordered by ROI\\n6. Provide a before/after complexity comparison (cyclomatic complexity if possible)\\n\\nConstraint: preserve the existing public API/function signatures unless a signature change is justified.","tags":["refactoring","legacy-code","modernization","clean-code","technical-debt"],"best_for":"Engineers tasked with modernizing old codebases or cleaning up before adding new features","outcome":"Refactored code with a change log, behavior-change warnings, remaining tech debt list, and follow-up suggestions.","inputs":[{"label":"paste the legacy code here"},{"label":"source and target language/version"},{"label":"known pain points"},{"label":"refactoring goals"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"code","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Security","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Security Code Audit","prompt":"Perform a security audit of the following code. Focus on real, exploitable vulnerabilities — not theoretical issues.\\n\\nCode to audit:\\n[paste the code here]\\n\\nLanguage/framework: [e.g., Python/Django, Node.js/Express, Java/Spring]\\nContext: [is this a public API? internal tool? handles PII? financial data?]\\n\\nAudit against the OWASP Top 10 and additionally check for:\\n1. Injection vulnerabilities (SQL, NoSQL, OS command, LDAP, template injection)\\n2. Broken authentication (weak passwords, missing rate limiting, insecure session management)\\n3. Sensitive data exposure (PII in logs, unencrypted secrets, verbose error messages)\\n4. Hardcoded credentials, API keys, or tokens\\n5. Insecure deserialization\\n6. Missing access control checks (vertical + horizontal privilege escalation)\\n7. Security misconfiguration (debug mode on, default credentials, CORS wildcard)\\n8. XSS and CSRF vulnerabilities\\n\\nFor each finding:\\n- Severity: Critical / High / Medium / Low\\n- Vulnerable line(s)\\n- Attack scenario (how an attacker would exploit it)\\n- Remediation code snippet\\n\\nEnd with a prioritized fix order.","tags":["security","owasp","audit","vulnerability","penetration-testing"],"best_for":"Developers preparing for a security review, or teams doing pre-launch security hardening","outcome":"A prioritized vulnerability report with severity ratings, attack scenarios, and remediation code for each finding.","inputs":[{"label":"paste the code here"},{"label":"language and framework"},{"label":"context: public API, internal tool, data sensitivity"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"analysis","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Documentation","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Write API Documentation","prompt":"Generate clear, developer-friendly API documentation for the following code.\\n\\nCode (function, class, or module):\\n[paste your code here]\\n\\nDoc format: [OpenAPI 3.0 YAML / Markdown / JSDoc / Python docstrings / Go doc comments]\\nAudience: [internal developers / external partners / public open-source community]\\n\\nFor each public function/endpoint, document:\\n1. Purpose: one-sentence description of what it does\\n2. Parameters: name, type, required/optional, default, constraints, description\\n3. Return value: type and description, including all possible shapes\\n4. Error cases: every error code or exception, what triggers it, and how to handle it\\n5. A working code example in [target language] that shows the most common usage\\n6. Any rate limits, side effects, or important caveats\\n\\nAlso generate:\\n- A module-level overview (2–3 sentences)\\n- A \'Quick Start\' section with the minimal working example\\n- A \'Common mistakes\' section with 3 gotchas","tags":["documentation","api","openapi","developer-experience","technical-writing"],"best_for":"Developers who want to document APIs quickly without writing boilerplate by hand","outcome":"Complete API documentation in the chosen format with examples, error codes, and a Quick Start section.","inputs":[{"label":"paste your code here"},{"label":"documentation format (OpenAPI, Markdown, JSDoc, etc.)"},{"label":"audience: internal devs, external partners, or public"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"10 min","output_kind":"templates","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Databases","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Database Schema Design","prompt":"Design a normalized relational database schema for the following requirements.\\n\\nApplication description: [describe what the app does]\\nCore business entities: [list the main things the system tracks, e.g., Users, Orders, Products, Reviews]\\nKey workflows: [describe the 3–5 most important actions users perform]\\nExpected scale: [rough row counts per table per year, e.g., \'100K orders/year\']\\nDatabase: [PostgreSQL / MySQL / SQLite]\\n\\nDeliver:\\n1. Full schema as CREATE TABLE statements with data types, constraints, and foreign keys\\n2. An entity-relationship description (which tables relate to which and how: 1:1, 1:N, M:N)\\n3. All junction/pivot tables needed for M:N relationships\\n4. Recommended indexes (beyond PKs) with rationale tied to the key workflows\\n5. Any columns that should be soft-deleted vs hard-deleted and why\\n6. Three schema decisions I might regret at scale, and the safer alternatives\\n7. Sample seed data (5 rows per key table) to illustrate the relationships","tags":["database","schema-design","sql","postgresql","data-modeling"],"best_for":"Backend engineers and architects designing a new data model or reviewing an existing one","outcome":"Production-ready CREATE TABLE statements, ER description, index recommendations, and scale risk warnings.","inputs":[{"label":"describe what the app does"},{"label":"list core business entities"},{"label":"describe 3–5 key user workflows"},{"label":"expected scale (row counts per year)"},{"label":"target database (PostgreSQL, MySQL, etc.)"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"code","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Git & Version Control","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Git Commit Message","prompt":"Write a conventional commit message for the following change.\\n\\nWhat changed (plain English): [describe what you did]\\nWhy it changed (motivation): [explain the reason or ticket it fixes]\\nAny breaking changes? [yes/no — if yes, describe]\\n\\nFollow the Conventional Commits spec (https://www.conventionalcommits.org):\\n- Format: <type>(<scope>): <description>\\n- Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, chore, ci, build, revert\\n- Subject line: imperative mood, ≤72 chars, no period at end\\n- Body (if needed): wrap at 72 chars, explain \'what\' and \'why\' not \'how\'\\n- Footer: reference issues (Closes #123) and note BREAKING CHANGE if applicable\\n\\nProvide:\\n1. The primary commit message (subject + body + footer)\\n2. Two alternative subject lines if the type/scope is ambiguous\\n3. A one-sentence explanation of why you chose this type over the alternatives","tags":["git","commit","conventional-commits","version-control","workflow"],"best_for":"Developers who want consistent, descriptive commit history without agonizing over wording","outcome":"A Conventional Commits-compliant commit message with body, footer, and two alternative subject lines.","inputs":[{"label":"describe what you changed in plain English"},{"label":"why the change was made (motivation or ticket)"},{"label":"any breaking changes? (yes/no and description)"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"2 min","output_kind":"templates","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Architecture","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"System Design Interview","prompt":"Walk me through designing [system name] at scale. Treat this as a system design interview where I need to demonstrate senior-engineer thinking.\\n\\nSystem to design: [e.g., URL shortener, ride-sharing app, distributed cache, real-time chat, news feed]\\nScale targets: [e.g., 100M users, 10K writes/sec, 99.99% uptime, sub-100ms p99 latency]\\nConstraints: [e.g., must be globally distributed, budget-conscious, uses AWS only]\\n\\nStructure the design as follows:\\n1. Requirements clarification — functional and non-functional requirements\\n2. Capacity estimation — storage, bandwidth, QPS (reads and writes)\\n3. High-level architecture — component diagram described in text\\n4. Deep dives: data model, API design, and the hardest 2–3 scaling bottlenecks\\n5. Data storage choices — SQL vs NoSQL, caching layer, CDN\\n6. Fault tolerance — how it handles node failures, network partitions, hot spots\\n7. Trade-offs — what you chose and what you sacrificed\\n8. Three follow-up questions an interviewer might ask next\\n\\nBe specific: use real technology names (Kafka, Redis, Cassandra, PostgreSQL, S3) and justify each choice.","tags":["system-design","architecture","scalability","interview","distributed-systems"],"best_for":"Engineers preparing for senior/staff-level system design interviews or architecting a new system","outcome":"A complete system design walkthrough with capacity estimates, architecture decisions, trade-offs, and follow-up questions.","inputs":[{"label":"system to design (e.g., URL shortener, ride-sharing app)"},{"label":"scale targets (users, QPS, uptime, latency)"},{"label":"constraints (cloud provider, budget, geography)"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"plan","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Performance","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Performance Optimization","prompt":"Help me find and fix the performance bottlenecks in the following code.\\n\\nSlow code:\\n[paste the code or the slowest function here]\\n\\nLanguage/runtime: [e.g., Python 3.12, Node.js 20, Java 21, Go 1.22]\\nMeasured performance: [e.g., \'takes 8 seconds for 10K records\', \'p99 latency is 2.4s\']\\nProfiling data (if available): [paste flamegraph summary, cProfile output, or describe what\'s slow]\\nTarget performance: [e.g., \'needs to complete in under 500ms\']\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Identify the top 3 bottlenecks ranked by impact\\n2. For each bottleneck: explain why it\'s slow (algorithm complexity, I/O bound, memory pressure, etc.)\\n3. Provide an optimized version of the code for each bottleneck\\n4. Show the theoretical speedup (e.g., O(n²) → O(n log n))\\n5. Suggest any caching, batching, or parallelism strategies that apply\\n6. Warn about any correctness trade-offs introduced by the optimization\\n7. Recommend what to measure after each change (specific metrics and tools)","tags":["performance","optimization","profiling","scalability","backend"],"best_for":"Engineers debugging slow endpoints, batch jobs, or functions where profiling reveals a clear hotspot","outcome":"Ranked list of bottlenecks with optimized code, complexity analysis, and measurement recommendations.","inputs":[{"label":"paste the slow code or function"},{"label":"language and runtime"},{"label":"measured performance (e.g., 8s for 10K records)"},{"label":"profiling data if available"},{"label":"target performance goal"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"analysis","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Documentation","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Write a README","prompt":"Write a comprehensive, developer-friendly README.md for my project.\\n\\nProject name: [project name]\\nOne-line description: [what it does in one sentence]\\nLanguage/framework: [e.g., Python/FastAPI, TypeScript/React, Go]\\nKey features: [list 3–6 bullet points of what it does]\\nTarget audience: [who uses this — internal team, open-source community, end users?]\\nInstallation complexity: [simple pip install vs. multi-step setup with prerequisites]\\n\\nStructure the README with these sections:\\n1. Title, badge row (build, coverage, license), and one-paragraph description\\n2. Features — bulleted list with concrete specifics\\n3. Prerequisites — OS, runtime version, required tools\\n4. Installation — numbered steps with exact commands to copy-paste\\n5. Quick Start — the minimal working example that shows the core value in under 5 minutes\\n6. Configuration — key environment variables and config options with defaults\\n7. Usage examples — 2–3 common use cases with code snippets\\n8. Contributing — how to set up a dev environment and submit PRs\\n9. License\\n\\nTone: clear, direct, welcoming. No marketing fluff.","tags":["documentation","readme","open-source","developer-experience","markdown"],"best_for":"Developers launching a new project or cleaning up an undocumented repo before sharing it","outcome":"A complete, well-structured README.md that lets a new developer go from zero to running the project in under 10 minutes.","inputs":[{"label":"project name"},{"label":"one-line description of what it does"},{"label":"language and framework"},{"label":"list 3–6 key features"},{"label":"target audience"},{"label":"installation complexity level"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"10 min","output_kind":"templates","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Architecture","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Tech Stack Selection","prompt":"Help me choose the right technology stack for my project. Be opinionated and practical — not just a list of options.\\n\\nProject description: [what the product does and who uses it]\\nTeam: [size, existing skills, e.g., \'3 engineers who know Python and React\']\\nScale expectations: [expected users, data volume, requests per second in year 1 and year 3]\\nKey constraints: [budget, time-to-market, compliance requirements, cloud preference, must-have integrations]\\nNon-negotiables: [anything you\'ve already decided or are locked into]\\n\\nFor each layer of the stack (frontend, backend, database, auth, hosting/infra, CI/CD, monitoring), recommend:\\n1. Your top choice — with a 2–3 sentence justification tied to my specific constraints\\n2. The strongest alternative — when would it be better than your top choice?\\n3. What to avoid — one option many teams choose that would be a mistake for my situation\\n\\nEnd with:\\n- A migration risk score (1–10) for the recommended stack\\n- The biggest technical risk in this stack and how to mitigate it\\n- Three questions I should answer before finalizing the decision","tags":["tech-stack","architecture","decision-making","engineering","startup"],"best_for":"Engineering leads and founders making technology decisions for a new product or platform rewrite","outcome":"An opinionated stack recommendation per layer with justifications, alternatives, things to avoid, and key open questions.","inputs":[{"label":"describe the product and its users"},{"label":"team size and existing skills"},{"label":"scale expectations (year 1 and year 3)"},{"label":"key constraints (budget, time-to-market, compliance, cloud)"},{"label":"non-negotiables (already decided or locked in)"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"plan","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Content Marketing","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Case Study Writer","prompt":"Write a compelling customer success case study from the following bullet points.\\n\\nCompany background: [customer industry, size, and role of the person quoted]\\nThe problem they had: [bullet points describing the pain before your product]\\nWhat they implemented: [which features/services they used and how]\\nResults achieved: [specific metrics — time saved, revenue gained, cost reduced, percentage improvements]\\nQuote(s) available: [paste any real quotes, or say \'none — please suggest placeholders\']\\nTarget audience: [prospects in which role/industry?]\\n\\nWrite a 600–800 word case study with:\\n1. A results-forward headline that leads with the most impressive number\\n2. A 2-sentence executive summary (the \'so what\' for a busy reader)\\n3. \'The Challenge\' section — make the pain visceral and specific\\n4. \'The Solution\' section — focus on workflow change, not feature list\\n5. \'The Results\' section — lead with numbers, then explain what made them possible\\n6. A pull quote from the customer\\n7. A closing CTA paragraph\\n\\nTone: credible and specific. No buzzwords like \'synergy\', \'game-changer\', or \'revolutionary\'.","tags":["case-study","content-marketing","copywriting","b2b","customer-success"],"best_for":"Marketing teams turning customer wins into written proof points for sales enablement","outcome":"A 600–800 word case study with headline, challenge/solution/results structure, pull quote, and CTA.","inputs":[{"label":"customer company background (industry, size, role)"},{"label":"the problem they had (bullet points)"},{"label":"what they implemented"},{"label":"results achieved (specific metrics)"},{"label":"any available customer quotes"},{"label":"target audience for this case study"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"templates","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Content Marketing","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Technical Blog Post","prompt":"Create an SEO-optimized outline and introduction for a technical blog post.\\n\\nTopic: [what you want to write about]\\nTarget keyword: [primary keyword you want to rank for]\\nAudience: [who reads this — e.g., \'senior backend engineers\', \'data scientists learning MLOps\']\\nAngle: [your unique perspective or new information, e.g., \'benchmarks comparing 5 approaches\', \'lessons from our migration\', \'the mistake everyone makes\']\\nCompetitors to beat: [paste 1–2 URLs of posts already ranking, or say \'unknown\']\\n\\nDeliver:\\n1. SEO analysis — search intent (informational/navigational/transactional), secondary keywords to weave in, and recommended title tag (≤60 chars)\\n2. Full H2/H3 outline with a one-sentence description of each section\'s key point\\n3. A 150-word introduction that hooks the reader with a concrete problem or surprising stat\\n4. Meta description (≤155 chars)\\n5. Three internal linking opportunities (describe what related content to link to)\\n6. Estimated word count and reading time\\n7. One thing most posts on this topic get wrong — and how yours will be different","tags":["seo","blog","content-marketing","technical-writing","thought-leadership"],"best_for":"Developer advocates, technical marketers, and engineers writing for company engineering blogs","outcome":"An SEO-ready outline, hook introduction, meta description, and differentiation strategy for a technical blog post.","inputs":[{"label":"topic to write about"},{"label":"primary keyword to rank for"},{"label":"target audience"},{"label":"your unique angle or new information"},{"label":"competitor URLs already ranking (or \'unknown\')"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"10 min","output_kind":"plan","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Product Communication","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Product Changelog","prompt":"Rewrite raw developer release notes into a polished, user-friendly product changelog.\\n\\nRelease version: [version number or date]\\nRaw dev notes:\\n[paste your internal notes, commit messages, or Jira tickets here]\\n\\nTarget audience: [end users / technical customers / both]\\nProduct name: [name of the product or feature area]\\n\\nRewrite the changelog following these rules:\\n1. Lead with user benefit, not technical implementation (\'You can now export to PDF\' not \'Added PDF serializer\')\\n2. Group changes under: New Features, Improvements, Bug Fixes, and (if applicable) Deprecations\\n3. Write each item as one sentence in active voice, max 25 words\\n4. For new features: add a one-sentence \'Why this matters\' in italics\\n5. Remove internal jargon, ticket numbers, and engineer names\\n6. Highlight the top 1–2 changes with a brief paragraph at the top (\'What\'s new in [version]\')\\n7. End with a \'How to update\' one-liner if applicable\\n\\nTone: clear, friendly, confident. Write for the user who doesn\'t follow your GitHub commits.","tags":["changelog","release-notes","product-writing","communication","saas"],"best_for":"Product managers and technical writers converting internal release notes into customer-facing changelogs","outcome":"A polished user-facing changelog grouped by change type with benefit-focused language and a highlights summary.","inputs":[{"label":"version number or release date"},{"label":"paste raw developer notes, commit messages, or tickets"},{"label":"target audience (end users, technical customers, or both)"},{"label":"product name"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"5 min","output_kind":"templates","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"HR & Recruiting","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Job Description","prompt":"Write a compelling, bias-reduced job description for the following role.\\n\\nRole title: [exact job title]\\nTeam/department: [where this person sits]\\nLevel: [e.g., Senior, Staff, Lead, Principal]\\nTop 3 things this person will own: [the most important responsibilities]\\nMust-have qualifications: [non-negotiable skills or experience]\\nNice-to-have qualifications: [preferred but not required]\\nCompensation range: [if you can share — improves applicant quality]\\nRemote/hybrid/onsite: [work model and location]\\nCompany culture in 3 words: [e.g., \'fast, collaborative, customer-obsessed\']\\n\\nWrite the JD with these sections:\\n1. Role summary (3–4 sentences) — lead with impact, not org chart position\\n2. What you\'ll do — 5–7 bulleted responsibilities starting with strong action verbs\\n3. What we\'re looking for — separate must-haves from nice-to-haves explicitly\\n4. What we offer — benefits, growth, culture (be specific, not generic)\\n5. About us — 2-sentence company description\\n\\nApply inclusive language: remove gendered pronouns, avoid \'ninja/rockstar/guru\', prefer \'you will\' over \'must have X years\'. Flag any requirement that may screen out qualified candidates unnecessarily.","tags":["recruiting","hr","job-description","hiring","talent-acquisition"],"best_for":"Hiring managers and recruiters who want well-crafted, inclusive JDs that attract strong candidates","outcome":"A structured, bias-reduced job description with impact-focused summary, responsibilities, requirements, and benefits.","inputs":[{"label":"exact job title"},{"label":"team and department"},{"label":"seniority level"},{"label":"top 3 ownership areas"},{"label":"must-have qualifications"},{"label":"nice-to-have qualifications"},{"label":"compensation range (optional)"},{"label":"remote/hybrid/onsite and location"},{"label":"company culture in 3 words"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"10 min","output_kind":"templates","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Internal Communications","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Internal Announcement","prompt":"Write a clear, well-structured internal announcement memo for the following news.\\n\\nAnnouncement type: [e.g., leadership change, reorg, new policy, product milestone, office update, layoff, acquisition]\\nThe news in plain terms: [describe what is happening]\\nEffective date: [when this takes effect]\\nWho is affected: [entire company / specific teams / specific roles]\\nKey questions employees will have: [list the top 3–5  \'what about me?\' questions]\\nWhat is NOT changing: [anything important to reassure people about]\\nWho is sending this: [name and title of sender]\\nChannel: [Slack / email / all-hands / internal blog]\\n\\nWrite the announcement with:\\n1. Subject line (for email) or first-line hook (for Slack/internal post) — max 10 words\\n2. Opening paragraph: the news clearly stated in 2 sentences (no burying the lede)\\n3. Context section: why this is happening (honest and direct)\\n4. Impact section: what changes for employees, broken down by audience if needed\\n5. FAQ: answer the 3–5 questions you listed above\\n6. Next steps: what employees should do and when\\n7. Closing: where to ask questions (Slack channel, email, open office hours)\\n\\nTone: transparent, empathetic, direct. Avoid corporate euphemisms.","tags":["internal-comms","memo","announcement","leadership","change-management"],"best_for":"Managers, chiefs of staff, and communications leads drafting sensitive or company-wide announcements","outcome":"A complete internal announcement with clear news statement, context, employee impact, FAQ, and next steps.","inputs":[{"label":"type of announcement"},{"label":"the news in plain terms"},{"label":"effective date"},{"label":"who is affected"},{"label":"top 3–5 employee questions to address"},{"label":"what is NOT changing"},{"label":"sender name and title"},{"label":"distribution channel"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"10 min","output_kind":"templates","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Exploratory Analysis","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Exploratory Data Analysis Plan","prompt":"Create a step-by-step exploratory data analysis (EDA) plan for my dataset.\\n\\nDataset description: [describe what the dataset contains — rows, columns, data types]\\nBusiness question I\'m trying to answer: [what decision or insight are you working toward?]\\nKnown data quality issues: [e.g., \'lots of nulls in the revenue column\', \'dates inconsistently formatted\', or \'none known\']\\nAnalysis tool: [Python/pandas, R, SQL, Excel, or a BI tool]\\n\\nProduce a complete EDA plan with:\\n1. Data loading and shape check — row count, column count, dtypes, memory usage\\n2. Missing value audit — percentage missing per column, pattern analysis (MCAR vs MAR vs MNAR)\\n3. Distribution analysis — for each numeric column: mean, median, std, min/max, skewness, histogram recommendation\\n4. Categorical analysis — cardinality, top-N value counts, rare categories to watch\\n5. Correlation analysis — correlation matrix, top 5 pairs by absolute correlation\\n6. Outlier detection — IQR method and Z-score method, flag columns needing review\\n7. Time-series check — if date columns exist, check for gaps, seasonality, and trend\\n8. Business-question-specific analysis — 3 targeted analyses directly tied to the question above\\n9. Data quality scorecard — rate each column: Clean / Needs Cleaning / Unusable\\n\\nFor each step, include the exact Python/R/SQL code snippet to run it.","tags":["eda","data-analysis","pandas","python","analytics"],"best_for":"Data analysts and data scientists starting a new dataset who want a systematic quality and insight checklist","outcome":"A step-by-step EDA plan with code snippets, a data quality scorecard, and 3 targeted analyses for the business question.","inputs":[{"label":"describe the dataset (rows, columns, data types)"},{"label":"business question you\'re trying to answer"},{"label":"known data quality issues"},{"label":"analysis tool (Python, R, SQL, Excel)"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"plan","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Business Intelligence","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"KPI Dashboard Design","prompt":"Design a KPI dashboard for the following business function. Be specific enough that a BI developer could build it from your output.\\n\\nBusiness function: [e.g., Sales, Marketing, Customer Success, Engineering, Finance, Operations]\\nStakeholder audience: [who will read this dashboard — e.g., VP of Sales, SDR team, C-suite]\\nDecisions this dashboard should drive: [list 2–3 specific decisions the audience makes using this data]\\nData sources available: [e.g., Salesforce, HubSpot, PostgreSQL, Stripe, Google Analytics]\\nRefresh cadence needed: [real-time / hourly / daily / weekly]\\n\\nDeliver:\\n1. KPI hierarchy — tier 1 (north-star), tier 2 (drivers), tier 3 (operational diagnostics)\\n2. For each KPI: metric name, formula, data source, owner, target value, alert threshold\\n3. Dashboard layout recommendation — number of sections, chart types, and which KPIs go where\\n4. Drill-down paths — which tier-1 metric can be decomposed into which tier-2/3 metrics\\n5. Three metrics that look important but are actually vanity metrics for this audience\\n6. Data freshness and quality risks — which KPIs are most likely to be wrong and why\\n7. Implementation checklist — 5 steps to go from zero to a live dashboard in a BI tool","tags":["kpi","dashboard","business-intelligence","metrics","analytics"],"best_for":"Analytics leads and BI developers designing dashboards for business stakeholders","outcome":"A complete KPI hierarchy with formulas, sources, targets, layout recommendation, and vanity-metric warnings.","inputs":[{"label":"business function (Sales, Marketing, Engineering, etc.)"},{"label":"stakeholder audience"},{"label":"decisions this dashboard should drive"},{"label":"available data sources"},{"label":"required refresh cadence"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"plan","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Experimentation","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"A/B Test Design","prompt":"Design a statistically rigorous A/B test for the following change.\\n\\nProduct area: [e.g., checkout flow, email subject line, onboarding screen, pricing page]\\nHypothesis: [If we [change X], then [metric Y] will [increase/decrease] because [reason]]\\nPrimary success metric: [exact metric and how it\'s measured]\\nGuardrail metrics: [metrics that must NOT get worse]\\nBaseline values: [current conversion rate, mean, or whatever the primary metric is]\\nMinimum detectable effect (MDE): [smallest change worth shipping, e.g., \'+5% conversion rate\']\\nExpected daily traffic to the experiment: [visitors/users per day]\\nStatistical requirements: [significance level α, power 1-β — default 0.05 / 0.80 if unknown]\\n\\nDeliver:\\n1. Formal null and alternative hypothesis\\n2. Required sample size per variant (with calculation shown)\\n3. Recommended test duration in days\\n4. Randomization unit (user, session, device) and why\\n5. Segmentation plan — which users to include/exclude and why\\n6. Pre-experiment checklist (SRM test, instrumentation check, novelty effect window)\\n7. Decision framework — what you\'ll do for each outcome: significant win / significant loss / inconclusive\\n8. Three threats to validity for this specific experiment and how to mitigate them","tags":["ab-testing","experimentation","statistics","product-analytics","growth"],"best_for":"Product managers and data scientists designing experiments that need to be statistically sound before launch","outcome":"A complete experiment design with sample size, duration, randomization unit, decision framework, and validity threats.","inputs":[{"label":"product area being tested"},{"label":"hypothesis (if X then Y because Z)"},{"label":"primary success metric and how it\'s measured"},{"label":"guardrail metrics"},{"label":"baseline metric value"},{"label":"minimum detectable effect (MDE)"},{"label":"expected daily traffic"},{"label":"significance level and power (default 0.05/0.80)"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"plan","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Customer Analytics","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Customer Churn Analysis","prompt":"Design a customer churn analysis and retention intervention plan for my business.\\n\\nBusiness type: [e.g., B2B SaaS, e-commerce, subscription box, mobile app]\\nDefinition of churn: [how you define a churned customer — e.g., \'no login in 30 days\', \'cancelled subscription\', \'no purchase in 90 days\']\\nCurrent churn rate: [monthly or annual percentage]\\nAvailable data: [list data sources — e.g., CRM, product analytics, support tickets, billing]\\nCustomer segments: [how customers are currently segmented, or \'unknown\']\\n\\nDeliver:\\n1. Churn segmentation framework — 4–6 churn archetypes for this business type (e.g., \'fast churn\', \'slow fade\', \'involuntary\')\\n2. Leading indicators — 8–10 behavioral signals that predict churn 30–60 days in advance\\n3. Feature list for a churn prediction model — what to engineer from the available data\\n4. Cohort analysis plan — which cohorts to compare and what patterns to look for\\n5. Retention playbook — for each churn archetype: trigger, intervention, channel, message, success metric\\n6. Cannibalization check — 3 interventions that feel helpful but actually accelerate churn\\n7. 30/60/90-day analytics roadmap to move from current state to a live churn early-warning system","tags":["churn","retention","customer-analytics","saas","predictive-analytics"],"best_for":"Data analysts and customer success leads building churn prediction and retention programs","outcome":"A churn archetype framework, leading indicators, retention playbook per segment, and a 90-day analytics roadmap.","inputs":[{"label":"business type (B2B SaaS, e-commerce, etc.)"},{"label":"definition of churn"},{"label":"current churn rate (monthly or annual)"},{"label":"available data sources"},{"label":"current customer segmentation (or \'unknown\')"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"plan","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Statistical Methods","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Anomaly Detection Strategy","prompt":"Design an anomaly detection strategy for the following time-series data.\\n\\nData description: [what the time series measures — e.g., API error rate, daily revenue, server CPU, website traffic]\\nData characteristics: [frequency: hourly/daily/weekly; known seasonality: yes/no; expected trend: growing/stable/cyclical]\\nAnomaly types to catch: [point anomalies, contextual anomalies, collective anomalies — or \'all types\']\\nCurrent baseline: [typical value range, e.g., \'error rate normally 0.1–0.3%\']\\nFalse positive tolerance: [low / medium / high — how bad is a false alarm?]\\nLatency requirement: [how quickly must an anomaly be flagged — real-time, within 1 hour, daily?]\\nTools/stack available: [Python, SQL, cloud monitoring, etc.]\\n\\nDeliver:\\n1. Recommended detection algorithm(s) — matched to the data characteristics above, with pros/cons\\n2. Baseline modeling approach — how to compute \'normal\' accounting for seasonality and trend\\n3. Threshold-setting methodology — statistical (Z-score, IQR, prediction interval) vs. adaptive\\n4. Feature engineering — what derived features to compute from the raw signal\\n5. Evaluation framework — how to measure precision/recall on historical data and set alert thresholds\\n6. Alert design — what context to include in an alert so on-call engineers can triage in under 2 minutes\\n7. Implementation plan — numbered steps from raw data to production alerts\\n8. Three common mistakes in anomaly detection for this type of data and how to avoid them","tags":["anomaly-detection","time-series","statistics","monitoring","mlops"],"best_for":"Data engineers and ML engineers building alerting systems for operational or business metrics","outcome":"A complete anomaly detection strategy with algorithm recommendation, baseline approach, alert design, and implementation steps.","inputs":[{"label":"what the time series measures"},{"label":"data frequency and seasonality characteristics"},{"label":"types of anomalies to catch"},{"label":"current baseline value range"},{"label":"false positive tolerance (low/medium/high)"},{"label":"latency requirement for detection"},{"label":"available tools and stack"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"plan","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Reflection & Planning","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Weekly Review","prompt":"Guide me through a structured weekly review and next-week planning session.\\n\\nThis week\'s highlights (wins, completions): [list anything you finished or that went well]\\nThis week\'s struggles (what didn\'t get done, what felt hard): [list incomplete items and friction points]\\nTop priorities for next week: [list up to 5 things that must happen next week]\\nUpcoming deadlines or events: [meetings, launches, due dates in the next 7–14 days]\\nEnergy level this week: [low / medium / high]\\nOne thing I want to do differently next week: [any habit, routine, or approach change]\\n\\nBased on my input, produce:\\n1. A brief \'Week in Review\' narrative (3–5 sentences) that frames the week\'s story fairly\\n2. Three learnings or insights from this week (including one from the struggles)\\n3. A prioritized task list for next week, formatted as Monday–Friday blocks with realistic time estimates\\n4. One thing to drop, delay, or delegate from next week\'s list to protect deep work time\\n5. A \'this week\'s win\' affirmation to start Monday with momentum\\n6. One question to sit with over the weekend that will make next week more intentional","tags":["weekly-review","productivity","planning","reflection","time-management"],"best_for":"Knowledge workers and managers who want a structured end-of-week ritual to close loops and plan intentionally","outcome":"A week-in-review narrative, 3 learnings, a day-blocked task list for next week, and one thing to drop.","inputs":[{"label":"this week\'s highlights and wins"},{"label":"this week\'s struggles and incomplete items"},{"label":"top priorities for next week (up to 5)"},{"label":"upcoming deadlines or events"},{"label":"energy level this week (low/medium/high)"},{"label":"one thing to do differently next week"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"10 min","output_kind":"plan","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Meetings & Collaboration","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Meeting Agenda","prompt":"Create a focused, time-boxed meeting agenda from the following information.\\n\\nMeeting goal: [one sentence — what must be decided, aligned, or resolved by the end?]\\nMeeting type: [e.g., decision meeting, brainstorm, status update, retrospective, kickoff, 1:1]\\nAttendees and roles: [list names/roles — who is the decision-maker?]\\nDuration: [30 min / 45 min / 60 min / 90 min]\\nContext/background: [brief context attendees need, or paste any pre-read material]\\nKnown tensions or disagreements: [anything contentious that needs careful facilitation?]\\n\\nProduce:\\n1. A pre-meeting checklist (what to send to attendees 24 hours before)\\n2. A time-boxed agenda with exact minutes per section and the meeting owner\'s role in each\\n3. Opening framing — the 2-sentence \'why we\'re here and what success looks like\' statement\\n4. Three decision points or discussion questions, ordered from most to least critical\\n5. A parking lot protocol — how to handle topics that arise but are out of scope\\n6. A closing ritual — how to end with clear owners, actions, and deadlines\\n7. A post-meeting follow-up template (summary format with decisions and action items table)","tags":["meeting","agenda","facilitation","productivity","collaboration"],"best_for":"Meeting organizers and team leads who want every meeting to end with clear decisions and no wasted time","outcome":"A complete meeting package: pre-meeting checklist, time-boxed agenda, key questions, and follow-up template.","inputs":[{"label":"one-sentence meeting goal (what must be decided or resolved)"},{"label":"meeting type (decision, brainstorm, status, etc.)"},{"label":"attendees and their roles"},{"label":"meeting duration"},{"label":"context or background"},{"label":"known tensions or contentious topics"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"5 min","output_kind":"templates","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Decision Making","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Decision Matrix","prompt":"Help me make a difficult decision using a structured decision matrix.\\n\\nDecision to make: [describe the choice you\'re facing clearly]\\nOptions available: [list all options you\'re considering — at least 2, ideally 3–5]\\nWhat matters most to me: [list 4–8 criteria that this decision should be evaluated against]\\nConstraints: [anything that disqualifies an option — budget, time, dependencies]\\nWho else is affected: [list any stakeholders whose interests matter]\\nDeadline to decide: [when must this be decided?]\\nGut leaning (if any): [your current instinct, or \'none\']\\n\\nDeliver:\\n1. A weighted decision matrix — assign weights to each criterion (totaling 100%) based on what you told me, then score each option 1–5 per criterion\\n2. Final weighted scores and a ranking of options\\n3. Sensitivity analysis — which criterion, if weighted differently, would change the top choice?\\n4. The strongest argument FOR each option (steelman)\\n5. The biggest hidden risk in the top-ranked option\\n6. A recommended decision with a 3-sentence rationale\\n7. A reversibility assessment — how hard is it to undo each option? (1=easy to reverse, 5=permanent)\\n8. The one question you should answer before committing, if any uncertainty remains","tags":["decision-making","decision-matrix","frameworks","strategy","critical-thinking"],"best_for":"Individuals and leaders facing high-stakes decisions who want to reduce bias and clarify their reasoning","outcome":"A weighted decision matrix with scores, sensitivity analysis, steelman arguments, and a recommended decision with rationale.","inputs":[{"label":"describe the decision you\'re facing"},{"label":"list all options (2–5)"},{"label":"list 4–8 criteria that matter to you"},{"label":"constraints (budget, time, dependencies)"},{"label":"stakeholders affected"},{"label":"decision deadline"},{"label":"gut leaning if any"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"analysis","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Learning & Growth","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Learning Roadmap","prompt":"Build me a 90-day learning roadmap to develop the following skill.\\n\\nSkill to learn: [specific skill — e.g., \'machine learning with PyTorch\', \'product management\', \'public speaking\', \'SQL for data analysis\']\\nCurrent level: [complete beginner / some basics / intermediate — describe what you already know]\\nLearning goal: [what will you be able to DO after 90 days? Be specific — e.g., \'build and deploy a binary classifier\', \'lead a product discovery sprint\', \'give a 20-min conference talk\']\\nTime available: [hours per week you can realistically dedicate]\\nLearning style: [reading / video / project-based / cohort / mix]\\nResources available: [budget for courses, books; subscriptions you already have]\\n\\nDeliver:\\n1. A prerequisite check — 3 things to confirm or learn before starting\\n2. A 3-phase plan (30/60/90 days) with clear milestones and the core skill unlocked at each phase\\n3. Week-by-week schedule for the first 30 days (specific topics, resources, estimated hours)\\n4. High-signal resources — top 1 book, 1 course, 1 practice platform, and 1 community for this skill (with links if well-known)\\n5. A portfolio project to build in phase 2–3 that proves competency to employers or peers\\n6. Three common learning traps for this specific skill (what beginners waste time on)\\n7. A \'minimum viable competency\' definition — the 20% of the skill that delivers 80% of the value","tags":["learning","skill-development","roadmap","career","self-improvement"],"best_for":"Professionals and students who want to learn a new skill systematically rather than randomly consuming content","outcome":"A 90-day structured roadmap with weekly schedule, curated resources, a portfolio project, and minimum viable competency definition.","inputs":[{"label":"specific skill to learn"},{"label":"current level (beginner/some basics/intermediate)"},{"label":"specific learning goal after 90 days"},{"label":"hours per week available"},{"label":"preferred learning style"},{"label":"budget and existing subscriptions"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"10 min","output_kind":"plan","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Project Management","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Project Kickoff Brief","prompt":"Create a complete project kickoff brief from the following description.\\n\\nProject name: [project name]\\nProject description: [what this project will produce and why it matters]\\nSponsor/stakeholder: [who commissioned this and what they care about most]\\nTeam members: [names and roles]\\nDeadline: [target completion date or launch date]\\nBudget: [budget or \'not yet defined\']\\nKnown dependencies: [systems, teams, vendors, or approvals needed]\\nKnown risks: [anything that could derail this — or \'none identified yet\']\\nDefinition of done: [how will you know the project is complete and successful?]\\n\\nProduce a complete kickoff brief with:\\n1. Problem statement (2 sentences: the \'before\' state and why it\'s a problem)\\n2. Success criteria — 3–5 measurable outcomes tied to the definition of done\\n3. Scope statement — in scope (bullet list) and explicitly out of scope (bullet list)\\n4. Milestone plan — 4–6 milestones with target dates and owners\\n5. RACI summary — who is Responsible, Accountable, Consulted, Informed for the top 5 decisions\\n6. Risk register — top 5 risks with likelihood (H/M/L), impact (H/M/L), and mitigation action\\n7. Communication plan — cadence, channel, and audience for status updates\\n8. First-week actions — a numbered checklist of the first 5 things to do to start strong","tags":["project-management","kickoff","planning","team","pmo"],"best_for":"Project managers and team leads starting a new initiative who want to align the team from day one","outcome":"A complete kickoff brief with success criteria, scope, milestone plan, RACI, risk register, and first-week actions.","inputs":[{"label":"project name"},{"label":"project description (what it produces and why)"},{"label":"sponsor and what they care about most"},{"label":"team members and roles"},{"label":"deadline"},{"label":"budget (or \'not yet defined\')"},{"label":"known dependencies"},{"label":"known risks"},{"label":"definition of done"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"plan","dateAdded":"2026-05-30","confidence":"high","last_verified":"2026-05-30","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Corporate Finance & Deal Support","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"M&A Due Diligence Data Room Analyser","prompt":"\\"You are a financial due diligence analyst. I\'m uploading [number] documents from a data room for a potential acquisition of [target company description — sector, revenue, geography].\\n\\nFor each document:\\n1. Extract key financial metrics (revenue, EBITDA, capex, working capital, debt)\\n2. Flag any red flags or inconsistencies vs. management\'s stated narrative\\n3. Identify off-balance-sheet risks (operating leases, contingent liabilities, earn-outs)\\n4. Note any items requiring specialist follow-up (legal, tax, IP)\\n5. Produce a 1-page issues log sorted by severity: Critical / Significant / Minor\\n\\nTarget deal size: [value]\\nBid date: [date]\\nKey focus areas: [list, e.g., revenue quality, customer concentration, working capital normalisation]\\"","tags":["m&a","due-diligence","corporate-finance","deal","advanced","multi-day"],"best_for":"M&A analysts, corporate development teams, PE associates, Big 4 TAS","source":"OpenAI Enterprise — Morgan Stanley M&A copilot deployment; Deloitte M&A Analytics practice","outcome":"A structured issues log with severity ratings, a normalised P&L bridging management accounts to quality-of-earnings, and a list of information requests for the next data room round.","inputs":[{"label":"number"},{"label":"target company description — sector, revenue, geography"},{"label":"value"},{"label":"date"},{"label":"list, e.g., revenue quality, customer concentration, working capital normalisation"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel"],"est_time":"Half-day","output_kind":"document","sample_output":"**Issues Log — Acme Co Acquisition**\\n\\n| # | Area | Finding | Severity | Action |\\n|---|------|---------|----------|--------|\\n| 1 | Revenue | 3 customers = 61% revenue; largest contract expires Oct 2026 unrenewed | Critical | Obtain renewal LOI or price into model |\\n| 2 | Working Capital | DSO increased 18→29 days YoY; AR aging not provided | Significant | Request aging schedule |\\n| 3 | Debt | €4.2M lease liability not on face of balance sheet (IFRS 16 non-compliant) | Significant | Restate for normalised net debt |\\n| 4 | Tax | €900K deferred tax asset assumes profitability — not supported by 3-year plan | Minor | Sensitise |\\n\\n**Normalised EBITDA bridge:** Reported €8.1M → +€0.4M owner salary → −€1.1M one-off contract → **Adjusted €7.4M (8.1× at €60M bid)**","dateAdded":"2026-06-05","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Corporate Finance & Deal Support","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Earnings Call Prep & Analyst Q&A Simulator","prompt":"\\"You are a financial communications expert and former sell-side analyst. I\'m preparing for our upcoming earnings call.\\n\\nCompany context:\\n- Results summary: [revenue, EBITDA, EPS vs. consensus]\\n- Key narratives to drive: [list 2-3]\\n- Sensitive topics to navigate: [list, e.g., margin pressure, guidance cut, CEO departure]\\n- Transcript of last quarter\'s call: [paste or summarise]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Draft 5-minute CEO opening remarks (factual, forward-looking, no spin)\\n2. Draft CFO financial summary (3 minutes)\\n3. Simulate the 10 hardest analyst questions you\'d face today, with model answers\\n4. Flag any statements that could create legal exposure (regulation FD, forward-looking statements)\\n5. Suggest 3 messages we should proactively land before analysts ask\\"","tags":["earnings","investor-relations","cfo","communications","half-day"],"best_for":"CFOs, IR directors, investor relations managers, communications leads","source":"OpenAI Enterprise — Goldman Sachs IR workbench; Morgan Stanley internal AI tools","outcome":"A ready-to-rehearse earnings call script with CEO and CFO remarks, 10 stress-tested Q&A pairs with legal-safe framing, and three proactive narrative insertions.","inputs":[{"label":"revenue, EBITDA, EPS vs. consensus"},{"label":"list 2-3"},{"label":"list, e.g., margin pressure, guidance cut, CEO departure"},{"label":"paste or summarise"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"2-3 hours","output_kind":"document","sample_output":"**CEO Opening (excerpt)**\\n\'Revenue grew 12% to $2.4B — our sixth consecutive quarter of double-digit growth. Importantly, this was broad-based: all three segments expanded. We\'re reaffirming full-year guidance of $9.8–10.0B.\'\\n\\n**Hardest Q — Analyst simulation**\\nQ: \'Gross margin compressed 180bps despite the pricing actions you took in Q2. What\'s structurally different?\'\\nA: \'Two items: first, the new data-centre contracts we signed in H2 carry lower initial margins that normalise by year 2; second, we deliberately accelerated cloud migration spend. Excluding both, underlying margins expanded 40bps.\'\\n\\n⚠️ Legal flag: \'We expect to close the acquisition by year-end\' is forward-looking — add customary safe-harbour language.","dateAdded":"2026-06-05","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Financial Planning & Analysis","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Zero-Based Budget Line-Item Challenger","prompt":"\\"Act as a Zero-Based Budgeting (ZBB) facilitator. I\'m reviewing [department]\'s budget for [fiscal year].\\n\\nBudget data: [paste cost centre lines — account, prior year actual, current year request, variance %]\\n\\nFor each line item above [threshold, e.g., $50K]:\\n1. Ask the three ZBB challenge questions: Is this necessary? Is this the right amount? Is this the right time?\\n2. Benchmark against industry norms where data exists\\n3. Propose three challenge scenarios: Zero (eliminate), 50% (halve), 100% (approve as-is)\\n4. Flag items where the prior year actual was unspent by >20%\\n5. Output a decision table with recommended stance and rationale\\n\\nBusiness context: [growth stage, cost reduction target, strategic priorities]\\"","tags":["zero-based-budget","zbb","cost-reduction","budgeting","fp&a","half-day"],"best_for":"FP&A directors, CFOs, cost transformation leads, management consultants","source":"McKinsey CFO Practice — ZBB implementation playbook; OpenAI enterprise FP&A pilots","outcome":"A ZBB decision table with eliminate / halve / approve recommendations for every line above threshold, with benchmarks and challenge rationale — typically identifies 15–25% addressable savings.","inputs":[{"label":"department"},{"label":"fiscal year"},{"label":"paste cost centre lines — account, prior year actual, current year request, variance %"},{"label":"threshold, e.g., $50K"},{"label":"growth stage, cost reduction target, strategic priorities"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel"],"est_time":"Half-day","output_kind":"table","sample_output":"| Account | PY Actual | Request | ZBB Stance | Rationale |\\n|---------|-----------|---------|------------|----------|\\n| External consulting | $420K | $490K | 50% — $245K | 40% unspent in PY; consolidate to 2 firms |\\n| Software licences | $180K | $210K | Approve | Per-seat growth aligned to headcount plan |\\n| Travel & entertainment | $95K | $110K | Zero — video-first policy | Benchmark: $800/head vs. $1,400 requested |\\n| Training | $60K | $85K | 50% — $43K | Internal AI upskilling covers 60% of need |\\n\\n**Addressable savings identified: $312K (22% of reviewed spend)**","dateAdded":"2026-06-05","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Corporate Finance & Deal Support","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Revenue Recognition Risk Screener (ASC 606 / IFRS 15)","prompt":"\\"You are a Big 4 revenue recognition specialist. Review the following customer contracts and identify all revenue recognition risks under [ASC 606 / IFRS 15].\\n\\nContract details: [paste contract summary or key commercial terms]\\nOur accounting policy: [paste rev rec policy from annual report]\\nKey questions to answer:\\n1. Identify all distinct performance obligations\\n2. Determine standalone selling prices (SSP) for each obligation\\n3. Flag variable consideration (rebates, bonuses, SLAs, refunds) and whether constraint applies\\n4. Identify any bill-and-hold, principal-vs-agent, licensing, or long-term contract issues\\n5. Recommend journal entry treatment and disclosure requirements\\n6. Rate overall revenue recognition complexity: Low / Medium / High / Specialist Required\\"","tags":["revenue-recognition","asc606","ifrs15","accounting","audit","advanced"],"best_for":"Controllers, technical accounting teams, auditors, CFOs at SaaS/services companies","source":"Deloitte Revenue Recognition tool; KPMG IFRS 15 handbook; PwC enterprise AI deployments","outcome":"A performance-obligation schedule with SSP allocations, a variable-consideration assessment, and a recommended journal entry template — with a complexity flag for items needing external specialist review.","inputs":[{"label":"ASC 606 / IFRS 15"},{"label":"paste contract summary or key commercial terms"},{"label":"paste rev rec policy from annual report"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"2-4 hours per contract","output_kind":"document","sample_output":"**Contract: Acme SaaS + Implementation + Training Bundle — $480K**\\n\\n**Performance obligations identified (3):**\\n1. SaaS subscription — $320K SSP — recognised ratably over 24 months\\n2. Implementation services — $130K SSP — POC method (estimated 65% complete at period end → $84.5K recognised)\\n3. Training — $30K SSP — on delivery (2 days in Feb)\\n\\n**Variable consideration:** SLA penalty clause (max $24K) → fully constrained; not included in transaction price\\n\\n**Complexity: Medium** — Implementation % completion estimate requires documented methodology\\n\\n**Journal entry (period end):** DR Contract asset $84.5K / CR Revenue $84.5K","dateAdded":"2026-06-05","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Financial Planning & Analysis","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"CFO Board Pack Builder","prompt":"\\"You are a CFO preparing the monthly/quarterly board pack. I\'ll give you the financial data; you produce the narrative and key messages.\\n\\nFinancial inputs:\\n- P&L: [paste actuals vs. budget vs. prior year — at least revenue, gross margin, EBITDA, net income]\\n- Cash: [opening balance, operating cash flow, capex, closing balance, days cash on hand]\\n- Balance sheet highlights: [total assets, net debt, working capital]\\n- Key operational metrics: [headcount, revenue per head, NRR/churn if SaaS, etc.]\\n\\nBoard preferences: [e.g., \'they care most about cash and NRR; less interested in EBITDA bridge\']\\nAny sensitive items to handle carefully: [restructuring, miss vs. guidance, etc.]\\n\\nProduce:\\n1. 1-page CFO narrative (plain language, no jargon)\\n2. 3 bullet \'state of the business\' for the board cover page\\n3. 5 \'questions the board will ask\' with your recommended answers\\n4. An EBITDA bridge (budget to actual) as a table\\n5. A 3-sentence forward-looking statement for the CEO to read\\"","tags":["board-pack","cfo","reporting","governance","monthly-close","2-hours"],"best_for":"CFOs, FP&A directors, financial controllers at scale-ups and mid-market companies","source":"CFO Connect community — board pack best practices; OpenAI enterprise CFO workflow pilots","outcome":"A ready-to-paste CFO board narrative, EBITDA bridge table, five board Q&A pairs, and a CEO forward-looking statement — from raw financials in under an hour.","inputs":[{"label":"paste actuals vs. budget vs. prior year — at least revenue, gross margin, EBITDA, net income"},{"label":"opening balance, operating cash flow, capex, closing balance, days cash on hand"},{"label":"total assets, net debt, working capital"},{"label":"headcount, revenue per head, NRR/churn if SaaS, etc."},{"label":"e.g., \'they care most about cash and NRR; less interested in EBITDA bridge\'"},{"label":"restructuring, miss vs. guidance, etc."}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"1-2 hours","output_kind":"document","sample_output":"**CFO Narrative (excerpt)**\\nRevenue of £8.4M came in £210K ahead of budget (+2.6%), driven by enterprise new business closing 3 weeks earlier than planned. Gross margin compressed 80bps to 68.2% as we absorbed the new AWS region migration costs; this is a one-off and normalises next quarter. EBITDA of £1.1M was £90K below budget — entirely the margin item; operating leverage remains on track for H2.\\n\\n**EBITDA Bridge**\\n| Item | £K |\\n|------|----|\\n| Budget EBITDA | 1,190 |\\n| + Revenue beat | +210 |\\n| − Gross margin miss | −310 |\\n| − Opex (within plan) | +10 |\\n| **Actual EBITDA** | **1,100** |","dateAdded":"2026-06-05","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Financial Planning & Analysis","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Working Capital Optimisation Playbook","prompt":"\\"Act as a working capital specialist. Analyse my company\'s cash conversion cycle and identify the highest-value improvement opportunities.\\n\\nCompany data:\\n- Revenue (trailing 12 months): [value]\\n- Accounts receivable: [value] — DSO target: [days]\\n- Inventory: [value] — DIO target: [days] (skip if services business)\\n- Accounts payable: [value] — DPO target: [days]\\n- Industry: [sector]\\n- Current CCC: [calculate or provide]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Calculate DSO, DIO, DPO, and CCC\\n2. Benchmark against industry peers (use known benchmarks for [sector])\\n3. Quantify the cash release if each metric hits the industry median\\n4. For each lever, give 3 specific actions (e.g., \'move net-30 customers to net-15 with 1% early pay discount\')\\n5. Build a 12-month roadmap with estimated cash impact by quarter\\"","tags":["working-capital","cash-flow","dso","dpo","treasury","half-day"],"best_for":"CFOs, treasurers, financial controllers, working capital managers","source":"BCG Treasury Benchmark; REL Hackett working capital survey; PwC CFO AI tools","outcome":"A benchmarked CCC analysis with quantified cash-release potential (typically 3–8% of revenue) and a prioritised 12-month improvement roadmap with owner and estimated impact by quarter.","inputs":[{"label":"value"},{"label":"value"},{"label":"days"},{"label":"value"},{"label":"days"},{"label":"value"},{"label":"days"},{"label":"sector"},{"label":"calculate or provide"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel"],"est_time":"Half-day","output_kind":"table","sample_output":"**CCC Analysis vs. Industry Median (SaaS)**\\n| Metric | Current | Industry Median | Gap | Cash Release |\\n|--------|---------|-----------------|-----|-------------|\\n| DSO | 52 days | 38 days | −14 | +$4.2M |\\n| DPO | 28 days | 45 days | +17 | +$5.1M |\\n| CCC | 24 days | −7 days | −31 | **+$9.3M** |\\n\\n**Top actions (DSO):**\\n1. Automate dunning: email D+3, call D+7, escalate D+14 — expected: −4 days DSO\\n2. Offer 1.5% early pay discount for payment within 10 days — expected: 35% take-up\\n3. Require credit card on file for accounts <$50K ARR — expected: −8 days DSO on SMB segment","dateAdded":"2026-06-05","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Corporate Finance & Deal Support","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Treasury FX Exposure & Hedging Strategy Brief","prompt":"\\"You are a corporate treasurer. Analyse our foreign currency exposures and recommend a hedging strategy.\\n\\nExposure data:\\n- Functional currency: [e.g., USD]\\n- Revenue by currency: [paste — e.g., EUR 35%, GBP 20%, JPY 10%, other 35%]\\n- Cost base by currency: [paste]\\n- Net exposure by currency pair: [calculate or provide]\\n- Forecast horizon: [months]\\n- Board\'s risk appetite: [e.g., hedge 70-90% of forecast net exposure for the next 6 months]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Calculate net transactional exposure by currency\\n2. Identify which exposures exceed the hedge threshold\\n3. Recommend hedging instruments (forward, option, zero-cost collar) with cost-benefit rationale\\n4. Draft the hedge accounting designation narrative required under IAS 39 / IFRS 9\\n5. Build a sensitivity table: P&L impact at ±5%, ±10%, ±15% FX moves (hedged vs. unhedged)\\"","tags":["fx","hedging","treasury","ifrs9","currency-risk","advanced"],"best_for":"Corporate treasurers, CFOs at multinationals, finance directors with international revenue","source":"Association of Corporate Treasurers (ACT) best practice; Bloomberg Treasury analytics; KPMG IFRS 9 guide","outcome":"A net exposure schedule by currency, an instrument recommendation with cost comparison, an IFRS 9 hedge designation narrative, and a P&L sensitivity table — ready for board or audit committee review.","inputs":[{"label":"e.g., USD"},{"label":"paste — e.g., EUR 35%, GBP 20%, JPY 10%, other 35%"},{"label":"paste"},{"label":"calculate or provide"},{"label":"months"},{"label":"e.g., hedge 70-90% of forecast net exposure for the next 6 months"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel"],"est_time":"Half-day","output_kind":"document","sample_output":"**Net Exposure — EUR (largest):** +$18.4M receivable over 6 months\\n**Hedge target (80%):** $14.7M\\n\\n**Instrument comparison:**\\n| Instrument | Cost | Protection | Upside |\\n|------------|------|-----------|--------|\\n| Forward | Zero (locked rate) | Full | None |\\n| EUR Put option | $147K premium | Full below strike | Retained |\\n| Zero-cost collar | Zero | Below floor | Capped |\\n**Recommendation:** Zero-cost collar (floor 1.04, cap 1.12) — board risk appetite met at zero cost\\n\\n**P&L Sensitivity (EUR, hedged)**\\n| FX Move | Unhedged P&L | Hedged P&L |\\n|---------|--------------|-----------|\\n| −15% | −$2.8M | −$0.3M |\\n| −10% | −$1.8M | −$0.2M |\\n| +10% | +$1.8M | +$1.3M |","dateAdded":"2026-06-05","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Financial Planning & Analysis","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Debt Covenant Compliance Monitor","prompt":"\\"Act as a financial covenant analyst. I need to monitor and report on our debt covenants every quarter.\\n\\nCredit agreement details:\\n- Lender / facility type: [e.g., €50M revolving credit facility, syndicated]\\n- Financial covenants: [list each — e.g., \'Net Leverage ≤ 3.5×\', \'Interest Cover ≥ 3.0×\', \'Minimum Liquidity $10M\']\\n- Testing frequency: [quarterly / semi-annual]\\n- Cure period: [e.g., 30 days]\\n\\nCurrent period financials: [paste EBITDA, net debt, interest charge, cash balance]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Calculate headroom on each covenant\\n2. Flag any covenants within 20% of the limit (amber) or breached (red)\\n3. Run a stress test: at what EBITDA level does each covenant breach?\\n4. Draft the compliance certificate narrative for lender submission\\n5. Suggest 3 actions to increase headroom on the tightest covenant\\"","tags":["covenants","debt","lenders","compliance","credit","treasury","intermediate"],"best_for":"CFOs, financial controllers, treasurers, PE-backed companies, leveraged businesses","source":"Loan Market Association (LMA) covenant monitoring templates; Deloitte debt advisory practice","outcome":"A covenant dashboard with RAG status, a lender-ready compliance certificate narrative, a break-even EBITDA table, and three specific headroom-improvement actions.","inputs":[{"label":"e.g., €50M revolving credit facility, syndicated"},{"label":"list each — e.g., \'Net Leverage ≤ 3.5×\', \'Interest Cover ≥ 3.0×\', \'Minimum Liquidity $10M\'"},{"label":"quarterly / semi-annual"},{"label":"e.g., 30 days"},{"label":"paste EBITDA, net debt, interest charge, cash balance"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel"],"est_time":"2-3 hours","output_kind":"table","sample_output":"**Covenant Dashboard — Q3 2026**\\n| Covenant | Limit | Actual | Headroom | Status |\\n|----------|-------|--------|----------|--------|\\n| Net Leverage | ≤3.5× | 3.1× | 0.4× (11%) | 🟡 Amber |\\n| Interest Cover | ≥3.0× | 4.8× | 1.8× (60%) | 🟢 Green |\\n| Min Liquidity | ≥$10M | $18.2M | $8.2M | 🟢 Green |\\n\\n**Break-even EBITDA (Net Leverage breach):** EBITDA < $28.4M (current: $32.1M)\\n\\n**Headroom actions:**\\n1. Accelerate £3M property disposal — removes from net debt calculation\\n2. Reclassify €1.4M capitalised software to opex — reduces debt by IFRS 16 impact\\n3. Negotiate covenant reset with 30bps spread increase — buys 0.5× leverage headroom","dateAdded":"2026-06-05","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Corporate Finance & Deal Support","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Private Equity Portfolio KPI Roll-Up & Board Memo","prompt":"\\"You are a PE portfolio management director. Roll up the monthly reporting from [number] portfolio companies into a fund-level board update.\\n\\nPortfolio data (paste for each company):\\n- Company name, sector, entry date, entry EV, entry net debt\\n- Latest LTM revenue, EBITDA, net debt, cash\\n- KPIs: [company-specific, e.g., ARR, churn, NRR for SaaS; EBITDA/MW for energy; EBITDA/bed for healthcare]\\n- Management\'s key messages: [1-2 sentences per company]\\n- Any covenant, refinancing, or M&A activity: [note]\\n\\nProduce:\\n1. Portfolio dashboard: entry multiple, current EV (based on [multiple assumption]), MOIC, IRR\\n2. Flag any company with >2 consecutive EBITDA misses or negative EBITDA trajectory\\n3. Highlight top 2 value creation opportunities and top 2 risks across the portfolio\\n4. Draft a 1-page board narrative in the style of a GP update letter\\"","tags":["private-equity","portfolio-monitoring","gp-lp","fund","board","advanced"],"best_for":"PE portfolio managers, operating partners, fund CFOs, GP finance teams","source":"ILPA portfolio monitoring guidelines; KKR / Blackstone operational excellence frameworks","outcome":"A fund-level dashboard with live MOIC and IRR per company, a traffic-light flags table, top 2 value-creation and risk items, and a GP board narrative ready for LP distribution.","inputs":[{"label":"number"},{"label":"company-specific, e.g., ARR, churn, NRR for SaaS; EBITDA/MW for energy; EBITDA/bed for healthcare"},{"label":"1-2 sentences per company"},{"label":"note"},{"label":"multiple assumption"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel"],"est_time":"Half-day","output_kind":"table","sample_output":"**Portfolio Dashboard — May 2026**\\n| Company | Entry EV | Current EV | MOIC | IRR | Flag |\\n|---------|----------|------------|------|-----|------|\\n| Acme SaaS | 6.2× | 9.1× | 2.4× | 31% | 🟢 |\\n| Beta Infra | 8.0× | 7.4× | 1.1× | 4% | 🔴 3rd miss |\\n| Gamma Health | 10.5× | 14.2× | 1.8× | 22% | 🟢 |\\n\\n**Top risk:** Beta Infra — EBITDA 3 consecutive misses; recommend operational review and management reset before Q3.\\n\\n**Top value-creation:** Acme SaaS — NRR at 118%; bolt-on of TechCo would lift EV by est. €22M at current multiple.","dateAdded":"2026-06-05","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Financial Planning & Analysis","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Month-End Close Accelerator","prompt":"\\"You are a financial controller. Help me compress our month-end close from [current days] to [target days].\\n\\nCurrent close process:\\n- Day 1: [describe activities]\\n- Days 2-3: [describe]\\n- Days 4-5: [describe]\\n- Biggest bottleneck: [describe]\\n- ERP / system: [e.g., SAP, NetSuite, Oracle]\\n- Team size: [number]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Map our close process against the Fast Close benchmark (top quartile: ≤3 days)\\n2. Identify the top 3 bottlenecks and root causes\\n3. Suggest specific automation or process changes for each bottleneck\\n4. Draft a 30-60-90 day implementation roadmap\\n5. Write the journal entry review checklist for accruals, prepayments, and intercompany eliminations\\"","tags":["month-end-close","controller","accounting","automation","fast-close","1-day"],"best_for":"Financial controllers, accounting managers, CFOs looking to accelerate close","source":"FSN Finance Function of the Future; Hackett Group close benchmark; Trintech close acceleration methodology","outcome":"A benchmarked close gap analysis, root-cause map, 30-60-90 day roadmap with quick wins, and a journal entry review checklist — typically reduces close cycle by 1-2 days in 90 days.","inputs":[{"label":"current days"},{"label":"target days"},{"label":"describe activities"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"e.g., SAP, NetSuite, Oracle"},{"label":"number"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"2-3 hours","output_kind":"document","sample_output":"**Bottleneck #1: Intercompany reconciliation (Day 3–4)**\\nRoot cause: 12 entities post in different time zones; no automated matching\\nFix: Implement continuous matching in NetSuite (native IC module) + hard cutoff at D+1 18:00 UTC\\nEstimated saving: 0.8 days\\n\\n**Journal Entry Review Checklist**\\n- [ ] Accrued expenses: all POs >$10K with no invoice matched?\\n- [ ] Prepayments: confirm amortisation schedule updated for any new contracts\\n- [ ] Payroll accrual: H2 headcount change reflected?\\n- [ ] Intercompany: all IC invoices matched and eliminated?\\n- [ ] Revenue: deferred revenue roll-forward agrees to contract schedule?","dateAdded":"2026-06-05","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Corporate Finance & Deal Support","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Transfer Pricing Documentation Assistant","prompt":"\\"You are a transfer pricing specialist. Help me document our intercompany transactions to comply with OECD BEPS Action 13 (Master File / Local File) and [country]\'s local transfer pricing rules.\\n\\nIntercompany transactions to document:\\n- Type: [e.g., management fees, IP royalties, intercompany loans, distribution services, shared services]\\n- Flow: [from entity A in country X to entity B in country Y]\\n- Annual value: [amount]\\n- Pricing method used: [e.g., TNMM, CUP, cost-plus]\\n- Comparable data available: [yes/no — describe]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Confirm whether the chosen pricing method is appropriate per OECD guidelines\\n2. Identify the 3 highest audit risk areas for this transaction\\n3. Draft the Local File functional analysis narrative (3-4 paragraphs)\\n4. Suggest the benchmark search criteria for a TNMM comparable set\\n5. Flag any documentation gaps that would weaken the position in a tax authority challenge\\"","tags":["transfer-pricing","tax","beps","international-tax","oecd","advanced"],"best_for":"Tax directors, transfer pricing managers, Big 4 tax teams, multinationals","source":"OECD BEPS Action 13 guidelines; Deloitte Transfer Pricing Advisory; EY TP documentation practice","outcome":"A Local File functional analysis narrative, a documentation gap assessment, recommended benchmark criteria, and an audit-risk ranking — typically covering 80% of a TP documentation sprint in one session.","inputs":[{"label":"country"},{"label":"e.g., management fees, IP royalties, intercompany loans, distribution services, shared services"},{"label":"from entity A in country X to entity B in country Y"},{"label":"amount"},{"label":"e.g., TNMM, CUP, cost-plus"},{"label":"yes/no — describe"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Half-day per transaction","output_kind":"document","sample_output":"**Method assessment:** TNMM is appropriate for a limited-risk distributor; CUP would require internal comparables you don\'t have.\\n\\n**Functional Analysis (excerpt):**\\n\'Entity B (UK distribution subsidiary) performs limited distribution functions: it takes title to goods, manages local warehousing, and bears routine market risk. Entity A (US parent) owns the IP, bears product liability, and sets pricing policy. Under the OECD functional analysis, Entity B is characterised as a limited-risk distributor and TNMM is the most appropriate method.\'\\n\\n**Top 3 audit risks:**\\n1. Management fee quantum — no time-recording supports the 3% allocation\\n2. IP royalty rate — last benchmarked 2019; HMRC likely to challenge currency\\n3. Intercompany loan rate — Libor-based; must be updated to SONIA","dateAdded":"2026-06-05","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"ESG / CSRD Disclosure Writer","prompt":"\\"You are a sustainability reporting specialist. Help me draft disclosures for [CSRD / TCFD / GRI Standards / all three].\\n\\nCompany context:\\n- Sector: [industry]\\n- Annual revenue: [value]\\n- Headcount: [number]\\n- Reporting year: [year]\\n\\nData I have available:\\n- Scope 1 emissions: [tCO2e]\\n- Scope 2 emissions (market-based): [tCO2e]\\n- Scope 3 categories covered: [list]\\n- Energy consumption: [MWh, % renewable]\\n- Climate risks identified: [physical / transition — describe]\\n- Targets: [net zero by year, SBTi status]\\n- Social metrics: [gender pay gap, diversity ratios, injury rates]\\n- Governance: [describe board ESG oversight]\\n\\nProduce:\\n1. TCFD-aligned climate risk narrative (2 pages)\\n2. GRI 305 Emissions disclosure table\\n3. CSRD ESRS E1 energy and climate KPI table\\n4. Identify the top 3 data gaps that an auditor will flag\\n5. Suggest 3 targets we could credibly commit to based on current data\\"","tags":["esg","csrd","tcfd","sustainability","reporting","disclosure","intermediate"],"best_for":"Sustainability managers, CFOs at EU-regulated companies, ESG controllers, IR teams","source":"EFRAG CSRD technical guidance; TCFD recommendations; GRI 305 standard; PwC ESG reporting tools","outcome":"A TCFD climate risk narrative, GRI 305 emissions table, CSRD ESRS E1 KPI table, a data-gap log, and three credible target proposals — covering the core of a first CSRD report in one session.","inputs":[{"label":"CSRD / TCFD / GRI Standards / all three"},{"label":"industry"},{"label":"value"},{"label":"number"},{"label":"year"},{"label":"tCO2e"},{"label":"tCO2e"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"MWh, % renewable"},{"label":"physical / transition — describe"},{"label":"net zero by year, SBTi status"},{"label":"gender pay gap, diversity ratios, injury rates"},{"label":"describe board ESG oversight"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Half-day","output_kind":"document","sample_output":"**GRI 305-1 Direct (Scope 1) Emissions**\\n| Metric | 2024 | 2025 | Change |\\n|--------|------|------|--------|\\n| Gross Scope 1 (tCO2e) | 4,820 | 4,310 | −11% |\\n| Natural gas combustion | 3,200 | 2,780 | −13% |\\n| Company vehicles | 1,620 | 1,530 | −6% |\\n\\n**TCFD Physical Risk (excerpt):** \'Our primary manufacturing facility in Valencia faces elevated chronic risk from rising average temperatures (RCP 4.5: +1.8°C by 2050) and acute risk from increased flooding frequency (return period shortening from 1-in-50 to 1-in-25 by 2040 under IPCC Tier 2 scenarios).\'\\n\\n**Data gap #1:** Scope 3 Category 11 (use of sold products) not calculated — material for a hardware manufacturer; auditor will qualify.","dateAdded":"2026-06-05","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Corporate Finance & Deal Support","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Commercial Lending Credit Memo Writer","prompt":"\\"You are a commercial lending analyst at a bank or credit fund. Write a credit memo for the following borrower.\\n\\nBorrower details:\\n- Company name & description: [industry, business model, years in business]\\n- Loan request: [amount, tenor, purpose — e.g., acquisition finance, capex, working capital]\\n- Financial summary (last 3 years): [revenue, EBITDA, net debt, capex, interest expense]\\n- Collateral: [describe assets offered]\\n- Existing debt: [describe senior, mezzanine, leases]\\n- Management team: [brief bio or note]\\n- Key risks identified: [list 3-5]\\n\\nProduce a credit memo covering:\\n1. Executive summary (recommend: Approve / Decline / Approve with conditions)\\n2. Business risk assessment (industry, competitive position, management)\\n3. Financial risk assessment with ratio analysis (leverage, coverage, liquidity)\\n4. Structural and collateral analysis\\n5. Conditions and covenants recommended\\"","tags":["credit","lending","banking","credit-memo","underwriting","intermediate"],"best_for":"Commercial bankers, credit analysts, private credit funds, CFOs preparing for financing","source":"ACIB credit analysis training; JPMorgan commercial banking underwriting standards; OpenAI enterprise banking pilots","outcome":"A full credit memo with executive recommendation, 5-section risk analysis, ratio table, and proposed covenant package — covering the core of a credit application in 2-3 hours rather than 2 days.","inputs":[{"label":"industry, business model, years in business"},{"label":"amount, tenor, purpose — e.g., acquisition finance, capex, working capital"},{"label":"revenue, EBITDA, net debt, capex, interest expense"},{"label":"describe assets offered"},{"label":"describe senior, mezzanine, leases"},{"label":"brief bio or note"},{"label":"list 3-5"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"2-3 hours","output_kind":"document","sample_output":"**Executive Summary — RECOMMEND APPROVE (with conditions)**\\nAcme Manufacturing Ltd requests a £7.5M, 5-year term loan to finance the acquisition of a complementary distribution business. Pro-forma leverage of 2.8× EBITDA is within policy (3.5× max); interest cover of 4.1× provides adequate headroom. Primary risk is customer concentration (top 3 = 58% revenue); mitigated by contractual 24-month frameworks and proposed covenant structure.\\n\\n**Ratio Analysis**\\n| Ratio | PY | LTM | Policy |\\n|-------|----|-----|--------|\\n| Net Leverage | 1.9× | 2.8× | ≤3.5× ✓ |\\n| EBITDA/Interest | 5.2× | 4.1× | ≥3.0× ✓ |\\n| Current Ratio | 1.4 | 1.3 | ≥1.0 ✓ |\\n\\n**Conditions:** (1) Audited accounts within 120 days; (2) No additional debt without consent; (3) Annual covenant test.","dateAdded":"2026-06-05","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Investor Relations Q&A Library Builder","prompt":"\\"You are an investor relations specialist. Build a comprehensive Q&A library from our earnings materials so the IR team can answer any investor question consistently and quickly.\\n\\nInputs:\\n- Last 4 earnings call transcripts: [paste or attach]\\n- Annual report / 10-K narrative sections: [paste or summarise]\\n- Current consensus estimates: [EPS, revenue, EBITDA for next 2 years]\\n- Recent analyst notes/themes: [summarise key concerns raised]\\n- Guidance given: [list all quantitative guidance items]\\n\\nProduce:\\n1. 40-question Q&A library organised by theme (financials, strategy, competition, ESG, guidance)\\n2. For each answer: a 3-sentence \'short form\' and a 1-paragraph \'long form\'\\n3. Flag 5 questions we\'ve never answered well — with a recommended new answer\\n4. Identify any statements in our past calls that contradict current guidance\\n5. Draft 3 proactive narrative updates for the next investor day\\"","tags":["investor-relations","ir","q&a","earnings","communications","half-day"],"best_for":"IR directors, CFOs, communications teams at public companies","source":"NIRI best practices; Morgan Stanley IR workbench (OpenAI enterprise deployment); Goldman Sachs IR AI tools","outcome":"A 40-question IR Q&A library with short-form and long-form answers, a \'weak answers\' improvement list, a consistency check across past guidance, and three narrative update drafts for investor day.","inputs":[{"label":"paste or attach"},{"label":"paste or summarise"},{"label":"EPS, revenue, EBITDA for next 2 years"},{"label":"summarise key concerns raised"},{"label":"list all quantitative guidance items"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Half-day","output_kind":"document","sample_output":"**Q: Why has free cash flow conversion been below 70% for three consecutive quarters?**\\n*Short form:* The primary driver is timing of customer collections — our enterprise renewal cycle concentrates cash receipts in Q1 and Q3. Underlying conversion ex-timing is 82%.\\n*Long form:* Free cash flow conversion of 64–68% over the last three quarters reflects two items: first, we shifted our largest enterprise renewal cohort to January starts (from October) to align with customer fiscal years — this creates a structural Q4 working capital outflow that reverses in Q1. Second, we accelerated $12M of data-centre capex to lock in pricing. Stripping both items, underlying FCF conversion is 82%, consistent with historical norms.\\n\\n⚠️ Consistency flag: Q1 2025 transcript states \'we expect FCF conversion of 75%+ for the full year\' — current guidance of 68% contradicts this; recommend proactive explanation.","dateAdded":"2026-06-05","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Financial Planning & Analysis","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Mid-Year Budget Reforecast Automation","prompt":"\\"You are an FP&A lead doing the Q2/Q3 mid-year budget reforecast. Help me rebuild the full-year view from actuals + revised assumptions.\\n\\nActuals (H1):\\n- Revenue: [value vs. budget]\\n- Gross margin: [% vs. budget]\\n- Opex by category: [paste]\\n- EBITDA: [value vs. budget]\\n\\nRevised assumptions for H2:\\n- Revenue: [driver — price, volume, mix change]\\n- Headcount changes: [hires/exits planned]\\n- One-off items: [restructuring, M&A costs, etc.]\\n- Market conditions: [describe any macro or sector change]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Build the H2 bridge from budget to reforecast (price / volume / mix / cost)\\n2. Produce 3 scenarios: Base (most likely), Bear (−15% revenue), Bull (+10% revenue)\\n3. Identify the 3 biggest P&L risks and quantify each\\n4. Write a 1-page reforecast narrative for CFO review\\n5. Flag any line items where H1 run-rate implies H2 budget is no longer achievable\\"","tags":["reforecast","fp&a","budget","scenario-planning","mid-year","half-day"],"best_for":"FP&A analysts and directors, business controllers, finance business partners","source":"AFP FP&A Guide to reforecasting; OpenAI enterprise FP&A automation pilots; Anaplan best-practice reforecast methodology","outcome":"A base/bear/bull reforecast with H2 bridge, a 3-risk P&L table with quantified impact, a CFO-ready reforecast narrative, and flagged budget lines that H1 actuals make unachievable.","inputs":[{"label":"value vs. budget"},{"label":"% vs. budget"},{"label":"paste"},{"label":"value vs. budget"},{"label":"driver — price, volume, mix change"},{"label":"hires/exits planned"},{"label":"restructuring, M&A costs, etc."},{"label":"describe any macro or sector change"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel"],"est_time":"Half-day","output_kind":"document","sample_output":"**H2 Revenue Bridge (Budget to Reforecast)**\\n| Driver | £M |\\n|--------|----- |\\n| Budget H2 revenue | 52.0 |\\n| − Price (avg −2% on renewals) | −1.0 |\\n| − Volume (2 lost enterprise deals) | −2.4 |\\n| + Mix (upsell beat) | +0.8 |\\n| **Base Reforecast** | **49.4** |\\n\\n**Scenarios:**\\n| | Revenue | EBITDA | EBITDA margin |\\n|--|---------|--------|---------------|\\n| Bull | £54.2M | £9.1M | 16.8% |\\n| Base | £49.4M | £7.3M | 14.8% |\\n| Bear | £42.0M | £4.2M | 10.0% |\\n\\n⚠️ Flag: Sales capacity budget assumes 12 AEs fully ramped by July — H1 hiring miss means only 9 will be productive; H2 new-logo budget is unachievable by ~£2.8M.","dateAdded":"2026-06-05","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Research & Strategy","section":"AI Market Intelligence","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"AI Industry Weekly Briefing","prompt":"You are an AI market analyst. Based on the following AI news items from this week, produce a structured executive briefing.\\n\\nNews items: [paste 5-10 recent AI headlines or summaries]\\n\\nDeliver:\\n1. Top 3 signal events (with 1-sentence why it matters)\\n2. Model capability shifts (any new benchmarks or releases)\\n3. Investment and funding round summary\\n4. Policy and regulation changes\\n5. One contrarian take or underreported signal\\n6. Recommended actions for a product team building with AI","tags":["AI market","strategy","weekly-brief","news","intelligence"],"best_for":"Product managers, CTOs, investors, founders tracking the AI landscape","source":"Moonshots with Peter Diamandis EP #262 — weekly AI market recap methodology","outcome":"A 400-word executive briefing with 5 structured sections ready to share with a leadership team.","inputs":[{"label":"paste 5-10 recent AI headlines or summaries"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"document","dateAdded":"2026-06-07","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Research & Strategy","section":"AI Market Intelligence","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"AI Company Valuation Analysis","prompt":"Analyse the valuation of the following AI company and assess whether it is justified.\\n\\nCompany: [company name]\\nLatest valuation: [amount]\\nRevenue run-rate: [ARR or MRR x12]\\nGrowth rate: [YoY %]\\nKey metrics: [MAU, API calls, enterprise customers]\\nMain model or product: [describe]\\nMain competitors: [list]\\n\\nProvide:\\n1. Revenue multiple implied by the valuation\\n2. Comparable multiples from public AI comps\\n3. Three bull-case assumptions required to justify the valuation\\n4. Three bear-case risks that could compress it\\n5. Your overall verdict: fair / overvalued / undervalued — and why","tags":["AI market","valuation","investment","strategy","analysis"],"best_for":"Investors, analysts, founders benchmarking their own company, finance teams","source":"Anthropic $965B valuation analysis context; Diamandis EP #262","outcome":"A structured valuation memo with revenue multiples, bull/bear assumptions, and a clear verdict.","inputs":[{"label":"company name"},{"label":"amount"},{"label":"ARR or MRR x12"},{"label":"YoY %"},{"label":"MAU, API calls, enterprise customers"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"list"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"20 min","output_kind":"document","dateAdded":"2026-06-07","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]},{"domain":"Research & Strategy","section":"AI Adoption","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"AI Adoption Gap Analysis for My Business","prompt":"Help me identify where my business is behind on AI adoption compared to industry leaders.\\n\\nMy business: [industry, size, main function]\\nAI tools we currently use: [list or none]\\nKey workflows taking most time: [describe 3-5]\\nMain pain points: [describe]\\nTeam size and technical capability: [describe]\\nBudget for AI tools: [monthly range]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Rate our current AI adoption on a 1-5 scale and explain\\n2. List the 5 highest-ROI AI use cases for a business like mine\\n3. For each: recommended tool, time to implement, expected time saving\\n4. Roadmap: what to do in Week 1, Month 1, and Month 3\\n5. Flag one quick win that takes less than 2 hours to implement today","tags":["AI adoption","business","ROI","quick-wins","productivity"],"best_for":"SME owners, operations managers, non-technical teams, executives exploring AI ROI","source":"Canada AI for All Strategy; Diamandis EP #262 adoption analysis","outcome":"A personalised AI adoption roadmap with 5 ranked use cases, tools, timelines, and one same-day quick win.","inputs":[{"label":"industry, size, main function"},{"label":"list or none"},{"label":"describe 3-5"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"monthly range"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"30 min","output_kind":"plan","dateAdded":"2026-06-07","related_tools":["claude","chatgpt"]}]');

